title: monte cristo sandwiches
directions: Combine mayonnaise, mustard and honey, stir well.
Spread mixture on one side of each bread slice.
Place on slice each of turkey, ham, Swiss cheese and Chedder cheese on top of 4 bread slices.
Top with remaining bread.
Cut each sandwich in half diagonally.
Secure with wooden picks.

title: broccoli, chicken and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until done.
Saute pepper, onions and celery in butter; simmer until tender.
Mix broccoli, cooked, deboned chicken, vegetables, salt and milk.
Mix well.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Place cut up chicken in casserole.
Mix the next 6 ingredients; pour over chicken.
Marinate overnight, at least 8 hours.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover; continue baking 1/2 hour.
Serves 4.

title: italian broiled chicken
directions: Cut chickens.
Brush both sides with salad dressing.
Cover, refrigerate 4 to 5 hours or overnight.
Season chickens with salt and pepper.
Place in broiling pan, skin side down.
Broil 5 to 7-inches from heat for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Baste with salad dressing.
Turn, repeat other side for 15 minutes until golden.

title: shrimp creole (bayou style)
directions: Saute bell pepper, onion, celery and mushrooms in margarine until barely tender, stirring often.
Stir in flour, then tomato sauce.
This will produce a very thick mixture.
Slowly add water, while stirring until mixture thins to desired consistency.
(Be careful not to get it too soupy.)
Stir in shrimp, lemon juice, soy sauce, bay leaves, garlic, salt, black pepper, sherry and parsley flakes.
If you want your creole hot, use the Tabasco sauce.
(Be careful; it only takes a few drops.)
Cover and simmer over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add green onions; replace cover and simmer 10 more minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in file.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 10 to 12 servings. Magnifique!

title: graham cracker pie crust
directions: In small bowl, combine crumbs, sugar and melted margarine. Press mixture in bottom and up sides of 8 or 9-inch pie pan or in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Refrigerate 10 to 15 minutes or bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool; fill as desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, then cover with Cheddar cheese.
(You can add chicken, ham or turkey for a meat casserole.)
Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs and pour over the broccoli and cheese.
Cover with foil.
Place in a 325° oven and bake about 1 hour.
The last 10 minutes, bake without the foil.

title: paint brush cookies
directions: Make sugar cookies, except cut rolled dough into 1 1/2-inch circles.
Paint design on half the cookies with egg yolk paint. Bake 6 to 8 minutes.

title: butter pecan sauce
directions: In small saucepan over medium heat, melt butter. Add brown sugar, whipping cream and corn syrup. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils. Remove from heat; stir in pecans and vanilla. Serve warm over refrigerated cheesecake.

title: seafood gumbo soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in hot oil in soup kettle.
Add seafood; saute for 5 minutes.
Stir in broth and tomatoes. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in rice and seasonings.
Serve.

title: peach soup
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in medium pan and boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 30 minutes. Strain and return to pan.
Add cornstarch and wine mixture, blending thoroughly.
Bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Allow to cool and add pureed peaches.
Chill well.
Ladle into bowls and serve as a first course.
To serve as a dessert, spoon over thick slices of pound cake and garnish with whipped cream and blueberries.

title: moist meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Add meat and all other ingredients, mix well.
Place in greased pan.
Cover with 1 can tomato soup or 1 (8-ounce) can tomato sauce.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Arrange asparagus in bottom of casserole dish.
Next the peas, mushroom soup and chestnuts.
Grate cheese over top also buttered bread crumbs.
Heat in 350° oven until cheese melts and crumbs are slightly brown.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Peel and cube potatoes; cook until tender.
Combine Cheez Whiz, cream cheese and soup in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until blended thoroughly.
Grease casserole dish.
Place potatoes in dish and cover with sauce.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Butter dish.
Mix everything together, except crackers.
Put in baking dish.
Top with crackers and sprinkle with margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lelia's rhubarb cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix together rhubarb, sugar and dry Jell-O.
Spread mixture in bottom of greased pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows over mixture.
Mix a cake mix according to directions on cake mix box and pour over mixture. Bake at 350°
for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: homemade tomato soup
directions: Drop your tomatoes into a pot of boiling water and cook for a few minutes.
Then drop them into very cold water.
This makes them easier to peel.
After peeling your tomatoes, squeeze out as many seeds as possible and discard the seeds.
Combine the tomatoes with a pinch of baking soda and mash.
(You can run it through a blender, food processor, use a beater or whatever you like to use.)
Heat with milk, butter, parsley, salt and pepper to taste.

title: grape leaf pickles
directions: In each jar, place 2 grape leaves and 4 to 6 green grapes. Boil salt, water and vinegar.
Pour over cucumbers and pack in jars. Sit jars in a water bath in kettle or in a shallow pan in oven until they change color.

title: drop cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients, beat well.
Add dry ingredients in order.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: bugles or chip dip
directions: Beat with mixer all ingredients.
Store in 20 ounce container. Serve with Bugles or chips.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in an electric blender; process until smooth.
Cover and chill thoroughly.

title: quick chicken or shrimp stir-fry
directions: Spray nonstick 12-ounce saut pan.
Heat to medium/hot.
Pour frozen vegetables in pan and stir-fry until almost done.
Push vegetables to side of pan and put in the chicken or shrimp.
Cook shrimp until they are pink, about 5 minutes.
Add marinade and pepper flakes to pan.
Heat thoroughly and serve over 1 cup of cooked rice.
Serves 2.

title: low cholesterol pancakes
directions: Sift flour, dry milk, sugar, baking powder and salt in bowl. Add egg whites, water and oil.
Blend together with whisk.
Heat 12-inch nonstick skillet until hot on medium heat.
Pour about 1/4 cup batter for each pancake.
Turn when lightly browned underneath.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pickled bean salad
directions: Heat sugar, oil and vinegar.
Pour over mixture.
Chill overnight.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Place roast in a slow cooker or crock-pot.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and dry soup mix until smooth.
Pour over roast. Cook on high for 3 hours.
Turn heat down to low and cook 5 to 8 hours longer.

title: irish cream
directions: Blend all ingredients at low speed until foamy. Serve immediately or cover and refrigerate up to 4 weeks.
Blend or shake well before using.

title: brownies for a crowd
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy, then beat in 2 eggs at a time, then vanilla.
Stir in chocolate syrup.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and stir into chocolate mixture.
Add nuts and pour into a well-greased (sprayed with Pam) 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 22 to 25 minutes at 350° or until touching leaves a slight imprint.
Cool and frost.

title: nachos dip
directions: Mix together and heat.
(I use crock-pot.)
Serve with nachos.

title: apricot chicken divine
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Spread olive oil in baking dish.
Mix flour and salt.
Dredge chicken pieces in flour mixture one at a time and place in baking dish.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Add water and bouillon cubes. Bring to a boil.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and vegetables. Bring to a boil.
Season to taste.
Continue to cook on low heat for 30 minutes.

title: london broil
directions: Cut a large "X" on both sides of roast.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Place in casserole and marinate beef overnight in refrigerator, covered.
Then grill or broil approximately 5 inches from heat for 4 to 5 minutes on each side or to desired doneness. Baste with remaining marinade.

title: quick n' easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into muffin pans and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: microwave streusel
directions: In bottom of round 9-inch pan, spread pie filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over filling.
Mix together brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Sprinkle over cake mix.
Melt butter and spread evenly over entire mixture.
Cook on High 7 minutes.
Turn 1/4 and cook another 7 to 8 minutes.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Cream Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese together. Stir in drained fruit and marshmallows. Top with pecans.

title: caramel dip
directions: Beat together softened cream cheese, brown sugar, vanilla and caramel topping until smooth.
Reserved 1 tablespoon chopped nuts. Add remainder to dip.
Sprinkle reserved nuts on top.
Slice unpeeled Granny Smith apples that have been dipped in pineapple juice to keep from turning brown.

title: easy fruit cake
directions: Mix cake with eggs and pineapple juice.
Flour fruits and nuts and add to cake batter.
Pour into two bread pans that have been buttered and dusted with flour.
Fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: orange marmalade bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar into a large bowl. Add walnuts and orange rind; stir to coat evenly.
In a separate bowl, beat orange juice, marmalade, eggs and melted butter until blended.
Add to dry ingredients; mix.
Bake in a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done. Cool on a rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool before cutting.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: bee sting cake
directions: In saucepan, mix brown sugar, milk, and batter. Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat; add nuts. Pour into 2 9-inch greased round cake pans.

title: shrimp creole
directions: The shrimp may be cooked separately and added to the Creole or the shrimp may be peeled and deveined and added for the last 5 or 6 minutes while cooking the Creole.
Another option is to saute the shrimp in butter and add just before serving.
Whatever you choose to do, do not overcook the shrimp.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Simmer together until tender.
This freezes well.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in casserole dish or pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pie crust. Refrigerate overnight.
Garnish each slice with extra whipped topping and 1/2 Reese's Peanut Butter Cup.

title: baked turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except eggs and cheese, and chips. Layer with the eggs. Mix chips and cheese and spread on top. Bake at 450° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pear gelatin
directions: Drain pears, reserving juice.
Chop pears and set aside.
Add water to the juice to measure 3 cups.
Place in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Whisk in cream cheese until smooth.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Whisk in whipped topping until smooth.
Add chopped pears.
Transfer to a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Cover and refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.
Garnish with mandarin oranges if desired.
Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: creamed peas and tuna fish on toast
directions: Add in frypan the butter; bring to boil, then add flour.
Salt and pepper to taste, then add evaporated milk and 1/2 can water; stir until thickened.
Add sweet peas (undrained); stir, then add tuna fish (drain if in oil or it has a lot of water in it).
Let simmer for 15 minutes.
Make toast.
Makes at least 12 servings.

title: buttermilk caramel candy
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a large saucepan; cook until it begins to boil, stirring constantly.
Cook until it makes a medium hard ball in a cup of cold water.
Take off range and add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until slightly cool.
Then drop into desired shapes and sizes on waxed paper.

title: strawberry bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add combined dry ingredients; mix well.
Press half of mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread with preserves.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients well and shape into 1 large or 2 small loaves.
Place in baking pan or dish and cover with sauce.

title: fudge oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring all but last 2 ingredients to a boil.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal and coconut.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper. Cool.

title: cheese and bacon stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Wash in salted water, then drain on paper towels.
While mushrooms are draining, cook bacon until crisp, then crumble.
Chop onion and grate cheese.
Mix mayonnaise, seasoned salt, onion, cheese and crumbled bacon. Place mushrooms, cut side up, in a 9 x 13-inch buttered Pyrex dish.
Fill each mushroom with cheese and bacon mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot and cheese is melted.
Yield:
approximately 48 mushrooms.

title: mel's double fudge german chocolate cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
Add eggs, coffee, buttermilk, oil and vanilla.
Beat at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Slice potatoes crosswise into 1/8-inch slices to within 1/2-inch from bottom of potatoes.
Drizzle part of butter into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place spuds cut side up; drizzle some butter on top of potatoes.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and remaining butter.
Bake 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes.

title: powdered sugar fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients in double boiler, except nuts.
Place over simmering water and stir until smooth.
Add nuts and mix.
Spread quickly in buttered 8-inch square pan.

title: cajun potato boats
directions: Cut tops off of baked potatoes.
Scoop out each potato leaving 1/4-inch thickness with skin.
Mash potato in large mixing bowl. Beat in butter, then sour cream, then seasoning.
Fold in remaining ingredients; reserving 1 cup shredded cheddar.
Stuff each potato shell full!
Place potatoes on buttered casserole dish and top each with reserved shredded cheddar.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Serve hot!

title: vienna nut torte
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Beat egg yolks and 1 egg until colored and light.
Beat in 1/2 cup sugar.
Add 1 cup nuts, bread crumbs and tea powder.

title: applesauce spice cake
directions: Sift flour; measure and resift with soda, spices and salt. Cream shortening well and gradually blend in sugar.
Beat in eggs, then applesauce.
Add flour mixture gradually, beating after each addition.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: bar room slaw
directions: Boil vinegar, salt, sugar, black pepper and peppers.
Mix cabbage, peppers, onions and mustard.
Pack in pint jars.
Pour equal parts of boiling mixture in each pint.
Seal.
Make sure lids are tight.

title: grilled sauteed onions
directions: Slice onions into rings, separating the rings in large bowl. Drizzle with margarine; sprinkle with salt.
Toss thoroughly. Cover grill top with aluminum foil, folding edges up.
Puncture numerous small holes in foil.
Place onions on foil in thin layer. Close grill.
Stir occasionally until light brown, 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in a large bowl. Stir in oats.
Set aside.
Beat egg, milk and oil in a separate bowl.
Add milk mixture to flour mixture.
Stir just until dry ingredients are wet.
Fill greased muffin pans half full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: cherry goop
directions: Spread pie filling into a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Drizzle melted butter over cake mix.
Top with chopped nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut stems from peppers.
Take out seeds and wash peppers. Drain.
Brown ground beef and onion together.
Drain.
Mix all other ingredients, except cheese.
Stuff peppers and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: taco pizza
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Add taco seasoning and prepare according to directions.
Lay 1st taco shell in middle of pizza pan. and lay remains shells overlapping center shell and edges to form a pizza crust.
Sprinkle half of the cheese on the shells to bond the shells together when the cheese melts.
Spread ground meat and remaining cheese.
Bake in oven preheated to 300 for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with taco sauce then add remaining toppings.
Cut with a sharp knife and serve.

title: peanut butter-dipped bonbons
directions: Beat the cream cheese and milk until fluffy.
Blend in sugar, cocoa, vanilla and nuts. Chill until firm.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Place on waxed paper. Chill for 3 to 4 hours.
Melt peanut butter chips and shortening. Dip balls and chill. Store in a cool place.

title: steak and potato casserole
directions: In electric skillet at 350°, add oil and
brown meat on both sides.
You can use another skillet on top	of
the stove using medium-high heat.
Remove
meat from skillet after brown and drain off grease.
Mix soup and water until dissolved in a bowl.	Put potatoes, onion
and
pepper
in skillet or a large baking	dish. Place
meat
on
top
of
potatoes.
Pour
soup mixture over this and cook covered at 275° in electric skillet about 1 hour or bake in 300° oven until meat is tender, about 1 hour.
Stir occasionally to keep potatoes from sticking.

title: indian corn bread
directions: Combine ingredients in mixing bowl in order given.
Pour into greased baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: In bowl, combine lime juice, garlic, chili powder and cumin. Add chicken; stir.
Marinate 15 minutes.
Cook onion and peppers; set aside.
Stir-fry chicken for 3 to 5 minutes, until no longer pink.
Mix chicken and veggies together.
Stir in salsa.
Place approximately 1/2 cup mixture on tortilla.
Sprinkle with cheese and roll up.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, sour milk with soda dissolved in it.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls on well floured pan and bake at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: deep fried cheese wonton
directions: Cut cheese to 1/4.
Place cheese on the wonton skin, then fold it.
Heat oil.
Deep fry the wonton.

title: hamburger cookies
directions: Put the coconut in a small bowl with a lid.
Add a few drops of the food coloring.
Put on the lid and shake until the coconut turns green.
Put 12 wafers flat side up on a baking sheet.
Place a mint on top of each wafer.
Bake the wafers at 350° for 1 minute.
Immediately sprinkle each wafer with coconut (lettuce). Top with remaining wafers flat side down and you will have hamburger cookies.

title: myra's congealed salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Pour into a dish. Chill.

title: chili-cheese dip
directions: Place in the order listed in a glass dish (9 or 10-inch). Cook in microwave for 2 1/2 minutes on High or bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: hawaiian pork chops
directions: Place all ingredients except pork chops in frying pan.
Mix well and add pork chops.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: summer rice dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Stir, and put under the broiler to brown.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts (add last).
Pour into lined muffin pans and bake at 425° for 15 to 17 minutes.

title: taco bean soup
directions: Brown meat with chopped onions.
Add beans, tomatoes and corn. Add dry taco seasoning and Ranch dressing.

title: rye bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together to make a stiff dough.
Knead on floured board.
Let rise until doubled.
Put into 3 greased loaf pans.
Let rise until about doubled.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar and well beaten egg.
Add salt and vanilla.
Sift flour and add to mixture, a little at a time alternating with milk until all are in.
Roll 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into cakes and bake in moderate oven at 350° until light brown.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Put gelatine in cold water for 10 minutes.
Heat over boiling water until melted. Add to tomato mixture. Turn into a greased mold. Add olives.

title: brisket in beer
directions: Place layer of onions and half of the garlic in a shallow roasting pan.
Add brisket.
Top with remaining onions and garlic. Pour beer over all and seal pan.
Place in preheated oven at 350° and roast for 3 to 4 hours.
Remove meat from pan; keep warm.
If desired, thicken drippings or serve as is.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: low calorie frozen lemon custard
directions: Mix egg yolk, sugar, lemon rind and 2 tablespoons lemon juice. In electric mixer, beat remaining lemon juice, water, egg white and milk at high speed until stiff.
Gradually beat egg yolk mixture into egg white mixture.
Spoon into refrigerator tray and freeze without stirring.
Approximately 508 calories in entire recipe.

title: rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients for 2 to 3 minutes and pour into pan.
Grease and flour a Bundt or tube pan.
Line bottom with pecan bits.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately pour on hot rum glaze.
This will settle the cake.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in pan. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently until mixture begins to bubble.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour mixture over cereal and stir until blended.
Press into 9x13 in. pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips and spread over cereal mixture.

title: mary's pineapple walnut salad
directions: Mix the pudding and whipped topping until the pudding is totally dissolved; adding as much of the pineapple juice as needed to make it smooth and creamy.
Add pineapple and walnuts and mix. Cover and refrigerate.
This can be made a day ahead of time and it keeps well.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, water and brown sugar.
Simmer mixture over low heat until thickened.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter a shallow baking dish (9 x 12 inch).
Spread apple slices and raisins evenly in pan.
Combine sugar and flour, cinnamon and nutmeg in a bowl.
Blend in remaining butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle evenly over fruit.
Press lightly.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until crisp.
Serve warm.

title: see's fudge
directions: Combine in large saucepan the sugar and condensed milk.
Boil 6 minutes.
Place in large bowl all other ingredients.
Pour boiled mixture over top and stir until all ingredients are melted. Pour into buttered pan.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: frontier jerky(david's favorite recipe for deer jerky.)
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients except meat.
Stir to mix well.
Place meat 3 to 4 layers deep in a glass, stoneware, plastic or stainless steel container, spooning liquid smoke mixture over each layer.
Cover tightly.
Marinate 6 to 12 hours in the refrigerator, stirring occasionally and keeping the mixture tightly covered.
Dehydrate meat as directed by your dehydrator.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and cocoa. Bring water, salad oil and margarine to a boil. Pour this mixture over the dry ingredients. Beat well until creamy. Add buttermilk, baking soda, eggs and salt and beat well. Bake on a cookie sheet at 400° for 18 minutes.

title: macadamia nut salad
directions: Boil first 6 ingredients in top of double boiler until thickened.
Put in refrigerator to cool.
Whip up whipping cream and put in refrigerator to cool.
Mix cooled sauce, 1 cup whipped cream and remaining ingredients.
Serve cold.

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Pour the juice from the can of fruit cocktail and mix with the other ingredients, then add the fruit from the can of cocktail. Put into pan and sprinkle on top 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup pecans.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: sugar-free peanut butterruth candy bar
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Divide in two.
Place on waxed paper in shape of candy bar.
Wrap and freeze.

title: apple chow-chow
directions: Chop and cube peppers, onions and apples.
Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until it starts to boil, not until it is mushy.
Pour into pint jars and seal.
Great with everything, but best with beans.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat eggs and add 1/2 cup milk.
Sift dry ingredients and add to batter.
Stir in oil and corn.
If too thick, add a little more milk.
Drop from teaspoon into deep grease and fry at 350°.
The fritters will turn themselves and are done when golden brown. Drain on paper towels.

title: crispy caramel corn
directions: Spread freshly popped corn in large shallow sheet pan.

title: potato and canadian bacon chowder
directions: In slow cooker, combine potatoes, carrots, leek, garlic, chicken broth, barley, bay leaf, thyme, pepper and Canadian bacon.

title: quick chicken rice bake
directions: Pour rice evenly over bottom of well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix soups, water and salt; pour over rice.
Coat chicken pieces with melted margarine; arrange in dish.
Bake covered at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: key lime cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; beat 2 to 3 minutes at medium speed. Pour into 3 round, greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° approximately 25 minutes.

title: meat and potato casserole
directions: Brown
ground
beef
with
onions
and	peppers; drain. Layer sliced
potatoes in ungreased casserole dish.
Top with ground beef mixture.
Mash Ro-Tel tomatoes with juice and pour over casserole.	Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Top
with	cheese;
place	in
oven until cheese melts.

title: chicken in wine
directions: Salt, pepper and flour chicken.
Fry until golden brown in oil.
Lift out and put in casserole.
Melt butter in pan, add soup, mushrooms, sour cream and wine.
Cook slowly until smooth, stir constantly.
Pour over chicken, cover and cook 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: mark's marinade
directions: Mix equal parts of each.
Place meat in marinade; refrigerate at least one hour, turning meat occasionally.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Sprinkle biscuits and rolling pin with flour.
Roll out flat and place on cookie sheet.
Top with pizza sauce, parsley flakes and cheese.
Bake 5 minutes at 425° or until biscuits are brown and cheese is melted.
Makes 8.

title: crunchy lemon chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix crushed bran flakes, lemon peel and salt.
Dip chicken in egg white.
Coat with bran flake mixture. Arrange in 13 x 9-inch pan which has been sprayed with a nonstick cooking spray.
Bake 20 minutes or until cooked through.

title: glorified cabbage
directions: Chop cabbage.
Boil until wilted.
Saute onion in butter.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Blend soup into mixture well.
Add cabbage and mix in bread crumbs until proper consistency.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown on top.

title: lemon poppy seed pound cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all cake ingredients.
Beat at low speed until all ingredients are moistened.
Beat at high speed until smooth (2 minutes).
Pour into greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 65 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Drizzle glaze over cake.

title: chicken jubilee
directions: Pour margarine over chicken and broil until brown.
Combine other ingredients; pour over chicken and bake, covered with foil, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot spicy tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and let steep 5 minutes.
Strain before serving.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground meat; add salt, pour off fat.
Add celery and onions; let simmer 1/2 hour.
Add soup, then simmer 1/2 hour. Serve on toasted buns.

title: licorice caramels
directions: Blend all ingredients, except anise and food coloring.
Bring to 238°, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in anise and food coloring.
Pour into plastic wrap lined 8-inch square pan.
Let cool overnight at room temperature.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Cream eggs, oil, Jell-O and strawberries.
Mix in cake mix. Add all other ingredients.
A small amount of sweet milk may be needed for cake batter consistency.
Makes 3 large layers.
Bake at 375°.
(Can be made in sheet form.)

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in a casserole dish.
Spread about 1 1/2 cups of Miracle Whip/mayonnaise over green peas.
Sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Top with shredded cheese before serving.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix with fork; press into large, deep pie dish.

title: easy pork chops or chicken
directions: Brush meat with salad dressing.
Coat with crumbs, salt and pepper to taste.
Bake chops for 60 minutes and the chicken 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: baked parmesan cottage fries
directions: In greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking sheet, arrange potato slices in thin layer.
Melt butter.
Drizzle over potatoes. Evenly arrange onions over top.
Combine garlic, Parmesan
and pepper.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 450° about 25 minutes or until browned.

title: spiced apples
directions: Peel and core apples; cut each into 12 wedges.
In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, heat butter or margarine; add apples.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon; cook about 6 minutes, stirring occasionally until apples are lightly browned and just tender.

title: indian corn
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add sliced onion.
Cook until meat is done.
Add corn and picante sauce.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with corn chips.

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, place cauliflower in water and salt. Microwave at High 8 to 9 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes. Drain off liquid from dishes.
Sprinkle stuffing mix, then cheese over cauliflower.
Microwave at High 1 to 2 minutes, uncovered until cheese melts.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: chicken loaf and sauce
directions: Mix milk and chicken broth.
Blend in eggs and bread crumbs. Allow to cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and spread in a greased pan and allow to stand overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Top with Mushroom Sauce.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Boil chicken breasts in 2 cups water until tender; remove from bone.
Retain broth.
Add the chicken meat, vegetables and pineapple.
Simmer on reduced heat for about 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill. Makes a large bowl of salad.

title: toffee squares
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients
together.
Pat down in cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Take out of oven and put chocolate chips on top.
When melted, spread and cover with chopped nuts.
Cut while warm.

title: pizza(makes two pizzas)
directions: In large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
When dissolved, add sugar, salt, oil and 2 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in about 1 1/2 cups flour.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl.
Let rise in warm place until double in bulk (about 45 minutes).

title: 20 minute beef chili
directions: Place beef pieces and cooking liquid, salsa and chili powder in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover tightly and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add beans; heat through.
Serve with cheese and onion.
Makes 4 servings.

title: popovers(6)
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Beat eggs slightly and add the milk and melted butter.
Pour liquid into dry ingredients, beating until batter is smooth.
Fill greased, large custard cups 1/2 full.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes, then decrease oven to 350° and bake 20 minutes more.
Fill hollow center with jam or scrambled eggs.

title: buttered pecan patties
directions: Cook
to
firm	stage.	Remove and add 2/3 stick margarine; let cool.
Add 1
1/2 cups chopped pecans and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Beat until it can
be
put	out
on
waxed	paper by teaspoons. I beat a while before adding nuts.

title: fruit salad
directions: In medium bowl, mix all ingredients together except the Cool Whip. Put in loaf dish, cover and refrigerate. Top with Cool Whip when serving, if desired.

title: pineapple-coconut pudding
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Combine pineapple juice and enough orange juice to make 1 1/3 cups.
Combine juice mixture, pudding mix and sour cream.
Beat with rotary beater or mixer for 2 minutes or until mixture is smooth.
Chill 5 minutes.
Stir whipped cream, pineapple and 3/4 cup coconut into pudding.
Spoon 1/3 of mixture into a 1 1/2 or 2-quart dish.
Top with 1/2 of wafers.
Repeat, ending with pudding.
Garnish with remaining whipping cream and coconut.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: roll-ups
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften; mix ingredients together. Smooth mixture over flour tortillas and roll.
Place in refrigerator to chill, then slice.
Serve with picante sauce. Great for parties!

title: southpaw apple cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flours and spices in small mixing bowl; set aside.
Cream together the margarine and sugar. Blend in egg and molasses.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring well to blend.
Stir in grated apple and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until light golden brown.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt oleo in frying pan.
Add onion and celery and brown lightly.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together and set aside.
In a large bowl, mix butter, sugars and vanilla.
Stir until creamy.
Add eggs and gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and raisins.
Drop about a tablespoonful of cookie batter on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: salsa dip
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Add oregano to taste.
Use on tacos or as a dip for tortilla chips.

title: seafood nicole
directions: Wash and dry fish.
Cut fillets into thirds or quarters. Scrub clam shells thoroughly.
In a 6 quart pot over medium heat, warm oil until hot.
Add garlic, onion, oregano, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cook onions until brown and add wine and tomatoes.
Cook for 45 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add clams and fish and simmer for about 45 minutes.
Serve in large bowls.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Prepare lime jello and
let
jell in a 9 x 13-inch pan. In a double
boiler,
combine
the lemon jello, boiling water, cream cheese and marshmallows.
Cook until all is melted.
Add the pineapple, nuts
and mayonnaise.
After this cools, spread on lime jello that
has
set.
Pour
cherry jello on top.
You may want to pour this on while it is in the refrigerator.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add pecans and salt.
Set aside for topping.
Mix all other ingredients and top with pecans.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: yellow or zucchini squash casserole
directions: Prepare Stove Top according to box directions.
Mix all together plus eggs.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with cheese.

title: esther's version seven layer salad
directions: Lay in lettuce in rectangular dish or pan.
One at a time, sprinkle on carrots, onion, pepper and peas.
Cover, as if spreading butter, the whole top of lettuce mixture with mayonnaise.
Should cover completely.
Sprinkle sugar and then bacon.
Finish with a covering of cheese.
Cover with wrap and refrigerate all day or overnight.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: For when it's half past three

title: bacardi rum cake
directions: Sprinkle nuts over greased 10 or 12-cup Bundt pan.
Mix all cake ingredients together.
Pour batter over nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Cool and put cake on a serving dish.
Prick top and spoon glaze over top and sides evenly.
Repeat until all the glaze has been absorbed.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Saute ground beef and drain off excess fat.
Saute onion, celery and pepper in olive oil until pastel colored.
Add to meat.
Add oregano, marjoram, garlic and water.
Simmer one hour. Add a little more water if needed.
Add mushrooms, tomato paste and sauce. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to simmer for 4 hours. Stir often.
Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Add to sauce or serve separately.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Remove casings from sausages and crumble or chop meat.
Finely chop Prosciutto.
In a frying pan over medium heat, melt 2 tablespoons of the butter.
Add sausages and half the Prosciutto to the pan and cook, stirring, for about 10 minutes.
Sausages will be browned and Prosciutto will be curled.
Stir in the rest of the Prosciutto.
Cook spaghetti according to directions and drain.
Add spaghetti to the hot meat mixture; add butter and parsley.
Mix quickly to blend.
At once, pour in eggs and quickly lift and mix the spaghetti to coat well with egg.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Mix again and serve immediately with extra Parmesan cheese on the side.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: rice salad
directions: While rice is hot, add mayonnaise and onion.
Mix well and chill, then you can add any of the following (whatever you like!): ham, peas, lima beans, carrots, pickle relish, pimentos, mustard and curry powder.
The amount of vegetables you add can be adjusted to your taste.
I also seasoned with black pepper.
Celery can also be added.

title: hot cheese squares
directions: Mix and bake in a lightly buttered 9-inch pie pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: In bowl, sift salt, baking soda and flour.
Into this, cream the shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir into mixture 1/2 package of chocolate chips.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: new york cheesecake
directions: Blend the cottage cheese and cream cheese.
Add the sugar to cheese mixture.
Blend the eggs, lemon juice, vanilla, cornstarch, flour and butter to the cheese mixture.
Blend in sour cream. Pour into greased spring-form pan.
Place in a cold oven.
Set at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn off heat.
Let stay for 2 hours. Refrigerate for 6 hours.
Serve with fruit or plain.

title: smoked salmon pizza
directions: Bake bread shell as package directs.
Spread with cream cheese.
Top with onions, cucumbers, smoked salmon, dill and capers.
Slice or cut into small squares and serve.

title: sewer punch
directions: In punch bowl, dump semi soft sherbet and pour in 1/2 juice and 1/2 7-Up.
Refill as needed.
Great for kids' parties!

title: hot cranberry-mandarin sauce
directions: Put drained mandarins in blender, chop coarsely.
Add the remaining ingredients, process for 20 seconds.
Pour into a saucepan, heat, stirring occasionally, simmer about 1 minute. Serve hot or cold.
This is a great sauce for canned or fresh peaches, apricots or pears, or as a sauce for chicken, turkey, ham or pork.

title: red raspberry dessert
directions: Mix
berries,
water, sugar and lemon juice in a saucepan. Dissolve cornstarch in the 1/4 cup water, then stir into berries. Cook
until clear, then cool.
Dissolve marshmallows in the
milk and
cool.	Then
fold
in	the
Cool Whip.
Mix crumbs, butter and
nuts
and pat into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour marshmallow
mixture
over crust.
Top with cooled raspberry mixture
and
refrigerate.	Make
sure
marshmallow mixture is
in refrigerator
hour
before adding raspberry topping.

title: kimberly's butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar thoroughly with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Add the eggs and beat again.
Sift the flour with the dry ingredients and add it to the creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Form the dough into a ball, wrap in foil and refrigerate 1 hour.
Preheat the oven to 350°.
When the dough is firm, pinch off a small piece at a time, leaving the rest in the refrigerator. Roll each batch out quite thin on a floured pastry cloth and cut into desired shapes.
Sprinkle the cookies with sugar and bake on a lightly greased or nonstick baking sheet until pale gold, 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool them on a rack.

title: cheese peas
directions: Partially drain peas.
Add salt, pimentos and Cheez Whiz. Heat and serve.
You can use amounts of pimentos and cheese to taste.
Also, Ro-Tel cheese dip works good with green peas.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Mix oil, dressing, dill and garlic.
Pour over crackers.
Stir several times.
Make one day before serving.
Store in airtight container.

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut biscuits into halves; makes 20 (1/2-inch circles).
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in everything but biscuits and cheese.
Heat in pan until bubbly.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Place biscuits, cut side down, around edge.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: herbed baked fish fillets
directions: Combine flour and herbs. Dip fish in egg white, then in flour mixture. Place fish in single layer in baking pan. Spoon yogurt over fish. Bake in preheated 400° oven about 15 minutes.

title: squash marmalade
directions: Bring squash and water to a boil; add sugar.
Cook 6 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add jello and flavoring.
Put in jars.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins.
Peel and cool while hot.
Cover with mixture of first four ingredients.
(Make additional mixture to cover potatoes, if necessary.)
Let stand several hours or overnight.
Drain thoroughly.
Add mayo or sour cream.
Onions may be added.

title: hamburger chow mein casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Mix hamburger with soup and milk.
Stir in chow mein noodles.
Bake in greased pan for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350° covered.
Makes 48 servings per 12 x 20 x 4-inch pan.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Blend in blender the cream cheese, vanilla, sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice.
Pour into prepared crust. Refrigerate overnight.
Spoon your favorite pie filling over individual servings, or entire pie.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with taco chips.
Yield: 3 cups.

title: barbecue sauce for ribs
directions: Brown meat in shortening.
Put into baking dish or oven pan. Pour sauce over meat and bake about 1 hour at 375°.

title: choconut ice cream pie
directions: Crust:
Melt chocolate and butter over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in 2 cups coconut; mix well.
Press on bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan.
Freeze.

title: almost stuffed cabbage
directions: Cook sausage and ground meat in skillet and drain.
Put bell pepper and onion with meat mixture; cook a few seconds and drain. Add tomatoes; cook with water and cabbage.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 15 minutes; lid on.
Cook rice in separate pot, then add to mixture.
Cook 5 more minutes.
Slice in 1-inch slices. Wedge a slice of cheese in each slice and pour cream of mushroom soup in and bake until hot and melted.

title: chili verde
directions: Brown pork.
Add onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Pour in Ortega chili and 1/2 can tomato sauce and 1/2 cup water.
Simmer for ?? hours.

title: green chili chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil
chicken
breasts	until done.
Cool; remove bones and skin.
Chop
or shred meat. Fry corn tortillas in hot oil just until
soft. Dilute chicken soup with milk or water to a pouring consistency. Grate cheese; chop onion and green chili; add garlic powder and salt to chili.
In casserole dish, start 1st
layer with tortillas, chicken, onion, chili, soup and end with cheese. Make as many layers as tortillas and ingredients permit.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: "people" puppy chow
directions: Melt together chocolate bits, peanut butter and margarine. Add M&M's and cereal (stir in a large paper bag).
Add confectioners sugar and shake well.
Serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges and put in pudding until smooth.
Add sour cream to Cool Whip.
Add fruit.
Mix all fruit with pudding mixture.

title: rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until transparent.
Add frozen broccoli. Cook over low heat covered until broccoli thaws.
Add soup, Cheez Whiz and cooked rice.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Garnish with toasted bread crumbs and cook in a preheated 350° oven for about 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: candied pecans
directions: Put all except nuts in a 1-quart microwave dish; cook 1 to 2 minutes on High until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in nuts until well coated.
Microwave 4 to 5 minutes on High.
Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Cool.
Break apart.

title: nanny's pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: spanish hamburger
directions: Slice onion and saute until tender.
Cook and drain ground beef.
Mix with onion.
Drain can of corn and mix with meat and onion.
Add tomato sauce.
Add water, salt and pepper to taste. Serve over rice.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place pieces of bread in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook and drain sausage and spoon over bread.
Sprinkle 1 cup of Cheddar cheese over all.
Beat eggs; add milk, mustard, salt and pepper and pour over ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40
minutes.
Can be prepared night before and refrigerated.

title: blond brownies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together, adding brown sugar.
Add butter, Wesson oil and eggs.
Add vanilla and nuts last.
Bake for about 30 or 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Falls when done.
Cut into squares before serving.

title: party bunch bites
directions: To Microwave:
Place butter in 2-cup glass container.
Cover with waxed paper; microwave on High 45 seconds or until melted. Stir in soup mix.
In a 4-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour butter mixture over cracker mixture; toss to coat well.
Microwave, uncovered, on High 5 minutes or until hot, stirring twice during heating.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage, biscuit mix and cheese.
Shape into bite size balls.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: sticky oven-fried chicken
directions: Arrange frozen chicken pieces in a single layer in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
In small bowl, combine the remaining ingredients.
Spoon over chicken.
Continue baking 20 minutes or more until chicken is heated through.

title: curried chicken tea sandwiches
directions: In a bowl, combine the first six ingredients.
Combine mayonnaise, lime juice and curry powder; add to chicken mixture and stir to coat.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve. Cut each slice of bread with 3 inch cookie cutter, whatever shape you desire.
Top each slice of bread with lettuce and chicken salad.

title: cake delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together for 4 minutes.
Pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cindy's chicken stew
directions: Cook chicken (save broth) and remove from bone. Tear up into small pieces, set aside. Cook potatoes, onion, corn, tomatoes sauce, salt and peppers in chicken broth. Cook for about 10 to 15 minutes. Add chicken, reduce to a simmer and cook about 15 to 20 minutes longer. Your stew is ready to eat.

title: marinated mushroom salad
directions: Place mushrooms in a glass bowl.
Combine vinegar, tarragon, lemon juice, salt, pepper and sugar in a blender container.
Blend to mix.
Pour oil in a steady stream while blender is on.
Add cheese and blend again.
Pour dressing over mushrooms and let stand a few hours at room temperature.
To serve, spoon mushrooms onto lettuce leaves; top with egg and garnish with parsley sprigs. Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar and peanut butter until crumbly.
Layer in bottom of pie.
Mix the pudding up and pour over peanut butter and sugar mixture in bottom of pie shell.
Cool.
Then top with Cool Whip and serve chilled.
May sprinkle with nuts or save some of the peanut butter and 10x sugar mixture to sprinkle on top.
Makes 2 pies.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate an hour until chilled. Use as a dip for shrimp or crab claws.

title: brazilian coffee
directions: Empty cocoa mix into cup.
Add coffee, stirring, until mixture is dissolved.
Top with whipped topping and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Serves 1 with 74 calories.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Blend in blender until well mixed.
Store in refrigerator.

title: 7 layer plus salad
directions: Layer in a salad bowl each of the ingredients with the bacon on top.

title: overnight fruit salad
directions: To Make Dressing: Mix eggs, sugar, flour, lemon juice and juice reserved from drained pineapple in a saucepan. Cook over medium-low, stirring constantly, until thickened. Cool and add mustard to dressing mixture.

title: barbecued burgers
directions: Saute onion and meat.
Combine other ingredients and heat. Serve on hot buns.

title: mom's jam cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add sifted ingredients alternately with buttermilk and vanilla.
Add jam and beat well.
Bake in lightly greased and floured pan in 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, and baking powder.
Work in the butter or shortening quickly with the fingertips or a table fork. Stir in the milk to make a soft dough.
Turn out on a lightly floured board and knead until smooth, about a minute.
Roll the dough until it is 1/4-inch thick and cut out 2-inch rounds. Spread the top of each round liberally with mustard.
Sprinkle grated Parmesan cheese on half of the rounds.

Place the remaining rounds, mustard side down, on top of the cheese-sprinkled rounds. Grease a baking sheet and bake in a preheated 425° F. oven for 12 to 15 minutes, or until the sandwiches are golden brown.
Serve hot.
Makes 12 sandwiches.

title: old fashion oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: verba's gooseberry pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar; stir into gooseberries.
Put on stove and begin to warm.
Beat 2 eggs.
Add to mixture before it gets too hot.
Cook until thickens.
Add butter.
When cool, cover with whipped cream.
I mash berries to prevent sour bites.
Will make 2 small 8-inch pieces or large 9-inch pie.

title: apple tempters
directions: Combine lemon, sugar and water.
Cut unpeeled apples into half-inch squares into lemon juice mixture.
Marinate in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Apples won't discolor in this mixture. When ready to serve, alternate apples, cheese and celery on a toothpick.
Stick into appropriate holder on a tray.
May also use grapefruit, apple or orange.

title: oatmeal caramelitas
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, oats, brown sugar, soda, salt and butter. Press 1/2 mixture into the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch glass pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with chocolate pieces and pecans.

title: corn souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.
You may want to sprinkle buttered cracker crumbs on top before baking.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Brown hamburg and onion; put in greased baking dish.
Add corn and cooked noodles.
Mix soups and pour over corn and noodles. Put browned buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Rinse all beans.
Place beans, pepper and onions in nonmetal bowl.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour over beans, etc.
Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours, overnight if possible.

title: garlic-onion dip
directions: In skillet over medium heat, saut garlic in oil 10 minutes or until golden brown.
In bowl, whisk together garlic and remaining ingredients.
Chill for a half hour or overnight.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and blend in brown sugar.
Add molasses and sour milk.
Sift together 3 cups flour with soda, salt and spices. Add to the first mixture together with the vinegar.
Add the rest of the flour, taking care to keep the dough soft.
Chill and roll out, not too thin.
Cut in desired shapes and bake on greased baking sheets about 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix flour with sugar.
Add milk.
Separate eggs and slightly beat yolks and add them to mixture.
Put in double boiler or saucepan and cook slowly, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add coconut and pour in baked pie shell.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken and chop or tear into pieces.
Mix chicken, vegetables and soup together.
Add pepper to taste. Spoon mixture into one thawed pie crust.
Place remaining crust on top.
Press edges together. Cut slits in top crust.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: banana spice cake
directions: Mix melted butter with graham cracker crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar, butter and eggs.
Beat 15 minutes and spread on crust.
Layer bananas.
Next, spread pineapple, then Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with crushed nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: butterscotch torte
directions: Mix together the flour, pecans and margarine (melted).
Press into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: honey bran muffins(low calorie)
directions: Beat honey and eggs together until blended.
Beat in bran and let stand to allow bran to soften.
Beat in yogurt.
Stir in remaining ingredients until just moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 large muffins.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cut top off bread and pick open the top of the bread.
Put pieces of bread aside.
Do not puncture any holes in exterior of bread.
Defrost spinach and drain excess water.
Mix all ingredients together by hand and pour into container to refrigerate for at least an hour, then pour into sweet bread and serve with bread pieces and veggies.

title: holiday ambrosia
directions: Combine pineapple, tangerine, grapes, walnuts, coconut and marshmallows in bowl.
Mix sour cream and sugar in small bowl. Stir into fruit mixture.
Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mama's frozen lemon pie
directions: Butter freezing tray and sprinkle bottom and sides with vanilla wafer crumbs. Beat egg whites until stiff. Beat in sugar and add egg yolks, 1 at a time, and beat well. Stir in lemon juice. Fold in stiffly beaten whipped cream. Pour into tray and sprinkle top with more vanilla wafer crumbs. Freeze.

title: homemade salisbury steak
directions: Combine hamburger and envelope together.
Place in a pan like meat loaf.
Pour gravy over top.
Cover with aluminum foil for 45 minutes; then uncover for the last 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chunky vegetable soup
directions: Heat to boiling, then add vegetables which have been cooked and salted separately.
Take 2 quarts flour and add water to make a smooth paste to thicken soup.
Brown hamburger in butter.
Cold pack 2 hours.
Makes 27 to 30 quarts.

title: leb cookies(a german cookie)
directions: Mix butter and sugar real good.
Add water and pecans.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add slowly while stirring. Sometimes I add a little more water or flour to make a real firm roll.
Wrap in waxed paper and place in refrigerator.
When dough is hard, slice thin cookies and bake as desired at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican salad
directions: Toss
first six ingredients together.
Top with crushed corn chips just before serving.

title: vegetarischer eintopf(vegetarian casserole)
directions: Wipe, peel and wash the carrots.
Wash, peel and rinse the potatoes.
Dice both ingredients.
Top and tail the beans and remove the strings if necessary.
Wash the beans and cut or break them into pieces.
Place the tomatoes in boiling water briefly (do not boil them), rinse with cold water and remove the skins. Remove the cores and cut the tomatoes into quarters.
Wash the cauliflower and divide into florets, peel and chop the onions.

title: grandma's nut pie
directions: In medium bowl, mix flour, sugar and salt with pastry blender. Cut in Crisco until it resembles coarse crumbs.
In a small bowl, beat egg, cold water and cider vinegar, then add to flour mixture. Stir until dough forms a ball.
Divide in half.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Use only 1 ball in this pie.

title: sausage and herb stuffing
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 400°.
Arrange bread onto baking sheet. Bake until light golden brown.
Cool. 2. Cook sausage in heavy large skillet over medium heat until cooked through, crumbling with fork after about 8 minutes.
Using slotted spoon transfer sausage to large bowl.
Add butter to any drippings in same skillet.
Melt over medium heat. 3. Add celery, onion, bell pepper, poultry seasoning, thyme, and sage to skillet.
Saute for 10 minutes.
Add mixture to sausage, then mix in bread.
Add stock to same skillet, bring to a boil scrapping up any browned bits. 4. Pour over stuffing.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add eggs and parsley; toss well.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: creamy orange cake
directions: Pour concentrate into 2-cup measuring cup, reserving 2 tablespoons for cake filling. Add enough water to remaining concentrate to make the amount of liquid needed for cake mix. Prepare cake mix as directed on package, using measured liquid. Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans. Bake and cool as directed on package.

title: apple berry chiller
directions: Combine all ingredients just before serving.
Serve with ice cubes, if desired.
Makes about 2 quarts.
Enjoy!!!

title: toasted party rye
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Add enough Worcestershire sauce to turn mixture a light brown color.
Spread mixture on slices of party rye; broil until spread browns.

title: easy cheesy lemon bars
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and egg.
Mix with fork until moist. Pat into 13 x 9-inch pan greased on the bottom.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Pour layer of spareribs in pan.
Cover with layer of onions. Pour barbecue sauce over.
Cover; bake at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Uncover last 1/2 hour.

title: cucumber relish (angie gillispie)
directions: Boil 15 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.
Boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter, mix in flour and slowly blend in the broth, cream and wine.
Cook, stirring, for about 5 minutes after mixture starts to simmer.
Stir in 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese. Measure out 1 cup of this sauce and save.
Add rest of Parmesan cheese and mix.
Melt remaining butter, add mushrooms and brown.

title: instant cheese pie
directions: Place cream cheese in bowl and stir until well softened.
Add about 1/2 cup milk a little at a time, blending mixture until very smooth.
Add remaining 1 1/2 cups milk and pudding mix.
Beat slowly until well mixed, about 1 minute.
Pour into crust. Chill.
Add cherry pie filling before serving.

title: hawaiian coconut spread
directions: Combine cheese and preserves, mixing until well blended.
Add coconut; mix well.
Chill.
Serve with nut bread slices, bread sticks, crackers or vegetable sticks.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: roy lee's slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, cucumbers and tomato with mayonnaise, salt, pepper and vinegar to taste. Let set to season before serving.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Pour boiling water into
mixture
of
Crisco, sugar and salt. Stir,
then
set aside and let cool.
When cooled, beat eggs and add.
Mix
lukewarm
water	with
yeast, then add to mixture. Then
blend
in
plain
flour.
Refrigerate 4 hours, then roll out
and
cut; let rise.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
May cook few rolls at a time.
Will keep in refrigerator for one week.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, margarine and cinnamon. Cover bottom of 9-inch baking dish or pan, that has been sprayed with Pam, with half of the mixture.
Arrange rhubarb on top evenly.
Cook water, cornstarch, sugar and vanilla until thick. Pour over rhubarb, then top with remaining crumbly mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: tinker's poultry dressing
directions: Put through meat grinder, a little at a time, of each.
Add poultry seasoning, 2 to 3 tablespoons or until it smells good. Add salt and pepper; stuff the bird or bake in a casserole dish.

title: praline frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix lightly.
Spread on 9-inch square gingerbread or cake.
Broil until bubbly and lightly browned.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except ground beef.
Mix well.
Add ground beef; mix thoroughly.
I like to mix before cooking all day or night.
Store in refrigerator.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Drain; let stand 5 minutes.

title: martha washington pudding
directions: Pour cherries into saucepan; crush.
Add 3/4 cup of sugar and tapioca.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes. Stir constantly.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: kid's favorite french toast
directions: Beat together milk and eggs.
Add salt and vanilla.
Dip bread into mixture until soaked.
Fry in butter on both sides until golden brown.
Serve with maple syrup or jam.

title: company baked beans
directions: Partially drain all beans; add chopped up bacon.
Mix and add remaining ingredients.
In a 2-quart casserole, bake uncovered 2 hours at 325°.
Makes approximately 2 quarts.

title: meatballs with mushroom sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together except mushroom soup.
Roll into little meatballs.
Brown nicely.
Combine mushroom soup with remaining onion soup mix (2 to 3 tablespoons).
Add water, about 1/2 cup, to make thin gravy of desired consistency.
Pour over meatballs.
Stir and simmer about 30 minutes.
Serve with noodles, rice or potatoes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine
ingredients
and bake in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes or until brown.

title: mexican stacks
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and garlic.
Add tomato sauce and tomatoes. Cook 15 minutes. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add dash of Worcestershire sauce.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with tortillas. Spoon meat mixture over each one, sprinkling with cheese.
Stack another layer of tortillas, meat and cheese on top of first layer. Place in oven and cook 20 minutes at 350°.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook meat and onions together.
Mix with other ingredients. Bake at 300° until done (inserted knife comes out clean), about 1 hour for 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serves 10.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Drain the liquid from all the chopped ingredients and then fold into the mayonnaise. Add vinegar and mix well. Chill. Serve with fish.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Mix together and roll into logs.
Put in waxed paper and chill.
Slice 1/2 inch thick and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 1 hour, divided.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar together.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add milk and dry ingredients alternately to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Pour batter into 2 (8 or 9-inch) cake pans, that have been greased and floured.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool and frost.

title: fruit salad
directions: Fold all ingredients together.
Let set at least two hours in refrigerator before serving.
Garnish with more chopped nuts, coconut and cherries.

title: zucchini bread i
directions: Mix together eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Divide batter into pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: molded turkey or chicken salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water over low heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add soup, salt, lemon juice, onion, mayonnaise and sour cream.
Chill until thick but not set.
Add celery and meat.
Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cinnamon popcorn
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir in the cereal and popcorn until evenly melted.
Bake for 10 minutes, stirring halfway through.
This is a very good recipe for gift giving at the holidays.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, and beat after each addition. Add flour, soda and sour cream.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into batter.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove immediately from pan. Mix a small amount of orange juice with some confectioners sugar and drizzle over warm cake.

title: garlic salad dressing
directions: In a jar with tight fitting lid, mix all ingredients by shaking well.
Chill.

title: poppy seed cake(serves 10)
directions: Mix the ingredients together with the cup of boiling water. Pour into a greased Bundt pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crunchy tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve on a bed of lettuce with sliced tomato and sliced hard-boiled egg.

title: "cheese cake"
directions: Put this on top of batter.
Bake at 325° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in medium bowl; mix well.
Combine eggs, milk and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients and mix well. Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until pie is set.
Cool on wire rack.

title: seafood sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in jar with lid.
Chill before serving.
If a milder sauce is preferred, substitute 1/4 cup pureed tomatoes for 1/2 chili sauce.
Try this for shrimp cocktail.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package and cut into bite size pieces when cool.
Make instant pudding as directed on package.
Layer cake, pudding and Cool Whip in a punch bowl, ending with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle Heath bars over top.
Chill and serve.

title: mexican stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells and set to side.
Cook meat and drain; add the cream cheese and chili powder.
Mix until blended.

title: cheese stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut off ends and scrub zucchini well.
Cook whole in boiling salted water to cover about 12 minutes or until barely tender. Remove from water and cut in halves lengthwise.
Scoop out center pulp.
Invert on paper towel to drain.

title: soft gingerbread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake at 400° until done.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan, 1-inch high or more.
It will rise nicely. Yields 32 servings.

title: hamburg stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in margarine until soft.
Add hamburg and fry.
Toss in a little flour.
Add mushrooms and soup; simmer 5 minutes.
Add sour cream and heat.
Do not boil!
Serve on rice. Will serve 8 people (a good meat stretcher!).

title: frozen asset
directions: Cut frozen pound cake lengthwise into 2 equal layers.
Place one layer on a large sheet of heavy-duty Reynolds wrap.
Cut 1 pint brick lengthwise into two slices and place on cake.
Top with second layer.
Wrap tightly in oil and freeze for half an hour. Remove from freezer.
Unfold foil.
Frost top and sides with one 4 1/2 ounce carton frozen whipped topping (thawed).
Arrange pecan halves and maraschino cherries on top.
Replace in freezer until topping is hard.
Remove double fold foil over top, close to food. Fold ends to make airtight seal.
Return to freezer.
Ready when frozen.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan. Cream the sugar, eggs and vegetable oil until well mixed.
Stir together the flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and cloves (optional). Add the dry mixture to the creamed mixture.
The batter will be very stiff.
Add the vanilla, apples and nuts and stir until thoroughly mixed.
Pour the batter into prepared pan.
Bake for one hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°. Heat butter or margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan in oven until melted. Remove. Stir in garlic, seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce. Add cereals, nuts and pretzels. Mix until all pieces are coated. Heat in oven 1 hour. Stir every 15 minutes. Spread on paper towels to cool. Makes 9 cups.

title: caramel ice cream dessert
directions: Mix oatmeal, pecans, caramel toping, margarine and brown sugar.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Crumble mixture.
Leave 3/4 of crumbled mixture in pan.
Spread softened ice cream over mixture.
Sprinkle remaining crumbled mixture on top.
Freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper together in a bowl.
In an 8 inch square pan layer crescent rolls or bread,
sausage, and cheese. Pour egg mixture over; and bake at 425° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: three bean salad
directions: Wash and drain all beans in colander.
Combine all beans, pepper and onion in bowl.
Heat vinegar, salt, pepper and oil. Pour over beans.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: swiss steak
directions: Dredge steak in flour mix.
In large skillet (electric skillet works great), brown steak in oil.
Top with spices, onion, celery, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Simmer 1 hour, check occasionally and add water, if necessary.
Serve over hot rice.

title: chicken maringo
directions: Coat chicken with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in oil in skillet, add garlic.
Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water. Add to skillet along with mushrooms and sauce.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, flour and salt together.
Beat eggs and add to milk. Gradually add to dry ingredients.
Add melted butter and vanilla.
Add coconut and pecans.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: stromboli
directions: Brown beef and onion; do not drain. Add sauce, Parmesan, garlic salt and oregano. Simmer for 15 minutes. Split and butter rolls.
Spoon meat mixture evenly on bottom of each roll. Set each roll on a square of foil.
Use all the liquid to soak into the roll.
Top each with slice of Mozzarella cheese.
Place top of roll on, then roll to seal foil.
Heat at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Can be used later, just reheat.

title: fran's frozen delight
directions: Put cranberry juice, frozen berries and lemon juice in blender. Fill with crushed ice.
Turn on blender a few seconds until well mixed.
Pour into glasses.
If a more frozen consistency is desired, make ahead and store in freezer.
Makes 1 quart.

title: instant cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in airtight container.
Use 1/3 cup to 1 cup boiling water.
Marshmallows optional!

title: holiday salad
directions: Cook together until smooth.
Remove from heat and let cool. Add remaining ingredients to cool mixture.
When combined, garnish with red or green cherries.
Chill 24 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Put broccoli, onion, cheese and bacon into salad bowl.
Make dressing with salad dressing, sugar and vinegar.
Mix well.
Pour over broccoli mix when ready to serve.

title: peach-champagne sorbet
directions: Soften gelatin in water in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until gelatin dissolves.
Combine peaches, sugar to taste (according to sweetness of peaches) and lemon juice in large bowl; mix well to combine.
Place half of mixture in blender; blend until smooth. Repeat with remaining half of peach mixture.

title: banana orange frost
directions: Put milk, orange juice, large scoop of orange sherbet and cut-up banana into blender.
Blend on high speed for 10 seconds. Pour into a tall glass.
Top with the small scoop of sherbet and serve right away.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and spread onto pizza pan.
Bake until brown. Set aside to cool.

title: glasa fruit
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Combine pineapple juice and dry pudding mix and stir until smooth.
Fold in pineapple chunks. Stir in bananas, oranges and Triple Sec.
Serve over vanilla ice cream or angel food cake or just as a breakfast jelly.

title: mediterranean broiled sandwich
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bread; spread on toasted bread. Broil 4-inches from flame about 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 4 open-faced sandwiches.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and oil together.
Add flour, salt, soda and vanilla.
Fold in apples and pecans.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Bake corn bread mix.
Brown bacon and cut up onions.
Slice peppers.
Break up corn bread into small pieces and put rest of ingredients together.
Mix well.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter together.
Pour over popcorn mix. Butter hands, then shape into balls.

title: corn pudding
directions: Butter baking dish well.
Mix all ingredients and salt to taste.
Dot with butter.
Set casserole dish in pan of hot water and bake at 325° until firm.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Cook two minutes in microwave.
Stir in baking soda.
Pour over 8 ounces popped corn in a grocery bag.
Shake hard.
Cook 90 seconds on High in microwave.
Shake again.
Cook 90 seconds again.
Shake and pour onto cookie sheet.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well, then put into a well lined 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan. Bake 45 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice vegetable dish
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add broccoli and steam for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Place in buttered dish.
Bake, uncovered, 40 minutes at 350°.

title: colonial yeast bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine corn meal, sugar or honey, salt, boiling water and oil.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir into cornmeal mixture.
Add whole wheat flour, rye flour and enough all-purpose flour to form a stiff dough.
Turn on floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down dough.
Divide into 2 balls.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes. Shape into 2 loaves.
Place in ungreased loaf pan.
Cover.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, sugar, butter, egg yolks and flavoring.
Bake at 450° until dry.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1 or 2 tablespoons of sugar and beat until it comes to a peak.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken and save broth.
Boil onion and bell pepper in broth until tender.
Add soups, Ro-Tel and chili powder.
Tear chicken apart and add to broth mixture.

title: steak salad
directions: Saute steak in butter; drain and set aside to cool.
Slice steak into small pieces.
Saute mushrooms (sliced) in butter; cool.
Slice cherry tomatoes in half, if large.
Slice scallions. Mix all ingredients.
Add favorite oil and vinegar dressing. Mince garlic and add.
Add sugar to taste.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together.
Roll in balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: country turkey noodle soup
directions: In 3 quart saucepan over medium heat, combine all ingredients except turkey and noodles.
Cover, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook 20 minutes, until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Add turkey and noodles; heat through.
Makes 7 cups or 4 servings.

title: coconut torte cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in three layers.
Cool completely.
With a long bread knife, slice each layer in half. Set aside on wax paper with cut side up.

title: lake livingston fish
directions: Rinse and pat dry the fish fillets.
Place in baking dish and sprinkle with Creole dressing.

Melt margarine and add lemon juice, parsley, dill weed, Parmesan cheese, green onions, white wine Worcestershire sauce and another shake or two of Creole seasoning. Pour mixture over fish fillets and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli as directed on package but cook only 4 minutes.
(If using fresh, peel stem portion and cook until not quite tender.)
Drain and put in greased 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle cheese over broccoli.
Put water chestnuts over cheese. Mix mushroom soup and evaporated milk.
Pour over other ingredients.
Bake about 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Take from oven and top with onion rings.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes more, until onions are crisp and golden brown.

title: one dish meal
directions: Place mushrooms in frying pan with oil.
Add broccoli, stir-fry.
Season with garlic salt or powder and black pepper. Add cooked and drained linguini, stir.
Add crispy cooked bacon, mix.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
If dish appears too dry, add a little mayonnaise.
Serve with green salad and toasted rolls.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook chicken in water until done.
Remove chicken from the bones.
Save the broth.
Crumble cornbread, bread, and crackers together.
Add eggs, salt, pepper, sage, green pepper, and onions. Add chicken pieces.
Pour liquid broth over the mixture and stir well.
Cook about 1 hour at 400°.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Mix ingredients in a blender.
Mix until smooth and creamy. Serve on crackers or bread.

title: summer fruit salad
directions: For salad, mix strawberries, grapes and bananas.
Spoon into lettuce covered dish.
Serve with Honey-Sour Cream Dressing.

title: chicken delight
directions: Combine in 3-quart casserole dish.
Cook 20 minutes at 400°.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Combine flour and baking powder.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add beaten eggs.
Add flour and baking powder, sifted together.
Stir in pecans and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: spinach ricotta quiche
directions: Saute chopped spinach in butter, black pepper, salt, and basil.
Set aside.	Mix spinach with all remaining ingredients except sour cream and paprika.
Blend well.
Pour into pie shell. Spread sour cream to edge of crust and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° 40 to 45 minutes. Serve hot.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine Jell-o and boiling water. Stir until dissolved. Add sauce to gelatin. Mix well. Stir in ginger ale. Pour into mold and place orange slices on top. Chill until set.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
Fold in enough of the can of beer to get the right consistency for the dip.
(Will probably use about 1/3 of the beer.)

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Add sugar gradually.
Add salt and vanilla.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake in a 300° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
