Serve topped with fresh sweetened berries.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain after cooking. Combine Blue cheese, cream cheese and milk in saucepan. Heat until mixture is smooth and melted.
Avoid burning or scorching mixture.
Place broccoli in casserole dish (average size).
Pour in cheese mixture.
Stir well. Top casserole with cracker crumbs. Bake at 375° for approximately 30 minutes or until you think it's finished.

title: quick whip chicken stir-fry
directions: Cook 1 pound boneless, skinless chicken breasts (cut into thin strips) in 1/2 cup low-fat mayonnaise.
Cook in large frying pan on medium heat for 3 minutes.
Add 1 package frozen mixed vegetables (thawed) or 3 1/2 cups cut up fresh vegetables.
Stir in 2 tablespoons soy sauce and 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder. Continue cooking for 5 minutes or until chicken is cooked through. Serve with rice.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: philly fruit dip
directions: Allow cheese to soften to room temperature.
Mix cheese, marshmallow cream and a few drops of cherry juice.
Mix thoroughly.
Serve with fruit.

title: herb scalloped tomatoes
directions: In a greased 2 quart casserole, mix together tomatoes and 2 cups of stuffing mix.
Stir in onion, sugar and seasoning mix. Dot with margarine; sprinkle remaining stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.
We have used this recipe at our church suppers.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Drain well.
Mix with other ingredients and serve.

title: mississippi pine cone
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Add remaining ingredients except almonds.
Place mixture on pretty dish and shape like a pine cone in center of dish.
Begin at large end with the almonds, placing side by side and sticking up, looking like "pine burrs."
Garnish with twig of pine needles from a real pine tree. If made the night before, do not place almonds until ready to serve.
Place crackers around cone.

title: tamale pie
directions: Oil casserole dish; spread half cornbread batter on bottom of dish.
Brown meat with all ingredients except cheese, beans, corn and olives.
Drain meat.
Add beans and corn and mix.
Spread filling on bottom of dish; add cheese and olives.
Add remaining cornbread batter.
Sprinkle cheese and olives.
Bake at 350° until bread is brown.
Let warm and slice.
Serve with green salad and wine.

title: fritters(basic fritter recipe)
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Whip egg.
Add milk and melted butter to egg.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients.
Beat batter vigorously.
Drop by tablespoons into hot oil (approximately 1 cup of oil is needed).
Fry until golden brown.
Turn over once. Place on paper towel to drain excess oil.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth batter.
Set oven at 350° to 400°.
Best results when cooked in pan with roast beef drippings (about 1/4 inch on bottom of pan).
Cooking time is 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mustard dip(for pretzels)
directions: Mix the above ingredients together.
Serve with pretzels.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour 2 cups batter in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: grandma's egg custard
directions: Mix the sugar and cornstarch together.
In another bowl beat eggs.
Combine dry ingredients with eggs.
Add milk and vanilla; stir well.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: roasted new potatoes with lemon
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter large casserole.
Add potatoes. Season generously with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan over medium heat.
Add lemon juice.
Pour sauce over potatoes and toss well.
Add lemon peel and toss to coat.
Bake until potatoes are tender, about 1 hour.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crispy onion rolls
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Melt butter and add soup mixture.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture into ungreased 8-inch round baking pan. Arrange biscuits in pan and pour remaining mixture over.
Bake for 12 to 14 minutes or until browned.
Serve at once.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Sprinkle nuts on top; refrigerate.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except carrots, then add the mix to the carrots. Chill.

title: fiesta corn
directions: Blend all ingredients together, except the cheese and chilies. Pour 1/2 of the corn mixture into a casserole; top with 1/2 of the grated cheese and the chilies.
Pour in the rest of the corn mixture and top with remaining cheese.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in 3-quart bowl.
Stir in sugar, salt, shortening, eggs, potatoes and 3 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto well floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic (about 5 minutes).
Place in greased bowl, turn greased side up and cover tightly.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours.

title: low-fat white bean soup
directions: Place beans in Dutch oven or large saucepan.
Add water to cover.
Bring to a boil; boil 2 minutes.
Cover; turn off heat and let stand 1 hour.
Drain.
Add 6 cups water, bouillon, thyme, salt, onion, garlic and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 1 hour.
Then add carrot and celery.
Cover and simmer an additional 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Just before serving, stir in parsley and tomato.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: In shallow baking or roasting pan, thoroughly blend all ingredients, except potatoes.
Add potatoes and turn to coat thoroughly.
Bake, stirring potatoes occasionally, for 60 minutes, or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Can be garnished with parsley.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Put popped corn in a roaster pan.
(Note:
Syrup will mix more evenly through popcorn that's slightly warm, so place the roaster in a slow oven while you cook the syrup or wait to pop corn until syrup is done.)
Bring the butter, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt to a vigorous boil, stirring constantly.
Cook 2 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat and add the baking soda and vanilla.
Pour syrup over popped corn, mixing well.
Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove popcorn from oven and let cool.
Break into chunks.

title: holiday wassail
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a large crock-pot (6-quart) on low.
Yields 5 1/2 quarts.

title: water chestnuts with bacon
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Cut strips of bacon into thirds.
Wrap bacon around chestnut; secure with toothpick.
Pour Worcestershire sauce over each toothpick all the way around.
Bake in oven until bacon is cooked thoroughly.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients; form
a well and add oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Bake in a 10 x 16-inch (jelly roll) pan for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Frost when cool with:

title: easy cheesy snacks(italian style)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Remove dough from can.
Do not unroll. Cut dough into 8 slices; place slices on ungreased cookie sheet. Top each slice with 1/8 of the onions, garlic powder and Cheddar cheese; press topping gently into dough.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 13 minutes or until light golden brown.
Sprinkle with cheeses. Serve warm.
Great for dipping!

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients; form into small meatballs.
Fry meatballs in shortening.
Mix the last 6 ingredients together in pan; heat until it thickens.
Add meatballs; simmer in crock-pot until done.

title: double decker fudge
directions: Spray 8-inch square pan with "Pam".
Place Reese's chips and 2/3 cup condensed milk in Corning Ware or similar type dish. Microwave 1 1/2 minutes.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Spread into pan and evenly distribute.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Add taco mix, tomatoes, enchilada sauce, salt, pepper and olives.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Combine egg, cheese and cottage cheese in a bowl and mix by hand.

title: rigatoni casserole
directions: On medium-high heat, saute beef, onion and garlic 4 minutes or until beef is browned.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and pepper. Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes.
In bowl, combine Ricotta, milk and salt.
Add rigatoni; toss to coat well.
Spoon 1/2 the rigatoni mixture into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with 1/2 the Mozzarella and 1/2 the sauce.
Repeat.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: heart smart baked chicken
directions: Mix together oatmeal, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and paprika.
Place oatmeal mixture in shallow dish.
In a separate shallow dish, mix garlic and milk.
Place chicken, one piece at a time, in oatmeal mixture, then dip in milk mixture and again in oatmeal mixture.
Place chicken in a large shallow baking dish and drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until fork can be inserted with ease.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix meat with all ingredients.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for about 1 hour.
If the meat is extremely lean, you may want to add an egg or 2 tablespoons of milk for added moisture.

title: cuban black beans potage
directions: Soak beans in 4 cups cold water for 1 hour.
Drain gently. Cook beans in 4 cups water until tender.
Add more hot water if necessary.
Drain beans, reserving liquid.
Saute onion in hot oil.
Add red sweet peppers and continue cooking for a few seconds.
Pour in beans and season with salt, wine, oregano and sugar.
Simmer over medium heat until creamy.
Add bean liquid or water if necessary.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in sour cream and flour.
Spoon into miniature muffin tins.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 18 small muffins.

title: christmas butter cookies(not necessarily for christmas)
directions: Cream butter; then add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll cookies out on a floured surface.
Use cookies to make cookies. Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water and let set until it begins to jell.
Mix strawberries, banana and pecans, then mix into chilled jello.
Pour half of strawberry mixture into an 8 x 8-inch or 6 x 10-inch Pyrex dish and place in refrigerator.
Hold other half out and stir occasionally to keep from jelling.
When refrigerated jello is firm enough, spread sour cream over the top and pour on the remaining jello mixture.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: applesauce
directions: Wash and cut up apples, seeds, skin and all.
Add water and salt.
Cook slow until done.
Put through coarse strainer.
Add spice to taste and sweetener or leave plain.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
This is very good with black walnuts.
Shape into rolls and chill 4 hours.
Slice and bake at 400° for 3 to 8 minutes.
Dough may be kept chilled for two weeks.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cut Crisco into flour until consistency of corn meal; add water and stir until forms ball.
Roll out on floured board into round shape to fit a pie pan; prick pie shell and bake at 400° until lightly brown, about 10 minutes.

title: salmon biscuit ring
directions: Drain salmon.
Combine with egg, cheese, onion and parsley; mix well.
Using fork, blend baking mix and milk until soft dough forms.
Knead gently 12 to 15 times.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook the rice as directed. Brown together the sausage, onion, green pepper and celery. Add the mushrooms and water chestnuts. Stir in the rice and soup.
Put in casserole dish and top with the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with the French fried onions. Bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes.

title: clouds at sunrise
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until frothy; add cream of tartar, then gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold in crushed crackers, nuts and vanilla.
Spread in well buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Bake for 25 minutes. Cool in pan on rack.
When cool, spread thawed whipped topping over crust.
Spoon cherry pie filling over whipped topping.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: cucumber and red onion salad
directions: Remove ends from cucumbers.
Slice unpared cucumbers thinly. Mix salt and water; pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain well.
Slice peeled onion thinly; separate into rings.
Toss with cucumbers.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables; toss until well coated.
Chill.
Serves 8.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Peel and cut up onion.
Cook potatoes and onion in 8 cups water.
When done, remove 2 cups water and reserve.
Add butter to hot potatoes.
Mix dry milk with reserved potato water.
Mash potatoes coarsely.
Add milk to potatoes.
If desired, add additional water, salt and pepper to taste.

title: classic macaroni salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir together real mayonnaise, vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper until smooth. Add macaroni, celery, green pepper and onion.
Toss to coat well. Cover and chill. Makes 5 cups.
(You may also add diced cheese and ham to use as an entree.)

title: quick cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in a sheet cake pan.
Mix all ingredients, except fruit, and pour over butter.
Pour fruit over batter and butter mixture.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes or until browned well.

title: bulgogi
directions: Put sesame seed in frying pan over medium heat.
Shake pan frequently.
Seeds will turn light brown in 2 to 3 minutes. Remove seeds and crush.
Cut beef across the grain into long thin (1/8-inch thick) slices.
In a bowl, mix all ingredients together except steak.
Add meat to mixture last and marinate at least 2 hours.
Remove meat from marinade and grill about 4 inches above solid bed of glowing coals.
Serve over fried or white rice.
This recipe will not taste the same if the meat is not grilled.

title: baked chicken with a flair
directions: Mix water and soup together.
Place chicken in a Pyrex pan. Pour mixture over.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: simple cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll out soft dough and spread with other ingredients.
Roll up and cut in slices.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer the ingredients in a pie pan: bean dip, taco seasoning mix, mixed with sour cream and mayo, layer of mild Cheddar cheese, green onions, layer of chopped tomato and layer of chopped black olives. Serve with taco chips.

title: country oven stew
directions: Coat meat with 2 tablespoons
flour.
Brown meat and onions in hot oil in skillet.
Stir in salt, pepper, soup and water.
Transfer to a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, in slow oven (325°) for one hour.
Stir in carrots.
Bake 30 minutes longer.

title: savory party bread
directions: Cut bread lengthwise and crosswise without cutting through the bottom crust.
Cut cheese into 1-inch squares, 1/4-inch thick. Place cheese slices in between bread cuts.

title: cashew chicken(from france)
directions: Slice chicken breasts into 1/4-inch pieces.
Set aside.
Wash and slice fresh mushrooms or drain and slice canned mushrooms. Set aside.
Wash scallions; slice white part into 1/4-inch slices. Cut green part into 1-inch lengths.
Slash both ends several times, making small fans.
Set aside.
Drain water chestnuts and slice.
Set aside.
Wash snow peas.
If fresh, this will already be done.
Mix tamari with cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Set aside.

title: strawberry cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a saucepan, put water and sugar.
Heat long enough to melt sugar.
Set aside.
Make up batter as if you would pie crust (flour, shortening and milk).
Divide in half.
Roll half out on floured wax paper.
Cut into strips about 1 1/2-inches wide.
This you will lay in bottom of pan with melted oleo.
Add fruit.
Roll out the other half of the dough and cut in 1/2-inch strips.
Lay this on top of the fruit.
Now pour water and sugar mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
You may use peaches or blackberries.

title: pineapple rice
directions: Cook rice and drain well. Combine pineapple, sugar and butter in a saucepan and stir well, place over heat and bring to a boil. Boil 10 minutes. Mix with cooked rice and place in a buttered casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to an hour. Serves 8 to 10.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Add eggs to mashed potatoes, mixing well, then add the flour and finish mixing.
Drop into boiling salt water or consomme. Cook until done.
Serve on top of sauerkraut.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind together cranberries, oranges and apple; let stand a few hours.
Dissolve jello in water.
Pour cranberry mixture with jello.
Add ginger ale.
Put in refrigerator until set.

title: chili-bean and eggplant custard
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, cut eggplant crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.
In nonstick 10-inch skillet over medium heat in 1 tablespoon hot salad oil, cook 1/3 of the eggplant slices until browned on one side.
Turn eggplant slices; add 1 tablespoon salad oil and cook until tender and browned on the second side. Remove eggplant to plate.
Repeat with remaining eggplant slices, adding more salad oil as needed.

title: cola cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except cola and marshmallows in large mixing bowl.
Blend at low speed, beat one minute at medium speed. Add cola and blend well.
By hand, stir in marshmallows.
Pour batter into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: fillets in lemon dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in oil.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Place 2 fillets on bottom of lightly oiled baking dish.
Spread filling over fish and top with remaining fillets.
Dust with pepper and paprika.
Dot with margarine if desired.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until fish flakes with a fork.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix raisins, eggs and vanilla.
Soak for 1 hour.
Cream butter, brown sugar and white sugar together.
Blend in flour, baking soda, salt, oatmeal, cinnamon and pecans.
Mix well; add egg and raisin mixture.
Drop onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: chicken mornay
directions: Into the bottom of 9 x 12-inch ungreased baking dish, pour the rice.
Place chicken breasts on the rice, then top each breast with slice of Swiss cheese.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef lightly in pan.
Peel potatoes and wash. Peel and wash onions.
In casserole dish, put layer of sliced potatoes, layer of sliced onions and layer of browned ground beef. Season each layer as you put them in casserole.
Continue to layer until you use up ingredients.
Pour cream of celery soup over contents.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: hot chili
directions: In large pot, cook hamburger and onions until done.
Drain. Add peppers, kidney beans, pimentos and mushrooms.
Add salt and chili powder to taste.
Then add sauce and stir well.
Cover and let simmer.

title: roast meat(pork or beef)
directions: Rub salt and pepper over meat.
Soak meat in garlic, vinegar and shoyu at least 6 hours.
Turn at least every 2 hours.
Leave in refrigerator.
Fry meat in 1 tablespoon oil in pot until brown. Add shoyu and vinegar sauce into pot; add 1/2 cup water and cook on low heat at least 2 hours or until meat is tender.
When liquid becomes absorbed, add more water.
When done, use the liquid from meat to make gravy.
Remove meat from pot.
Add more water to make the amount of gravy desired.
Add shoyu, salt and pepper to your taste and thicken gravy with flour or cornstarch.

title: zippy deviled eggs
directions: Halve eggs and remove yolks.
In a large bowl, break up eggs with a fork.
Using a hand mixer, blend in mayonnaise, mustard, onion powder, salt and Tabasco until smooth.
Fill egg whites with mixture.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic in frypan.
Add spaghetti sauce and seasonings.
Cook noodles.
Drain well.
Arrange in baking dish a layer of cooked noodles, cottage cheese to which a beaten egg has been added, a layer of Mozzarella cheese and meat sauce. Continue layers until dish is full.
Sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Keep popcorn hot and crisp in a slow oven (300° to 325°).

title: brownie cake dessert
directions: Mix cake mix, cornstarch, applesauce, yogurt, vanilla and eggs.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Grease flat, oblong pan. Heat oven to 350° and bake dessert until center springs back. Frost, if desired, or cover with Cool Whip.

title: mexican relish
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well. Chill. Serves with Fritos or tortilla chips.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In large bowl, stir first five ingredients until well blended.
Pour into pie crust and bake 50 to 55 minutes.

title: mushroom madeira soup
directions: In a small saucepan, combine the Madeira, 1/2 cup chicken stock and 1/2 pound mushrooms. Bring to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes; set aside.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni in salted water until tender; drain.
Blanch in cold water; drain.
Add other ingredients except mayonnaise.
Toss lightly, then mix in mayonnaise.
Cover and chill several hours before serving.
Serves 15 to 20 people.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Boil together for custard the first 5 ingredients.
Cook until thick, then cool.
Combine pineapple, marshmallows and cherries. Fold in whipped cream.
Add custard to fruit mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 12.

title: crusty corn meal loaves
directions: Mix 2 1/2 cups flour, corn meal, salt and dry yeast.
Using an electric mixer, add soft butter.
Gradually add water and honey; beat.
Add 1/2 cup flour and beat at high speed for 2 minutes. Stir in additional flour.
Make a stiff dough.

title: poppy seed coffee cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, pudding mix, oil and eggs; beat well. Add hot water and 1/4 cup poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.

title: mint brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Combine sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add the Nestle chocolate and flour, nuts and peppermint.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut.

title: doyle's goulash
directions: Cook hamburger and onion in skillet until brown. Add other ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix together boiling water and zucchini in large mixing bowl. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in lightly greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.
Top with Lemon Swirl Frosting.

title: norwegian apple pie
directions: Slice baking apples.
Place into a pie plate.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by rounded tablespoons onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in lemonade concentrate.
Add cold water and cranberry juice cocktail.
Put in punch bowl with 2 trays of ice cubes and ginger ale.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Mix and stir in sugar and flour.
Add butter, salt, vanilla, almond extract and buttermilk and blend well.
Pour into two 8-inch unbaked pastry shells.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: holiday cranberry tea
directions: Combine all ingredients in a Dutch oven over low heat.
Cook, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes or until sugar dissolves.
Serve warm.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cook ham in a skillet over medium heat. Add onion.
Cook and stir until tender.
Add the salt and potatoes; blend.
Keep on low heat. Incorporate the sour cream and serve at once, sprinkled with paprika.
Serves 6.

title: noodles with cheese and sour cream
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Saute onions and butter in a frying pan.
Mix with noodles.
Add cottage cheese and sour cream.
Mix together into the noodles.
Put into casserole or pan.
You can put buttered crumbs on top if you wish.
Heat in 375° oven to warm only.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Drain and mash potatoes.
Add oleo, salt and egg.
Make patties of mixture and wrap around a marshmallow to form a ball. Dip in crushed cornflakes and fry in oil in skillet.
Serve with precooked ham, etc.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Mix chicken and broth.
Add remainder of ingredients; mix well.
Pour into casserole dish; bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until brown.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Cook carrots in 1/2 cup boiling water in covered saucepan for 3 minutes and drain.
Combine with the rest of the vegetables. Combine mustard, vinegar, garlic, salt and pepper.
Gradually add oil, stirring briskly to blend.
Pour over vegetables and toss to coat.
Chill thoroughly.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Beat together the shortening, sugar and vanilla with mixer until mixture looks like ice cream.
Thoroughly beat in eggs, one at a time.
In a 1-pint measuring cup or bowl, stir together buttermilk and soda (mixture bubbles up).
By hand, stir the flour in several additions into the creamed mixture, alternating with the buttermilk mixture and mixing only until smooth.
Turn into a 10-inch angel cake pan.
Bake in preheated 325° until cake tester comes out clean, 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes; loosen edges.
Turn out on rack with another rack, turned right side up.
Cool completely.

title: no bake barbecue beans
directions: In skillet, combine all.
Cook on medium heat until thick. Let boil good.

title: grits and green chili
directions: Brown sausage, stirring until it is crumbly and no longer pink. Drain on paper towels. While sausage is cooking, bring water and salt to a boil. Add grits and cook until creamy. Remove grits from heat. Add cheese and stir until cheese is melted. Add green chili, eggs and margarine. Add cooked sausage. Bake in 9 x 13-inch dish at 350° for 1 hour. Let set a few minutes. Cut into squares and serve.

title: grandma's butter crisps
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla, lemon extract and eggs and blend.
Add dry ingredients and milk; mix well.
Chill dough thoroughly, several hours or overnight.
Press a small amount of dough at a time through cookie press onto ungreased cookie sheet using the plate for shape desired.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes until light golden.
Cookies may be decorated before baking with bits of candied fruit, jam or colored sprinkles or bake plain and then ice and decorate.

title: tasty zucchini relish
directions: Sprinkle salt over ground zucchini and onion.
Let stand overnight; drain.
Rinse with water; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, bring to boil, turn heat down and simmer 30 minutes. Put relish in 7 or 8 sterilized pint jars; seal.

title: beer batter chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper in bowl.
Beat in beer until smooth.
Let stand approximately 30 minutes.
Pour oil in frypan. Heat oil on high flame, then lower.
Dip chicken pieces in batter. Cover completely.
Fry until chicken is done.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve with salad.
Great cold day after.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches with 1/2 cup sugar.
Let stand.
Put butter in a 2-quart casserole.
Place in a 325° oven to melt.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix until smooth.
Pour over melted butter. Do not stir!
Spoon peaches on top of batter.
Do not stir!
Bake for 1 hour in a 325° oven.
You can use canned peaches or other fresh fruit.

title: mama's tater soup
directions: Cover potatoes with water and boil until tender.
Pour off water but keep enough to make potatoes soupy.
Mash potatoes into water.
Add butter, onions, salt, pepper, garlic salt, carrot and milk.

title: apple dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix all other ingredients for great dip.

title: fruit balls
directions: Chop or grind coarse all of the ingredients.
Add 3 tablespoons orange concentrate; mix well and then form into balls and roll in coconut.
Store in airtight container in a cold place.

title: grace's special
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Roll out dough.
Spread with margarine.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll not more than 1 1/2-inches high.
Cut into 2-inch lengths.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: italian velvet cake
directions: Cream together butter, oil and sugar.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat 5 egg whites until stiff peaks.
Fold into cake mixture.
Put into 3 round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix altogether with electric mixer until well blended.
Dip sliced apples into dip.
Optional: Add peanuts (skinless, salted or unsalted, chopped or whole) on the side or mixed into dip. (Nuts will become soft after a day or two if mixed into dip.)

title: applesauce cake
directions: Blend shortening and sugar together.
Add egg and applesauce. Sift together next 5 ingredients.
Dissolve soda in boiling water. Mix all together and add walnuts.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour or until done.

title: venison strips with wine
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Shake flour, salt, pepper, crushed rosemary and thyme in regular sized oven cooking bag.
Place in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add wine, broth and oil; mix to dissolve flour.
Add venison, onion and bay leaf.
Close bag with nylon tie. Make 6 half-inch slits in top of bag.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until fork-tender.
Serve over cooked noodles tossed with butter and parsley.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add small amounts to creamed mixture until well blended.
Add nuts and apples.
Mixture will be very stiff.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: waldorf astoria red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add milk, sifted dry ingredients (flour, cocoa and salt).
Beat until fluffy, then add food coloring and vanilla.
Fold in (do not beat).
Mix soda and vinegar together and add last.
Pour into two 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook and drain tortellini.
Add ingredients to taste and add any additional ingredients desired.

title: brownies #1
directions: Melt butter in saucepan, then stir in cocoa and cool. Beat eggs and add sugar.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt and gradually add to egg mixture.
Stir in vanilla and cooled chocolate mixture.
May add 1 c. walnuts.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 28 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: easy crisp sweet pickles
directions: If you start pickles at 6 or 7 P.M., you can be finished by after lunch the next day.

title: lemon-marinated chicken
directions: Mix together and marinate chicken 2 to 4 hours.
Grill until done, brushing marinated mixture over it while it cooks.
Can use on tuna steaks or salmon steaks.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour in skillet.
Add water, butter and vanilla.
Cook until thickened.
Serve on hot buttered biscuits.

title: aunt jane's hot sauce(salsa)
directions: Skin tomatoes and quarter.
Start cooking in large pot while doing the rest of them.
Cut into small pieces the rest of the ingredients.
Continue cooking for 1 to 2 hours (until as thick as you like).
I take a slotted spoon and take out large hunks and put through the blender as it cooks.
Bottle and seal.
Process for 25 to 30 minutes in canner.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Sift flour and soda together.
Add to first mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour.
Add flavorings and blend.
Pour in greased and lightly floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 300° oven about 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: curried fruit
directions: Mix liquids.
Add slowly to flour until thick.
Pour over fruit in Pyrex dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Heat to serve.

title: out-of-this-world cherry pie
directions: In a large saucepan, bring to a boil the cherry pie filling, pineapple with its juice, cornstarch, sugar and food coloring. Cook until thick.
Remove from heat; add the dry gelatin.
Mix well.
Cool to lukewarm or cooler.
Place in baked pie shell. Chill.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar, butter and bananas.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour, soda and salt, then stir in the nuts.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: quick butter roll
directions: Roll dough into a rectangle.
Spread 1 stick of oleo over dough.
Add 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon nutmeg.
Roll dough up and put in a pan.
Put remainder of oleo, sugar and nutmeg over roll. Add vanilla and boiling water.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes, until juice is thick and roll is brown.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Cook sugar and water on high until sugar melts.
Add nuts and cook until crystallized.
Don't stir too much especially if you use peanuts as the husk will come off.
Lower heat when you add nuts.
Add vanilla; stir until dry.
Pour and spread on buttered pan.
Salt lightly and bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: beef stew
directions: Place stew beef, onion soup, mushroom soup and 2 cups water into a crock pot.
Boil potatoes and carrots in water on top of stove until partially done, drain and place in crock pot with beef mixture.
Cook on high until morning, leave on low until later in the day when you are ready.

title: baked bean bluff
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in microwave.
Cook bacon in microwave.
Combine all the ingredients and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve or pour into baking dish and top with additional bacon and heat for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In large heavy skillet melt 2 tablespoons butter over low heat.
Saute onion until limp but not brown.
Push onion to one side and add flour, stirring until brown.
Add all other ingredients except shrimp.
Stir constantly until mixture thickens and comes to slow boil.
Lower heat until mixture simmers.
Cover and continue to cook about 35 minutes.

title: bobbie's cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans and butter.
Preheat oven at 375°.
Melt butter in Bundt cake pan and cover the entire pan. Pour out excess butter.
Place pecans in bottom of pan.
Pour in cake batter and bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Do not open oven.
Crust is golden brown.
Use knife to loosen cake after it has cooled, before serving.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Empty potato slices and dry sauce packet into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Heat tomatoes, water and oregano to boiling.
Pour into potatoes and arrange pepperoni on top.
Sprinkle with grated Mozzarella or Cheddar cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and blend well.
Add food coloring and cocoa.
Blend in buttermilk.
Add flour and salt.
Gradually add vanilla and beat.
Mix vinegar and soda; stir in last.
Do not beat.
Pour into 9-inch cake pans and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Heat butter in a 2-quart saucepan until melted.
Stir in brown sugar, salt and cream.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; cool to lukewarm.
Stir in enough powdered sugar gradually until of spreading consistency.
Stir in vanilla.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Chill and serve with chips, crackers or vegetables.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: Put together in layers.
Let set overnight.
Mix well before serving.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Beat eggs, salt, pepper and garlic salt together with a fork.
Dip eggplant into egg mixture and then bread crumbs and fry until brown.
Drain well.
Put in bottom of casserole dish.

title: pecan-pumpkin pie
directions: Mix well the first 4 ingredients; spread over bottom of unbaked pie shell.	Combine the next 5
ingredients.
Stir	in pecans.
Spread over pumpkin mixture in pie
shell.
Bake	at 350° for 50 minutes, or until set.

title: banana-kiwi fool
directions: Put first five ingredients in pot over medium heat; stir to thicken and boil 1 minute.
Put in glass dish, cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.
Beat cheese, sugar and vanilla until fluffy; add cream and beat until stiff.
Fold fruit mixture into cheese mixture.
Chill some more.

title: strawberry nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat thoroughly. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream and more strawberries, if desired.

title: lemon butter bars
directions: Crust: In a small bowl, mix 1 cup flour, 1/4 cup granulated sugar and butter until mixture is crumbly, resembling corn meal. Press on bottom of a square 9-inch baking pan that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes until edges are lightly browned. Leave oven on.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Prepare a whole chicken by rinsing and then patting dry. Season with salt, pepper and a little garlic salt.

Put about 1/4 stick margarine and 1/4 of an onion in the cavity of the chicken. Put chicken directly in a large brown grocery sack. Fold the edge of the sack 3 or 4 times, then put 4 or 5 large paper clips on it to keep it sealed.
Place sack on a cookie sheet and cook 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chayote and rice salad
directions: Place in a blender the green pepper, garlic, oil, lime juice and salt.
Chop them at high speed, then add red pepper, tomato, onion and cilantro.
Chop coarsely for 10 seconds.
In a medium bowl mix together rice and blender mixture.
Stir in some sliced blanched almonds, if desired.
Cut Chayote into small pieces. Carefully stir it in to keep pieces whole.
Put mixture in a Tupperware mold and refrigerate overnight.
Serve at room temperature on a serving plate with green aspic and avocado in the middle and a cherry tomato on top.
Serves 6 to 8.
Delicious.

title: strawberry squares
directions: Bake cake 30 minutes in a 350° oven in a greased cookie sheet; cool.
Make pudding; add cream cheese and spread on cake.
Cook strawberries with cornstarch; cool and spread on top of cream cheese.
Top with Cool Whip; cut in squares (pineapple or blueberries can be used in place of strawberries).

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Slice cucumber and onion.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over cucumber and onion.
Cover and chill for 30 minutes or more before serving.

title: orange delight
directions: Stir jello into boiling water until dissolved.
Add cream and marshmallow to hot liquid.
Mix until dissolved.
Cool in refrigerator until syrupy.
Fold in drained pineapple, carrots and nuts.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Let cool.
Add remaining ingredients, except whipped cream.
When mixture begins to jell, add whipped cream, mixing well.
Pour into mold or Pyrex pan.

title: peanut crunch cake
directions: Mix peanut butter and Karo syrup.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well.
Press 2/3 of mixture in tube pan, sides and bottom. Freeze, then add ice cream.
Pack ice cream into frozen crunch mixture.
Freeze.
After frozen, remove from pan and wrap to keep frozen until needed.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Brown onion in bacon drippings.
Cook lima beans according to the directions and drain.
Mix these ingredients and stir in the tomato soup.

title: ground nut sauce(uganda)
directions: Pound peanuts with mortar and pestle, grind in blender, or put through meat grinder several times to make coarse peanut powder. Roast in pan for 1 minute.
Fry in oil the onions, tomatoes, curry powder, garlic and ginger root. Add peanut powder.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add water or milk slowly to form sauce.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Add salt.
Serve over rice or plantains.
Serves 6.

title: wild rice and ham casserole
directions: Cook rice together according to directions in 3 cups water. Set aside.
Cook broccoli.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer half of rice, broccoli, Cheddar cheese, mushrooms and cut up ham.
Repeat. Spread soup on top and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: Simmer until smooth, stirring well.
Cook 20 minutes.
Just before serving, add the paprika, lemon juice and salt.

title: saucy cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, egg and salt; shape into 50 meatballs. Place in shallow baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Broil until browned; turn once.
Spoon off fat.
In saucepan, cook pepper and onion in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour over meatballs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: quick dip
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: exquisite dairy dessert
directions: Arrange a layer of ladyfingers in a large glass bowl.
Whip the cream cheese and sour cream with sugar and add the pudding mixed with milk until you get a smooth mixture.
Divide into two and cover the ladyfingers with half the quantity.
Decorate with sliced fruit and cover with whipped cream.
Repeat the arrangement of the layers and top with strawberries.
Keep refrigerated.

title: old fashioned sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes and butter, mixing until blended.
Add combined sugar, flour and spices; mix well.
Blend in eggs and milk.
Pour into crusts.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and continue baking 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: catfish stew
directions: Cook the fish until the meat flakes.
Fry the fatback and use the drippings to saute the onions.
In a large pot, combine fish, potatoes, onions, tomato sauce, paste, salt and pepper.
Cook until potatoes are well done.
Add Tabasco sauce to taste.

title: banana-split cake
directions: Combine first three ingredients and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan for the crust.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain and rinse.
While macaroni cooks, brown ground beef, onion, salt and pepper.
When done, mix macaroni and beef and add pizza sauce, tomato paste, tomato sauce and sugar. Mix all together and add several dashes of garlic salt, onion salt and oregano.

Place 1/2 mixture in long casserole dish and top with 1/4 pound Mozzarella cheese and put rest of mixture on top; cover with 1/2 pound Mozzarella cheese and put pepperoni slices on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot mushroom turnovers
directions: With electric mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese, 1/2 cup butter and flour until soft dough forms.
Wrap dough, chill 1 hour.
In medium skillet, saute mushrooms and onion until tender. Blend in salt, thyme and 2 tablespoons flour.
Stir in sour cream. Chill.

title: easy  dessert
directions: Butter a 9 x 13 inch pan, turn undrained crushed pineapple into pan and spread around.
Cover with pie filling.
Spread dry cake mix all over fruit.
Slice 1-1/2 sticks butter all over the cake mix.

title: pineapple macaroons
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Combine next ingredients (6).
Combine flour and baking powder.
Beat into pineapple mixture until blended.
Spoon by heaping tablespoon 1-inch apart onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: dover cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat until creamy.
Sift flour and baking powder together and add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Beat
until smooth.
Bake in tube pan for an hour.
Test for doneness.
Bake at 350°.
Top with powdered sugar.

title: bacon tomato cups
directions: Spray 3 mini muffin pans with Pam.
Separate biscuits into 3 parts.
Place in muffin pans.
Use tart shaper.
Dip in flour and push biscuit into pans.
Mix all ingredients together and spoon into biscuit.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes 20 to 30 appetizers.

title: quick and easy chili
directions: Brown ground chuck in Dutch oven, stirring until it crumbles; drain. Add beans and next 5 ingredients to beef in Dutch oven. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium and simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Ladle chili into bowl. Sprinkle with cheese and dollop with sour cream, if used.

title: spinach in a bread bowl
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread.
Cut circle in top of one loaf of bread; hollow it out.
Put filling inside.
Cut remaining loaf into cubes.
Serve with small knife.

title: corky's famous rice pudding
directions: Put milk, rice and butter in heavy saucepan.
When it comes to a boil, add sugar and mix well. Stir occasionally.
In separate mixing bowl, mix eggs, light cream, vanilla and food coloring. Beat well.
When rice is cooked, add egg mixture.
Cook until rice floats to the top.

title: cheese cake
directions: Blend until smooth.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with Comstock pie filling (your choice).
Chill 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies (from cake mix)
directions: Combine
the
ingredients
and
cool
in
refrigerator covered, for about	2 hours.
Roll out on floured surface, not too thin with favorite cookie cutter. Bake at 375° for 6 to 10 minutes. Cool on rack.

title: fruit freeze
directions: Drain juice from apricots, apples, peaches and pineapple. Blend in blender. Mash bananas and mix with lemon juice. Mix into fruit mixture. Freeze (stirring often) until mushy with ice.

title: thumbprints
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in flour, almond extract and salt until well combined.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place balls 1 1/2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly, then indent centers with thumb.
Fill with 1/4 teaspoon of preserves.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until edges are firm.
Cool on wire rack. Makes about 40 cookies.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water in a large bowl.
Add other ingredients; freeze.
Remove from freezer approximately 2 hours before serving and mash into slush with a potato masher.

title: broccoli casserole(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Coat a shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with vegetable oil cooking spray.
Set aside.

title: sweet salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
Store at room temperature.
Great on fresh spinach, mushroom and crouton salad.

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Clean and devein shrimp.
Crush crackers and melt butter or margarine.
Mix up the crabmeat if using.
Align shrimp on a cookie sheet.
You must cut the shrimp up the back and spread open on the cookie sheet.
Mix margarine or butter with the cracker crumbs and place on top of each shrimp.
If using the crabmeat, it should be mixed in with the margarine or butter and cracker crumbs, adding the garlic powder to taste.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes, or until the shrimp appear to be opaque in color.

title: burrito filling
directions: Cook ground beef in large skillet until it starts to brown. Add onions and cook until limp.
Drain excess fat.
Add can of tomatoes and green chilies, beans and Tabasco.
Add can of green chilies; stir to mix.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve on either flour tortillas or corn tortillas. Garnish with shredded cheese, chopped onion and shredded lettuce. Makes 8
servings (1/3 cup each); 194 calories and 16 grams fat.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Combine crushed Ritz crackers, butter and sugar.
Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Save some crumbs for top.

title: dutch apple salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and cook as pudding.
After it starts to thicken and becomes clear, add butter and vanilla.
Let cool.
In larger bowl, combine diced apples, grapes, marshmallows and nuts.
Pour pudding mixture over and stir to blend.

title: spinach sandwiches
directions: Mix spinach with mayonnaise and cream cheese (creamed together), eggs, green onions, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco, lemon juice and salt.
Let ingredient mixture stand for a while before making sandwiches, as it blends better. Butter one side of each of two slices of bread, then spread with filling.

title: doughnuts (best baked)
directions: Fill muffin pans 3/4 full after they have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
While still warm, dip in melted 4 tablespoons butter and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, drain and add spaghetti sauce.
Partially cook noodles and drain.
Grease lasagna pan with butter.
Cover bottom with noodles.
Cover with sauce and then cover with cheeses.
Continue layering in this way ending with cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: country biscuits
directions: Cut firm butter into 1/4-inch pieces.
Toss baking mix and butter pieces with fork until coated.
Add milk; stir just until milk is absorbed.
(Do not overstir.)
Turn dough onto cloth covered board, dusted with baking mix.
Roll to coat.
Fold and knead dough 5 times.
Pat lightly to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with floured 3-inch cutter.
Bake about 9 minutes, then brush melted butter.
Makes 8 biscuits.

title: good meal
directions: Soak bread in milk.
Crumble in mustard and ketchup.
Mix remaining ingredients and shape into a loaf in 8-inch square pan and bake at 375° until done.
You can also put carrots around the outside.

title: double-good blueberry pie
directions: In saucepan, combine 3/4 cup sugar, cornstarch, salt and water.
Add 2 cups blueberries and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and is thickened and clear. Remove from heat.
Add butter and lemon juice.
Cool.
Mix remaining 2 cups berries to cooled mixture.
Put into baked pie shell or graham shell.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: taco hot sauce
directions: Combine tomato paste and water in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and simmer 1/2 hour to keep sauce a thin consistency.
Add water during simmering.
Cool and serve with tacos.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time. Beating well. Add cake flour to cream mixture stirring until combined. Stir in vanilla extract. Pour batter into a well greased 10 inch tube pan. Bake 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes. Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: steamed cabbage
directions: Put cabbage in skillet	with
butter, hot water and hot pepper.
Cook over medium heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt and serve.

title: crusty cheese 'n chicken casserole
directions: Prepare fryer and cook in water and salt until tender.
Remove fryer from broth and debone.
Spread chicken in an 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Saute onion, celery and carrots in butter in heavy saucepan.
Add soup, cheese, milk and chicken broth.
Cook until cheese melts.
Add peas.
Pour cheese mixture over chicken and cover with crescent rolls.
(Unroll crescent rolls and place on top.) Brush top with 2 tablespoons evaporated milk.
Bake 30 minutes or until brown at 325°.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Boil broccoli and cauliflower until real soft.
Take soups and sour cream and mix up real well.
Lay broccoli and cauliflower in shallow casserole dish.
Cover with soup mixture and then put grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate kahlua cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine cookie crumbs with melted batter; pat gently onto bottom and sides of an 8 or 9-inch pan. In a large bowl, beat cream cheese with sugar and beat until well-blended.
Stir in 1/2 cup Kahlua, coffee and vanilla.
Spoon into crust and bake for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Chill 6 to 8 hours. Combine whipped cream with sugar and 1 tablespoon Kahlua.
Spread on filling and garnish with shaved or grated chocolate.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
In a large bowl with fork, mix first 8 ingredients.
In medium bowl with fork, beat eggs, pumpkin and salad oil until blended.
Stir pumpkin mixture into flour mixture, just until flour is moistened.
Gently stir in raisins and walnuts.
Spoon batter evenly into loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool bread on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: pepper sauce for pasta
directions: Heat 1/2 cup oil.
Add spices (except celery seed) and 2 cloves of garlic.
Cook briefly.
Add all the vegetables except tomatoes and stir to coat with oil and saute.
Add tomatoes.
Heat 5 minutes.
Add celery seed.
At this point, the sauce can be mixed with cooked Penne for pasta with vegetables.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl (except oil).
Heat oil in frying pan until hot.
Drop batter in hot oil.
Brown lightly on both sides.
Serve with applesauce.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart baking dish (shallow).
Combine corn, eggs and onion in large bowl.
Combine flour, salt, pepper, sugar and nutmeg.
Stir into corn mixture. Add butter, cream and pimientos.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Set in pan and pour hot water to 1-inch depth around dish. Bake, uncovered, 1 hour or until pudding is firm.
Cut into squares.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mammaw's blue ribbon winning pound cake
directions: *If flour is self-rising, omit the baking powder.

title: hard candy
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in a large, heavy saucepan.
Stir over high heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil, without stirring, until temperature reaches 310° or until drops of syrup form hard brittle threads in cold water.
Remove from heat.
After boiling has ceased, stir in flavoring and coloring.
Pour onto 30 inches of heavy-duty foil covered with powdered sugar.
Cool.
Break into pieces.
Store in airtight containers.
Makes in excess of 2 pounds.

title: *sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork in Crisco.
Add apples and bouillon.
Cook slowly, until tender.
Blend cornstarch into vinegar.
Add to pork mixture, along with soy sauce, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add peppers and cook for about 8 to 10 minutes longer; peppers should be crisp.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: buckeyes
directions: Combine peanut butter, sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Knead dough.
Roll into balls and refrigerate until firm (put toothpick in each ball before refrigerating).
Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip 3/4 of ball in chocolate.

title: coconut philly fudge balls
directions: Gradually mix sugar, cream cheese, vanilla and salt until well blended.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in shredded coconut. Chill 2 hours and serve.
Keep in refrigerator when not serving.

title: mincemeat pie
directions: Simmer all of the ingredients for 2 hours or until thick enough for wooden spoon to stand in.
Stir in the 1 cup of crab jelly (optional).
Let cool.
If you like brandy, add 1 cup.
Put mincemeat into storage container (preferably glass jars).
Half of recipe makes about 1 quart.

title: plum bread
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl and mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 large or 2 small loaves.
While still hot, poke holes in bread with a toothpick and pour glaze slowly over bread.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Mix mashed bananas in juice; let stand at least 5 minutes.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
When gelatin is cool, add strawberries, pineapple and banana mixture. Blend well.
Spread 1/2 in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill.
Whip together cream cheese and sour cream; spread over chilled mixture. Top with remaining gelatin-fruit mixture.
Chill.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: cream cheese crescents
directions: Spread 1 can crescent rolls in a 13 x 9-inch pan, sealing seams (using warm fingers). Beat cheese, egg yolk and sugar. Spread over crust.
Spread second can of crescent rolls on top (like a crust). Brush with egg whites and sprinkle with sugar. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Cut into squares or triangles.

title: recipe for happiness by virginia and duck
directions: Keep your heart free from hate, your mind from worry, live simply, expect little, give much.
Fill your life with love; scatter sunshine.
Think of others, forget yourself.
When you are depressed, fix or do something for someone.
Do for others what you would like for someone to do for you.
Count what you have not what you don't.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars in large mixing bowl.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt. Blend into creamed mixture.
Chill.
Shape dough into 3/4-inch diameter balls.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 1/4 teaspoons cinnamon.
Bake in 325° oven for 8 to 12 minutes until when pressed gently with a finger in the center, they don't indent.
Allow to cool slightly before removing from pan.
Yield: Approximately 3 dozen.

title: tutti frutti salad
directions: Drain juices from all fruit.
Chop peaches, pears and bananas in small pieces.
Put fruits in large container and mix with the vanilla pudding and then mix Cool Whip into the fruit.
Lite fruit can be used instead of regular fruit for diabetics.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix. Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Roll out onto floured surface.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Cool and ice.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix ingredients together in 2-quart casserole.
Cover with pie crust.
Turn edges under.
Cut slits in crust and flute edges. Bake about 30 minutes at 375°.
Makes 6 slices.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion; drain.
Put Velveeta in pan. Add chili powder and Ro-Tel tomatoes (mashed up).
Add beef; stir continuously until melted.
Use Mexican chips and dip.
Best when completely melted and warm.

title: golden glow salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add pineapple juice, vinegar, salt and chill.
When slightly thick, add other ingredients.

title: lobster sauce(chinese recipe)
directions: Brown hamburger, drain and chop up fine.
Add beaten egg.
Mix well.
Add garlic powder and sugar.
Stop there.
Separately add beef bouillon and water.
Then add cornstarch, soy sauce and Gravy Master. Pour into meat mixture and simmer 10 minutes, uncovered. Serve over Chinese noodles or rice.
Then sit and enjoy!

title: sausage-rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Pour off grease.
Add bell pepper, celery, onion and garlic.
Simmer a few minutes, then add uncooked rice and soups.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: chocolate oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats and let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Add sugar, eggs and margarine.
Mix very well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven 35 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients and stir; then add fruit cocktail.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost while warm.

title: oven potatoes
directions: In large bowl, toss potatoes and onions with seasonings to coat well.
Pour mixture into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Drizzle with oil.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake in 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: curry chicken casserole
directions: Cut broccoli in spears.
Cook until tender.
Lay in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry powder. Place chicken breasts over broccoli; pour soup mixture over chicken and top with cheese.
Saute croutons with butter; sprinkle over top.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Combine all the ingredients and chill for several hours before serving.

title: fat man's delight
directions: Melt oleo in 8 x 11-inch pan.
Mix flour and pecans.
Press down in bottom to form crust.
Cook at 400° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Add pineapple and blueberry pie filling. Pour in 9 x 13 pan.

title: party wheel of brie
directions: Place cheese on 8-inch plate. Cut rind from top of cheese carefully; score top of cheese into 6 wedges.
Press 2 teaspoons each of the raisins, walnuts and currants onto alternate wedges; repeat with remaining wedges.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on Medium (50%) 2 to 4 minutes or just until cheese is soft and warm.
Serve with crackers and fruit slices, if desired.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Add butter and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and milk.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. For frosting, use one can prepared frosting mix, mixed with one banana.

title: tammy's famous hot sauce
directions: Chop jalapenos and onion.
Mix all ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cool for 30 minutes.
Slightly blend small portions at a time in blender.
Enjoy.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a full rolling boil.
Boil hard 4 minutes.
Cool.
Can or freeze.
Excellent, served on pancakes.

title: spicy meatballs
directions: Sprinkle Accent, salt and onion over meat.
Mix bread crumbs and milk and add to meat.
Form into one-inch balls.
Roll in flour and brown in butter.
Drain off fat.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add cumin, chili powder, garlic powder, red pepper, salt, pepper and tomatoes.
Heat through. Cover bottom and sides of 13 x 9-inch baking dish with tortilla chips.
Pour beef mixture over tortillas.
Place a layer of tortillas over meat mixture and set aside.
Combine cottage cheese, Monterey Jack cheese and egg.
Pour over tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle large center row of Cheddar cheese diagonally from corner to opposite corner. On each side of cheese, lay lettuce, then tomatoes, olives and onions.
Makes a very decorative casserole.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle corn flake crumbs on top of casserole and top with butter.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cranberry pineapple salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in cranberry sauce, pineapple and juice, celery, lemon juice, oranges and nuts.
Pour into mold.
Chill until firm and unmold on a bed of lettuce.
Serve with mayonnaise.
Goes well with turkey.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix rice and eggs; add the rest of ingredients in order.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until very creamy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour three times.
Add soda to sour cream blending together.
Add flour and sour cream mixture alternately to the sugar mixture.
Blend well. Add flavorings.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then fold into mixture.
Pour into well-greased, lightly floured tube pan or loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: minnie ann's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skin on (do not overcook, just firm).
Skin potatoes and cut in chunks.
Boil eggs; peel and cut up smaller than potatoes.
Add sweet pickle relish with a little juice.
Add onion, chopped up.
Add pimentos, mayonnaise and mustard.
Stir up; add more mayonnaise if needed.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: azteca lasagna mexicana
directions: Heat oven to 375.
Brown meat and drain.
Stir in salsa, tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Simmer, stirring frequently for 5 minutes.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake cake first and cool completely.
Cream Philly cream cheese with pudding.
Add milk and mix until creamy.
Spread cream cheese mixture over cool cake.
Spread drained pineapple over that.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 9-inch pan, melt butter.
Over melted butter, spread graham cracker crumbs, then shredded coconut.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over the bottom layer, then sprinkle pecan pieces.
Pour can of Eagle Brand milk on the top and bake for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: kindness cookies
directions: Combine.
Drop spoonfuls on oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: our chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Serves 1 to 4.

title: different pecan pie
directions: Cook pie filling as directed; blend with corn syrup. Gradually add evaporated milk and slightly beaten egg, stirring to blend.
Add chopped pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 375° until top is firm and just begins to crack, about 40 minutes.
Cool at least 3 hours.
Garnish with prepared Dream Whip whipped topping and pecans.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix together food coloring and cocoa; set aside.
Cream and beat fluffy sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Add food coloring mixture. Add sifted flour, salt, buttermilk and vanilla.
Remove from mixer and add baking soda and vinegar.
Bake in 3 pans at 350° for 18 minutes.

title: pina colada pie
directions: Beat whipping cream until it begins to thicken.
Beat in 1 tablespoon powdered sugar and rum flavoring.
Beat until cream holds shape.
Fold in 2 tablespoons well drained pineapple. Spread over cake and top with toasted coconut.

title: riot of roll dough
directions: Measure water into large warm mixing bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, shortening or margarine, egg, salt and half the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in remaining flour until dough is easy to handle.
Put in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover loosely with aluminum foil.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
When dough rises, punch it down occasionally.
When fresh rolls are desired, remove dough from refrigerator.
Cut off amount needed and return remaining dough to refrigerator.
Dough may be kept 3 to 4 days.
Make into buns or cinnamon rolls and let rise until double in bulk.
Bake in a 350° oven.

title: fudge cookies
directions: Melt chocolate bits in top of double boiler.
Mix all ingredients well and drop onto greased pan and bake at 325° for fifteen minutes.
Yields 16 cookies.

title: my cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a hot greased pan and cook at 450 until done and brown.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: In large pan put sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine. Heat on top of stove until milk comes to boil.
Remove pan from stove and add last 3 ingredients.
Stir, then drop from a teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let cookies set until cool.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Put cream cheese in bowl.
Let set out until soft.
Add other ingredients except pecans.
Form into ball, roll in pecans and chill.

title: grandma cumming's german slaw
directions: Grate cabbage.
Add pineapple and miniature marshmallows.
Add mayonnaise with pineapple juice and salt.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
This can be used as a dessert served over pound cake and topped with whipped cream.

title: walnut pie
directions: Pour into a 9-inch pie plate, well-greased. Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 325° oven. Cool. Spread top with tart jelly and top with unsweetened whipped cream.

title: crabbies
directions: Stir all ingredients, except English muffins, until creamy. Spread on English muffins.
Broil until bubbly.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars, oil and margarine until fluffy.
Add eggs and flavorings.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to cream mixture; mix well.
Roll in small balls and place on greased cookie sheet. Press down with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: shrimp fondue
directions: Spread bread and cut in cubes.
Arrange alternate layers of cubes, shrimp and grated cheese.
Combine eggs and milk and pour over other ingredients.
Bake in pan of water for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: egg and broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl mix all ingredients.
Chill 2 to 3 hours. Serves 5 to 6.

title: round steak with rich gravy
directions: Sprinkle one side of meat with half the flour and pound in with mallet or edge of heavy saucer.
Turn meat and pound in remaining flour.
Cut into six or eight serving pieces.
Melt shortening in large skillet and brown meat slowly and thoroughly over medium heat, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Cover rhubarb
with
boiling water; let stand while you make the
crust.
Drain fruit; add eggs, cornstarch, lemon and sugar. Cook until	thick.	Pour
in
baked shell and top with meringue.

title: grandma scheffer's banana nut bread
directions: Prepare loaf pan with waxed paper, greasing the ends of the pan.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add sour milk (may sour with 1/2 to 1 teaspoon vinegar) and bananas.
Mix, then slowly add flour.
Last add the soda (it may be mixed in a little warm water).
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour (until toothpick comes out clean at 350°.
Cool on rack, then remove from pan.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix cooked noodles with all ingredients except salad dressing.
Once ingredients are mixed add desired amount of Italian dressing, to taste.
Amounts of any ingredient can be changed to suit personal taste.

title: german chocolate cake icing
directions: Cook all ingredients in a saucepan slowly until it thickens. Remove from stove and cool.
Spread on German Chocolate Layer Cake.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients until sugar dissolves.
Marinate overnight.
Drain 1 hour before serving.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, jello and cornstarch with boiling water and heat to a rolling boil; let cool. Cook pie crust and let cool.
Place sliced peaches into crust.
Pour mixture over peaches and place in refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours.
Top with Cool Whip and serve.

title: lucy's tuna casserole
directions: Mix everything together and put in baking dish.
Cook 30 minutes at 350° without a lid.

title: mock sour cream
directions: Blend in blender until smooth.
Use as you would sour cream.

title: cauliflower walnut casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower (do not overcook). Mix sour cream, cheese, flour, bouillon, and mustard. Spoon over cauliflower in shallow baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle on top. Bake 15-20 minutes at 400°. Delicious!

title: tenderizing marinade
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add rest of ingredients (pour liquids over, shake on seasonings).
This is a tenderizing marinade; bake meat, covered, slowly for a long time, depending on the quantity. Add water if needed.
Juice may be made into gravy by adding 1/2 cup water mixed with
1 tablespoon cornstarch and simmering.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Place by spoonfuls on a cookie sheet (greased) and bake at 325°.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook and drain frozen broccoli. Cook rice and add to cooked broccoli. Add onion, celery, soup and Cheez Whiz. Pour into casserole dish and bake 1 hour.

title: orange delight salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O with Cool Whip, mixing well.
Add cottage cheese. Add drained fruit. Cool in refrigerator. This keeps well for several days.

title: potato soup
directions: This is one of my family's favorite dishes.
It is very simple, but good.

title: chow-chow
directions: Slice tomatoes and peppers; add salt and let sit overnight. Drain, but do not wash.
Grind all these ingredients; put in a kettle with all other ingredients except sugar.
The juice should just cover the top.
Add the sugar to taste.
Simmer about 5 minutes after the mixture comes to a boil.
Seal in prepared sterile jars.
This was my mother's recipe.

title: lee's mexican hors d'oeuvre
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Spread refried beans on bottom.
Beat (with beater) the avocado, cream cheese, lemon juice and a little salt and pepper and spread on top of beans.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased pan.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: mexican corn
directions: Dice celery, onion, green pepper and pimentos and mix with corn.
Mix vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate for a few hours or overnight.
This salad is good to make the day ahead of serving.

title: slushie drink
directions: Fill blender 1/2 full of water.
Add orange juice, Tang and ice cubes.
Turn on to high speed until ice is crushed; stir several times, then serve.

title: rabbit and gravy
directions: Wash rabbit and pat dry.
Roll in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Fry in oil until brown.
Drain off oil.
Mix mushroom soup and can of water into small bowl.
Pour over rabbit in skillet. Cover; place in oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
You can also use chicken, pork chops or beef.

title: moravian molasses cookies
directions: Melt shortening and margarine until it bubbles and add to sugar.
Stir in molasses.
Dissolve soda in boiling water and add to mixture.
Sift in approximately 4 pounds flour.
Add spices along with flour.
The dough should be almost stiff enough to roll.
Cover; let set overnight.
Do not refrigerate.

title: welsh rarebit
directions: This mixture should not boil.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add mustard, salt and pepper.
Mix.
Add bread crumbs and stir over gentle heat.
Add egg yolk. Put in cheese and stir until melted. Mix in beer.
Spread on hot buttered toast.

title: spinach tortilla roll-ups
directions: Defrost spinach in advance; put in a colander and squeeze all water out.
Chop green onions, cilantro and parsley and then mix in bacon bits, mayonnaise, sour cream and dressing mix.
Tear spinach into pieces and add it; mix well together.
Lay out a flour tortilla and spread a layer of mixture evenly over the tortilla. Roll it up like a burrito, leaving ends open.
Cut into bite-size pieces before serving.
Makes 5 to 7 rolls, depending on thickness of spread.

title: tater tots casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until clear.
Mix Cheez Whiz and sour cream together well; add the sauteed onion
and pour over Tater Tots in baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, removing foil the last few minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix well and pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes in pan and then turn onto plate.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: broccoli and ham hot dish
directions: Bring to boil broccoli.
Drain.
Heat onion and margarine but don't brown.
Add remaining ingredients and broccoli and mix well. Put in greased casserole and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Good way to use leftover ham.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Chop onions and saute lightly.
Add grated cheese, finely chopped peppers and tomatoes, salt and sour cream.
Mix well; heat (do not boil).
Run tortillas through hot grease and drain well. Fill baking dish with layers of tortillas and mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Serves 6.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and almonds in a small casserole dish.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with almonds and cook an additional 10 minutes until brown on top.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: german chocolate delight
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Remove from oven.
While still hot, poke 24 holes in the cake with wooden spoon.
Let cool. Pour over cake the Eagle Brand milk and butterscotch fudge caramel topping.
Cool completely.
Top with Cool Whip and crushed Skor or Heath bars.
Keep refrigerated.

title: scratch and sniff
directions: Paint a thin coat of glue on desired areas.
Sprinkle with powder.
Let dry.
Odor will return when finished product is "scratched and sniffed."
Perfumes or extracts can be added scents.
Be careful!
A little goes a long way.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine
butter
and sugar; add egg and beat well.
Add flavoring
and dry ingredients.
Roll out dough and cut.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: raspberry shrub
directions: Cook packages of raspberries.
Rub through strainer with wooden spoon; cool.
Add lemonade.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale, chilled.

title: six-week muffins
directions: Mix together dry ingredients and then add oil, eggs and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Store rest of batter in a large bowl with lid.
Will keep in refrigerator for 6 weeks.

title: gourmet potato salad
directions: Dice potatoes. Add all ingredients. Adjust mayonnaise by preference. Top with boiled egg slices.

title: orange flank steak
directions: Preheat the broiler. Trim the fat from the meat.
Place meat on unheated rack of a broiler pan.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients except the cornbread mix.
Add the cornbread mix and stir thoroughly.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 400 degrees.
Serve hot.
May sprinkle some grated cheddar cheese on top when bread is done.

title: hot cross buns
directions: Prepare roll mix according to directions, adding the sugar, cinnamon and currants.
Let dough rise until double.
Roll and knead on floured board.
Let rise again.
Make into rolls.
Put on greased cookie sheets and cut cross in top of each with kitchen shears.
Brush with beaten egg white.
Let rise.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: white lasagna
directions: In a large saucepan, cook noodles, drain and set aside.
In a skillet, cook meats, celery, onion and garlic until meat is browned and vegetables tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in spices; add cream and cream cheese.
Cook and stir until melts.
Stir in wine.
Gradually add cheeses, stirring until melted; remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese and egg.
Layer noodles, meat, melted cheeses and cottage cheese mixture.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: solar sun dills
directions: You will also need a gallon jar.

title: strawberry cream dip
directions: Whisk ingredients in a small bowl.
Makes about 3/4 cup of dip.

title: rice and pintos casserole
directions: Cook hamburger meat.
Saute onion and butter.
Add together. Stir in pinto beans, rice and tomatoes.
Mix well and simmer. Spoon into a 11 x 14-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all together in electric mixer.
Pour into 3 well-greased and floured pans or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Put ingredients together in crock pot and simmer all day on low, about 5 hours.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package in large pot. Stir in cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Stir constantly until smoothed out and starts to bubble.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cover chicken pieces with cold water. Bring to simmer. Skim foam from top. Add carrots, onion stuck with cloves, bay leaf, parsley, thyme and celery (or 1/2 teaspoon thyme and 1 teaspoon dried parsley). Cover pot, leaving lid slightly ajar. Add salt to taste. Use in 4 days or freeze.

title: rice krispie cookies
directions: Drop from spoon.
