May use nuts instead of coconut.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms quickly under running water.
Remove stems and drain.
Bring a kettle of water, enough that will cover the mushrooms, to a boil.
Add the salt and lemon juice.
After water comes to a boil, take off heat and dump in mushrooms.
Let them remain for 5 minutes.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix crumbs, confectioners sugar, 1 cup of nuts and cocoa.
Add corn syrup and rum.
Mix well.
Shape in pinch balls.
Roll half the balls in confectioners sugar and the remainder in 1/2 cup nuts.

title: enchiladas - chicken or turkey
directions: Mix chicken, chilies, tomato, onion and garlic in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes, until hot.
Stack 4 of the tortillas on 10-inch plate.
Cover tightly and microwave on High 20 to 30 seconds or until hot.
Place about 1/3 cup chicken mixture down center of each tortilla; top each with about 1 tablespoon of the guacamole.
Roll tortillas around filling.
Arrange enchiladas, seam sides down, on plate.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of the cheese. Microwave, uncovered, on High 2 to 3 minutes or until enchiladas are hot and cheese is melted.
Repeat with remaining tortillas. Serve with taco sauce, if desired.

title: prize cupcakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add sugar, shortening and milk; beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat 2 more minutes.
Fill pans 1/3 to 1/2 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 30 cupcakes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix with hands.
Shape into ball. Wrap in Saran Wrap and store in refrigerator overnight to mix flavors.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Put rhubarb in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle sugar evenly over, then the package of jello.
Make cake:
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg.
Add flour and milk.
Spoon over cake and bake at 350° until done.

title: chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Combine sugar and shortening in large mixing bowl; mix until creamed together.
Next, add applesauce and mix with creamed mixture.
Combine cocoa, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Next mix in flour a little at a time, then add raisins.
Now add vinegar and mix well into mixture.
Grease and flour large iron skillet (9 x 13-inch pan) and pour batter in.
Preheat oven to 250° to 300°. Bake slowly for 1 hour or until done.
Do not overbake.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix well shortening, sugar, egg and flavorings.
Mix flour and salt; stir in.
Divide dough in half. Blend red food coloring into one half.
Roll 1 teaspoon each colored dough on a lightly floured board into a strip about 4-inches long.
Place strips, side by side; press lightly together and twist like a rope.
Curve top down the handle of cane.
Bake 9 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove while still warm and sprinkle with 1/2 cup crushed peppermint candy.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in the bottom of a greased 8-inch pan.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over apples.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box.
Rinse and set aside.
Mix all other ingredients and mix with macaroni.
Chill for 4 hours. Makes a lot.

title: apricot salad
directions: Drain apricots and mandarin oranges (and pineapple).
Reserve juices.
Chop apricots.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water; add 1 cup reserved juice with apricots, oranges and marshmallows.
Place in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Blend sugar, flour, egg, butter and remaining 1 cup juice.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Chill.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread over firm gelatin.
Chill and serve.
Makes 15 servings.

title: mahogany pound cake
directions: Sift together flour and cocoa.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each. Add.
Stir in vanilla.
Combine baking soda with sour cream.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with dry ingredients.
In separate bowl, beat 6 egg whites until stiff.
Fold into greased tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: squash muffins
directions: You can divide the mixture and put 1 teaspoon lemon and 1 teaspoon of coconut flavoring.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except Ritz crackers.
Put in casserole dish. Top with Ritz crackers. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix well and pour over meat balls.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Prepare pie crust.
Combine ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour filling into pie crust.
Top with second crust. Seal and crimp edges.
Slit top of crust to vent.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil the macaroni as directed on the package; drain and rinse with cold water.
Add the mayo and the contents of envelope included in the macaroni and cheese mix.
Toss well.
Fold in remaining ingredients and chill.
Serve from a large salad bowl lined with lettuce leaves; garnish with ripe olives.

title: pecan log
directions: Mix together sugar and marshmallow cream and roll into logs. Wrap in Handi-Wrap and freeze.

title: "mom's" chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut up hen.
Saute.
Pour off excess fat.
Cover with water; cook until tender.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder and eggs.
Mix in approximately 1 cup of chicken broth from cooked chicken.
Roll out dough; cut in 1 1/2-inch strips.
Bring chicken broth to boil and drop dumplings into boiling chicken broth.
Do this hurriedly, and dumplings will be done almost immediately.
Shake pepper over finished product.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Combine sugar, salt, butter and milk.
Boil for 6 minutes. Remove from heat and add chocolate chips, German chocolate, marshmallow cream and nuts.
Beat until all chocolate is melted. Pour into a buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Let stand a few hours before cutting.
Store in a tin box with wax paper between layers.

title: patio salad
directions: Cook frozen vegetables 2 minutes in water and salt.
Add rice; stir to moisten all rice.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes, then stir in mayonnaise, pickles and onion.
Add meat and cheese, mixing lightly.
Serve on crisp greens with tomato wedges.

title: chicken and broccoli alfredo
directions: Prepare fettucini according to directions.
Add broccoli the last 4 minutes of cooking time; drain.
In skillet over medium heat, heat butter.
Add chicken and cook until browned, stirring often.
Add soup, milk, cheese, peppers and fettuccini mixture and cook through, stirring often.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: pepper relish
directions: Remove seeds from peppers, grind with onions.
Pour boiling water over mixture.
Let stand 4 minutes.
Drain.
Make solution of 1/2 pint vinegar and 1 pint water.
Pour over mixture and bring to a boil.
Let stand for 10 minutes and drain again.
Add 1 pint vinegar, salt, sugar and mustard seed.
Boil for 5 minutes. Bottle and seal.
makes 4 to 4
1/2 pints.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chili con queso dip(microwave recipe)
directions: Place cheese cubes in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spoon chili over cheese until it is shielded.
Microwave on Medium-high (7) for 10 to 11 minutes.
Stir and serve with tortilla chips or a platter of raw vegetables.

title: olive cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese and olives in a bowl with onion and Tabasco sauce.
Mix well. Set mix in refrigerator for about 15 minutes to harden slightly for handling. Shape mixture into ball. Roll in chopped parsley or chopped nuts to coat well.
Return to refrigerator to chill until serving time.
Serve with assorted crackers or chips.

title: grilled garlic pepper cowboy steak
directions: In a small bowl, combine all of the ingredients except the rib-eyes. Stir until a paste forms. Rub the paste into the steaks; cover and refrigerate for 1 hour. Remove from the refrigerator and grill to desired doneness over a hot fire. Yield: 2 servings.

title: percolator wassail
directions: Place ingredients into the basket of percolator.
Perk and enjoy.

title: c&h sugar's hawaiian pork casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, brown the cubed pork in the oil and sprinkle with soy sauce.
Drain the pineapple (save syrup) and add to the meat mixture.
Mix syrup and vinegar and heat.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and water and add to hot liquid, cooking until clear and thickened.
Pour over meat mixture.
Cover and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cook green pepper and onion in the butter (add shredded carrots for color).
Cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add to casserole and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour, milk and beaten egg yolks. Add margarine. Cook until thick. Pour over vanilla wafers and sliced bananas. Beat egg whites until stiff. Put on top.
Brown lightly in oven.

title: salmon pate
directions: Mince parsley and onion.
Mix remaining ingredients.
(A food processor works well.)
Mix until smooth paste.
Adjust spices. Refrigerate overnight.
Makes 2 cups.
Will keep refrigerated 7 to 10 days.

title: quick and easy brownies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together; cream butter and sugar. Add well-beaten eggs.
Mash bananas with fork and add sour milk; add alternately with the flour to the butter mixture.
When well blended, pour in bread pan (buttered), 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inches.
Bake in preheated oven (350°) for about 1 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix all ingredient together for 10 minutes.
Pour into a greased bundt pan and bake for 1 hour at 300 degrees.

title: creamy dijon pasta with vegetables
directions: In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook pasta until just tender, 10 to 12 minutes. Drain in a colander.
Put cream cheese and milk in a pot.
Cook over medium, stirring constantly, until cream cheese is melted and well blended with milk. Add pasta and toss to coat. Reduce heat to medium-low.
Stir in mustard, meat, vegetables, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are very hot and barely tender (approximately 5 to 7 minutes).
Top with a sprinkling of grated Parmesan cheese. Serves 4 to 6.

title: icing for angel food cake
directions: Mix well.
Ice cake, then top with can of pie filling.

title: sunday night chicken
directions: Combine rice, celery, onions, margarine, parsley and seasonings.
Mix lightly.
Spoon mixture in greased 3-quart shallow baking dish.
Top with chicken breasts. Combine soup, mayonnaise and milk.
Mix until blended.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Serves 6.

title: baked artichoke dip
directions: Run artichoke hearts through food processor.
Combine with all other ingredients, except 2 tablespoons of the cheese and the bread crumbs.
Put mixture in a greased 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake in a preheated oven (375°) for 20 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and bake in 8 x 11-inch casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add flavoring.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Spoon batter into greased 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: kathy's macaroni salad
directions: Combine ingredients together and chill.

title: grandma's banana bread
directions: Sift together 2 cups flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, and nutmeg.
Cream together shortening and sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and sugar mixture alternately to bananas, mixing just until blended.
Combine pecans and 1 teaspoon flour; stir into batter.
Pour into greased 9-inch tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 - 50 minutes, or until bread tests done.
Cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes, then remove from pan and place on rack.
Makes one loaf.

title: autumn fruit salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar and flour.
Stir in water; bring to a boil.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Remove from the heat; stir in butter and vanilla.
Cool to room temperature.

title: tuna fish croquettes
directions: Saute onion in butter; do not brown, only soften.
Make a roux from butter and flour.
Pour over soup.
Add onion, tuna and all the rest of ingredients.
Add crackers last and only enough to make mixture easy to handle.
Put mixture in refrigerator and chill it.
Form into small croquettes and roll in rest of cracker crumbs, crushing more if needed.
Fry in deep fat at 425°
for 3 to 4 minutes.
This may be made up and then frozen if desired.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in 2 quarts of salted water until tender. Brown the meat, onions and green pepper.
Stir in the water, tomato paste and sugar.
Stir well and simmer slowly for 30 minutes.
Drain spaghetti and put into a deep casserole.
Pour sauce over all well and sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: oriental green beans
directions: Steam beans (7 minutes) until tender-crisp.

title: easy pour pizza(who doesn't like pizza?  here's a fun recipe to try.)
directions: When finished cooking, drain grease and drop on top of liquid pizza.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until pizza is done.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Peel sweet potatoes and cut in chunks.
Combine all ingredients, except almonds, in blender or food processor. Process until sweet potato is grated.
Pour into a large buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds.
Dust with cinnamon sugar, if you wish.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Place in refrigerator until chilled.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: crockpot corn
directions: Put corn, cream cheese, margarine and peppers in crock pot. Mix flour and milk.
Add to corn mixture.
Cook on high setting for 2 hours. Stir occasionally.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, baking powder, vanilla and milk. Add alternately with milk to first 4 ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add egg and milk to dry ingredients.
Drop a teaspoon of batter for each hush puppy into hot deep fat.
Cook a few at a time until golden brown.

title: angel food cake and glazes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix powdered sugar and flour.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in 3-quart bowl on medium speed until foamy.
Beat in granulated sugar on high speed, 1 tablespoon at a time, adding vanilla, almond extract and salt with the last addition of sugar.
Continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Do not underbeat.
Sprinkle sugar-flour mixture, 1/4 cup at a time, over meringue, folding in just until sugar-flour mixture disappears.
Spread batter in ungreased pan.
Cut gently through batter with metal spatula.
Bake until cracks feel dry and top springs back when touched lightly, 30 to 35 minutes.
Invert pan on heatproof funnel; let stand until cake is cold.
Remove from pan.
Spread top of cake with vanilla glaze, if desired.
Makes 8 servings (130 calories per serving).

title: green fluff salad
directions: Sprinkle Jell-O over cottage cheese; mix well.
Add Cool Whip and pineapple; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 3/4 cup Milnot together.
Spread half in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt together caramels and 1/4 cup Milnot, stirring constantly.
Pour on top of baked cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans on top. Pour the other half of the batter on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Cool 20 minutes, then cut.
Best when warm.

title: colcannon(irish)
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, cook potatoes in boiling salted water about 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Transfer potatoes to a mixer bowl and mash.
Add the milk, salt and pepper.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer until fluffy.

title: ricotta pie(torta di ricotta)
directions: Mix together with fork flour and salt.
Add shortening, egg and water.
Blend well and knead slightly.
Set aside.

title: low fat italian sauce(15 minute pasta sauce)
directions: Wash porcini mushrooms in water; strain and save the water. Heat olive oil in pot and add porcini mushrooms.
Add herbs and chopped tomatoes.
Add liquid from Porcini mushrooms and fresh mushrooms.
Saute 15 minutes with lid off.

title: salted nut roll bars
directions: Mix until crumbly and press into 9 x 13-inch cake pan, then bake at 350° for 13 to 18 minutes or until golden brown; take out and sprinkle about 3 cups miniature marshmallows over top and put back in oven for 1 to 2 minutes, until marshmallows puff up.
Do not overbake.
Spread topping over top.
Cool and cut into bars. Store in covered container.

title: orange chocolate fudge
directions: In microwave-safe bowl, stir the first 4 ingredients until blended (mixture will be dry and crumbling).
Slice stick of butter into 6 pieces; arrange evenly on top of mixture. Microwave, uncovered, on High until butter is partially melted (about 2 minutes).
Stir until smooth.
Pour into wax paper lined pan.

title: meaghan's apple snicker salad
directions: Peel, core and cube apples.
Chop Snickers into small pieces (remember, the less Snickers you use, the healthier the salad). Combine vanilla pudding with milk and mix until smooth.
This should be done in a large bowl.
Fold whipped topping into pudding mixture.
Add Snickers and apples and stir until Snickers and apples are coated.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: butternut squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, eggs, sugar, butter or margarine, milk, ginger and coconut flavoring, pour into a lightly greased 8 inch square baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.
While baking, combine corn flake crumbs, brown sugar, pecans and margarine in a bowl.
Sprinkle casserole with crunchy cereal topping and bake 10 additional minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix and freeze.
Chunk up, then pour 1 to 2 liters of ginger ale over it.
Serve.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla and flour. Blend oatmeal until very fine (or leave as is).
Add salt, baking powder and baking soda to oatmeal.
Add to mixture.
Fold in chocolate chips, Hershey bar and pecans.
Roll in balls.
Place 2 inches apart.
Cook 6 to 7 minutes at 375°.
Cookies will not look completely done.
Do not overcook.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour half of batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes.
While cake is baking, melt caramels with milk and butter in microwave oven or double boiler, stirring until smooth. Pour caramel mixture over partially baked cake.
Spread evenly. Sprinkle chocolate chips and 1/2 cup of pecans over caramel mixture.
Pour remaining cake batter over top, spreading evenly. Sprinkle with remaining pecans.
Bake 40 minutes or until center is set.
Cool before slicing.

title: mashed potatoes royale
directions: Cook and mash potatoes with a little less milk than usual. Add regular butter, salt and pepper.
Stir in sour cream, Parmesan cheese and garlic salt to taste (may add 1 cup grated Cheddar).
Pour into buttered 11 x 7-inch casserole.
Cover and refrigerate all day or overnight.
Uncover.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
May be frozen before baking. Longer standing improves flavor.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all together and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Press and roll into a ball.

title: jiffy hamburger buns
directions: Stir together 2 cups flour and dry yeast. Heat milk, water, oil, sugar and salt to very warm (120° to 130°). Add liquid all at once to flour and yeast mixture. Beat until smooth, about 3 minutes on medium speed of electric mixer. Add enough additional flour to make soft dough. Mix well. Mixing may be done either by hand or mixer. Let rest 10 minutes. Roll out on well floured surface to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with 3-inch round cutter or coffee can. Place on greased baking sheets. Let raise in warm place (80° to 85°) 30 minutes. Bake in preheated 425° oven 12 to 15 minutes until lightly browned. Makes 12 to 15 buns.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring applesauce to a boil.
Stir in both packages of jello and crushed pineapple.
Cool.
Pour in Fresca.
Stir and chill.

title: no cholesterol pumpkin pie
directions: Blend tofu in a food processor or blender until creamy smooth. Add honey, pumpkin, egg whites and spices; blend well.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked deep dish pie shell.
Bake approximately 1 hour in a preheated 400° oven or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out almost clean.
Cool and serve.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring water, cocoa and oleo to a boil.
Set aside to cool. Add sugar, flour, salt, buttermilk with soda, eggs and vanilla, mixing in order.
Bake in a brownie pan sprayed with Pam at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: nut cake
directions: Beat sugar and butter together.
Add eggs, salt and vanilla. Then add flour, baking powder and milk.
Mix; add nuts.
Put in two 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook until smooth and bubbly.
Heat to boil and continue boiling for 1 minute.
Stir in sherry, spaghetti, chicken and mushrooms.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Great for leftover turkey or chicken.

title: muffins (plain)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease muffin pan, mixing ingredients very well.
Bake 17 to 20 minutes for regular size or until a toothpick is inserted and comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes, then remove muffins from pan and cool completely on wire rack.

title: pizza
directions: First you make the crust.
Then you put on the sauce.
Put on the cheese.
Put on all the stuff.
Put it in the oven.
Then you take it out.
Then they serve it to you.
Then you eat it.

title: brownies
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Add cooking oil and cocoa.
Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add eggs to mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well and pour in an 8-inch greased pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Mix together sugar, salad oil and vinegar.
Pour over kraut mixture.
Toss and chill.

title: grandmother's favorite dressing
directions: In large bowl combine bread crumbs, cornbread, biscuits, onion, celery, parsley, sage, salt and pepper.
Toss well.
Add broth, butter and eggs.
Mix well but toss lightly.
Mixture should be extra moist just this side of soupy.

title: wonderful pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Alternate flour with whipping cream, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Use 10-inch baking pan that has been well-greased and dusted with flour.

title: boot's vegetable soup
directions: Cook 30 minutes after you mix.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook margarine and water, stirring constantly.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt.
Cook until thick and pour over potatoes and onion.
Add bacon pieces; stir.
Serve immediately.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut zucchini in half lengthwise and scoop out pulp, leaving about 1/4-inch thick shell.
Chop pulp and set aside.
Reserve shells.

title: crab smitty
directions: Pick through crabmeat and remove any pieces of cartilage. Melt butter in heavy skillet and add lemon juice, salt, pepper, onion juice, hot sauce and thyme.
Quickly add crabmeat and stir lightly.
Saute, stirring a few times with a wooden spoon just until crab is cooked through, about 2 minutes.
Lower heat.
Cover crabmeat with ham slices.
Cover skillet and let simmer 2 or 3 minutes.
Serve as is on toast.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain all canned vegetables and place in a large bowl.
In a saucepan, mix sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Heat mixture until sugar dissolves.
Let cool.
Add vinegar mixture to vegetables.
Toss.

title: sour cream apple squares
directions: Combine flour, sugars and cinnamon; cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in walnuts.
Reserve 2 cups crumb mixture; press remaining mixture onto bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine sour cream, egg and vanilla; spread over crust.
Top with apples; sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Chill.
Makes 12 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly, spoon off excess fat.
Add next 6 ingredients to meat.
Simmer, uncovered, until thick, about 45 minutes to an hour, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in boiling water until tender.
Drain and rinse in cold water.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add yolks, one at a time; beat well after each. Blend in vanilla and chocolate.

title: strawberry yogurt treat
directions: Wash strawberries. Cut up, measure 1/2 cup.
Pour strawberries into bowl.
Add the vanilla yogurt.
Stir with a spoon.
Spoon into bowl and enjoy!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease 8 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken in pan and layer with cheese.
Mix soups and milk; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle dressing on top.
Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes with jackets on. Cut bacon in small pieces. Fry. Remove bacon. Saute onions in fat. Stir in flour and salt. Add sugar, vinegar and water. Bring to a boil. Add bacon pieces and pour over the cut and cooled potatoes. Make ahead and reheat for better flavor.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together and beat sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir together and add apples and nuts.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve on buttered bread or use as a dip.

title: rosy cinnamon apples
directions: Combine candies and water in a saucepan, stirring over heat until dissolved.
Place apples in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Pour melted candy over apples.
Cover and cook on top of stove until apples are tender.

title: better than anything spice cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as usual, using the pineapple juice as part of the liquid.
Bake
in
sheet
pan
or
pound
cake pan according to directions on cake mix box.

title: chicken tostadas
directions: Heat tostada shells according to package directions.
In medium skillet, quickly cook chicken strips and onion in butter until chicken is browned.
Add salsa and seasoning mix, reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
To assemble, spread 1 heaping tablespoonful refried beans on each shell; spoon 1/3 cup chicken mixture next and top with lettuce, tomato and cheese.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute onions in butter until transparent.
Add clam juice from bottle and from cans of clams.
Add potatoes and cook until potatoes are tender.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Reheat and serve.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: stuffed pears
directions: Drain pears.
Dry centers with paper towel.
Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix with syrup until smooth with no lumps. Fill pears; garnish with drained cherries pushed into center of cream mixture.
Chill until dinner.
Can be made ahead.

title: frank's favorite lasagna
directions: Brown the ground chuck, sausage, onion and garlic in the pan; drain grease. In large pan (Dutch oven type), mix sugar, tomato paste, pear tomatoes and meat mixture. Simmer over low heat for 1 hour. Cook noodles. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, alternate sauce, cheese, noodles, sauce, cheese and noodles until ingredients are totally used. Bake in oven at 325° until brown and bubbly.

title: sour cream drop cookie cakes
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together
(if dough is too soft, then cover
and	refrigerate).
Heat
oven
Drop by level teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake
like a cake (until almost no indentation remains when touched,
about
minutes).
Remove
immediately from cookie sheet.
Cool and glaze.
Makes 4 1/2 to 5 dozen.

title: tasty omelet
directions: Mix together 5 eggs, milk, salt, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce and melted oleo.
Alternate layers of bread and cheese.
Put chopped ham on top of each layer of bread.
Pour milk and egg mixture over all; cover with foil and refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 325° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: peanut butter cup candy
directions: Cream the margarine and peanut butter.
Add sugar until the consistency to form into balls.
Add vanilla.
Mix thoroughly using hands.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in small double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate using toothpick.
Place on waxed paper to cool.

title: cool lime pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix, gelatin, sugar and water in saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Add juice.
Pour into bowl; cover with plastic wrap and chill until cold and slightly thickened.
Spoon into crust. Freeze 1 hour or chill in refrigerator 3 hours before serving. Garnish with Cool Whip if desired.

title: curried chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into large pieces.
Place in shallow, buttered baking dish.
Cover with broccoli.
Mix soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry powder; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with dressing and pour butter over top.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes.

title: cranberry gelatin salad
directions: Add lemon juice and cranberry sauce while gelatin is tepid. When cool, blend in other ingredients.
Serves 6 to 8. Attractively served in individual molds on lettuce.

title: marinated oriental salad
directions: Combine these ingredients in a large bowl.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fold in the Cool Whip.
Makes two 8-inch pies.
Pour into two 8-inch graham cracker crusts. Chill 1 hour or longer.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, stirring well.
Pour oil to depth of 1/8-inch into a large, heavy skillet.
Drop potato mixture by 6 heaping tablespoonfuls into hot oil; press into 3-inch rounds with the back of a fork.
Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Drain well on paper towels.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: sweet 'n sour ham
directions: Drain pineapple; keep juice.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 cup.
Stir onion and oleo until tender.
Stir in ham, pepper, pineapple and juice.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce and simmer 5 minutes.
Mix water and cornstarch.
Stir in meat mixture.
Heat to boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Serve over rice.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Press this dough mixture into greased and floured cake pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients until creamy and smooth.
Pour on top of dough and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Combine rice, dry onion mix, celery soup and water; place in greased casserole dish.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Prepare stuffing as directed on box.
Cook spinach and drain. Mix all ingredients together and make into balls.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: weight watchers delight
directions: Slice cake.
Make pudding as directed.
Put layers of cake first, then layer of pudding, layer of pineapple and layer of fruit cocktail.
Repeat process.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: date pinwheels
directions: Cream butter; add sugars, vanilla and egg.
Beat until light. Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Chill until firm enough to roll.
Half dough.
Roll each half on floured wax paper into a 12 x 9-inch rectangle.
Spread with filling; roll up tightly from end.
Wrap in paper; chill overnight.
Slice 1/8-inch thick.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheets in 375° oven for about 10 minutes.

title: amazing pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Pour into pie shells. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 45 minutes or until the pies are done.
After pies are cool, top with whipped cream.
This recipe makes 2 pies.

title: great baked potato soup
directions: Wash potatoes and
prick with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Let cool.
Cut in half lengthwise and scoop out pulp.
Melt butter in large heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook mixture 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat stirring constantly until mixture is bubbly and slightly thickened.

title: puffs
directions: Bring water, butter and salt to a boil.
Add flour; stir until it forms a ball, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on a well-greased cookie sheet (use Pam).
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
(You can make these smaller by using a smaller amount; check at 20 minutes.)
Cool and stuff.
One recipe makes about 40. Can be frozen.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Makes 1-inch balls. Flatten with fingers on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and dice.
Boil potatoes until tender.
Do not overcook potatoes.
Drain potatoes.
Add medium onion, green pepper and eggs.
Stir in mustard and sweet pickles.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add celery seed to taste.
Stir in Duke's mayonnaise enough to mix potato salad well.

title: overnight salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: Cook bacon in a large Dutch oven until crisp; remove bacon, reserving 1 tablespoon drippings in Dutch oven.
Crumble bacon and set aside.

title: sandoval sauce(hot relish)
directions: Blend all ingredients together in blender on high speed for 15 to 30 seconds.

title: fresh fruits ala l'orange
directions: Mix fruits together.
Add sugar and lemon juice and rind for the extra tang.
Also add fresh orange juice and mix well.
The juices keep the bananas from turning brown and gives it a nice flavor.
This makes for a healthy snack or dessert and will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and add Jiffy mix.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: quick and easy casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion (don't salt).
Mix all ingredients and put in a large casserole dish and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese; sift flour, pepper and salt into bowl.
Cut butter into small pieces and add.
Blend until coarse crumbs.
Add cheese and blend until dough hangs together.
Roll out 1/4 of dough at a time 1/4 inch thick.
Cut into strips.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375° or until straws are lightly browned.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix the graham cracker crumbs and melted oleo.
Pat into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Next, combine 2 sticks of softened oleo (not melted), box of powdered sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix with electric mixer for approximately 2 minutes until smooth and creamy.
Spread over crust. Slice bananas and layer over the filling. Drain the pineapple cans and spread over top of bananas. Slice strawberries and layer on top. Top it all off with the Cool Whip.
Chill for at least 4 hours.

title: applebutter
directions: Cook until well blended, about 15 minutes.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars.
Process 10 to 15 minutes.

title: orange tapioca jello salad
directions: Put Jell-O and pudding in hot water. Cook until thick. Cool. Add oranges and Cool Whip. Stir and refrigerate until you serve.

title: squash fritters
directions: Melt butter/margarine.
Add beaten eggs, flour and sugar. Stir to mix.
Add onion and squash.
Drop by spoonful onto greased griddle (350°) until brown.

title: simple meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stir in enough rolled oats (about 1 1/4 cups) to form the mixture into a loaf.
Place in pan that has been sprayed with nonstick coating.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: clams casino
directions: Open quahogs and separate the meat from the shell.
Put a dash of Tabasco on each quahog.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Put a teaspoon of bread crumbs on each quahog.
Place a small piece of bacon on top of each quahog.
Broil quahog in half shell for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix
hot
water,
cup
sugar,
salt and shortening together.
Cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Add
teaspoon
sugar.
Mix well and stir into first mixture.
Add
beaten
eggs.
Stir in 4 cups flour; beat thoroughly.
Stir
in 4 more cups flour and mix thoroughly.
It is not necessary
to knead.
Place in greased bowl.
Brush top of dough with	melted shortening and cover bowl with a damp cloth and then
with aluminum foil or a lid so that a crust will not form on top.
Put	in
refrigerator
and use as needed.
This also makes good
cinnamon
rolls.
When ready to use, take as much
dough
as needed.
Shape
into rolls.
Place in greased pan; let
rise until doubled.
Bake at 400° until brown.
This dough will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: english pea salad
directions: Chill English peas and drain.
Lightly toss peas, eggs and onions with mayonnaise.
Add salt and pepper.
Add cheese and celery.
Chill well and serve on a lettuce cup and garnish with pimento.

title: watermelon jam
directions: Prepare jars.
Combine all ingredients except sugar in large saucepan.
Bring to a full rolling boil over high heat, stirring constantly.
Quickly add 5 1/2 cups sugar.
Return to a full rolling boil and boil 1 minute.
Fill jars.
Leave undisturbed until lids seal, about 1 hour.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine meal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Add egg, milk and onion.
Stir just until mixed.
In deep fat fryer or electric skillet, heat oil to 365°.
Fry 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients; let stand to thicken.
Add baking powder, soda and flour.
Roll and bake in 350° oven.
Bake to like brown.

title: hot salsa
directions: Mix all together and the flavors set at room temperature for a few hours.
Caution:
This recipe is very hot just the way it reads, so add extra jalapenos carefully.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Mix all real good with a fork and make into little balls. Bake at 250° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: turkey tacos
directions: Brown ground turkey in nonstick skillet.
Drain meat, then stir in onion, garlic, tomatoes, kidney beans, chili powder and ground cumin.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove cover during the last 5 minutes so liquid can evaporate.
Fill warmed tortillas with 1/3 cup filling.
Top with shredded lettuce and 1 tablespoon grated Cheddar.
Per 2 tacos:
310 calories, 10 gm fat.

title: milk gravy
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
In skillet, brown the seasoned flour in oil.
Stir frequently.
Add milk.
Stir to dissolve flour.
Let cook until cooked down into a gravy.
Stir often to prevent sticking and to dissolve lumps.
Takes about 35 minutes.

title: low-fat brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Batter will be very thick.
Spray bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with cooking oil spray.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into 15 pieces.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Blend all ingredients, except brown sugar and nuts.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.

title: roasted eggplant spread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place eggplant on baking sheet.
Bake until tender, turning occasionally, about 1 hour.
Remove eggplant from oven.
Let stand until cool enough to handle, about 10 min. Cut eggplant lengthwise in half, remove pulp.
Place pulp in medium bowl;
mash with potato masher until smooth.
Add tomatoes, onions, parsley, vinegar, oil, garlic, salt and oregano;
blend well.
Cover eggplant mixture,
refrigerate 2 hours.
Preheat broiler.
Split pita breads horizontally in half to form 4 rounds. Stack rounds;
cut into sixths or form 24 wedges.
Place pita wedges on baking sheet.
Broil until crisp, about 3 min., serve the eggplant spread with warm pita bread wedges.
Garnish with lemon and lime slices.

title: turkey cabbage soup
directions: Brown the ground turkey; drain the fat.
Then, in a large pot, add all the other ingredients.
Let it cook for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: frozen broccoli casserole or fresh squash casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in casserole dish.
Put the uncooked rice evenly in the dish.
Spread the broccoli or squash evenly over the rice.
Shake onions over top.
In a pan, heat the water or milk, soup, salt and pepper.
Mix together well.
Pour over top.
Bake 1 hour, then add cheese and bake until melted. Cook uncovered!

title: popovers that pop
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Generously grease 10 popover pans or ten 6 ounce custard cups (standard muffin pans can be used, filling alternating greased cups with batter).
Be sure eggs and milk are at room temperature.

title: peach and cranberry salad
directions: Peach Layer:
Prepare 1 package each jello as directed.
When cool, pour into 8-inch square glass pan.
Arrange peach slices in the jello and set.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and mayo; add cranberries, pineapple and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour in flat pan (8 x 10) and freeze.

title: five minute vegetable soup
directions: Sprinkle a small amount of salt in the bottom of an iron skillet.
Brown hamburger in the skillet with the salt.
In a large boiler, combine the meat with drippings and the remaining ingredients.
Allow the soup to come to a boil.
Serve when all ingredients are hot.

title: creamy crab and artichoke dip
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, blend cream cheese and mayonnaise until mixture is smooth. Stir in crab meat, artichokes, cheese and onion. Pour mixture into a 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve with crackers.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Stir together sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt; mix with apples.
Turn into ungreased square 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Dot with butter.

title: magnificent breakfast muffins
directions: Mix apples and sugar in a large bowl.
Add cranberries, carrots and nuts; stir gently to combine.
Mix dry ingredients and add to apple mixture; stir well.
Stir in eggs and oil.
Mix gently but thoroughly.
Divide evenly into greased muffin tins. Makes 12 large muffins.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick tests done.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes. Remove to wire rack.

title: mashed potato donuts
directions: Beat eggs, add remaining ingredients. Fry in deep oil. Brown on both sides. Coat with powered sugar.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Brown ground beef in large frying pan with onions, black pepper, salt and seasoned salt.
Boil kidney beans and season to taste.
Boil Polish sausages until done.
Combine cooked rice, beans and Polish sausages together in a large pot.
Mix well.
Add 1 tablespoon of chili powder (more, if desired).
Drain ground beef.
Combine all 3 mixtures together.
Add Cajun seasoning. Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve in bowl with cornbread or rolls.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Cut through sauerkraut several times.
Combine kraut with celery, onions and green and red peppers.
Dissolve sugar in oil and vinegar.
Pour over vegetables and toss.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Stir occasionally.

title: chicken and eggplant
directions: About 40 minutes before serving, cut chicken breast halves lengthwise into 1/2-inch wide strips.
Cut each baby eggplant lengthwise in half.
(If using regular eggplant, cut each crosswise in half, then lengthwise into 1-inch wide strips.)
In 12-inch skillet over high heat in hot salad oil, cook chicken until lightly browned and it loses its pink color throughout. With slotted spoon, remove chicken to bowl.

title: fresh cherry pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and cherries together.
Line pie pan with pastry.
Add cherry mixture and cover with top crust.
Bake in very hot oven (400°) for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 25 minutes longer.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Combine dry ingredients and cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to scalded milk cooled to room temperature. Make a well in center of dry ingredients.
Add liquid and work into dough.
Knead dough 15 to 20 minutes; set aside for 10 minutes.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into squares or triangles and fry in 420° shortening.
Fry 1 or 2 at a time so fat will stay hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken. DO NOT SALT.
Cool chicken and then remove meat from bones.
Spray large casserole dish with PAM.
Cut up chicken into sprayed dish.
Heat both cans of soup with 1/4 can of water. Mix into chicken.
Prepare stuffing using the chicken broth instead of water.
Spoon stuffing on top of chicken.

title: cream soup base
directions: This is dry mix that can be stored and kept on hand until needed.
When ready for soup, add 2 cups of cold water and cook over medium heat, stirring until thickened.
Add more water, if needed.

title: millionaire pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add 2 cups flour.
Mix well.
Add milk with extract in milk, then the remaining 2 cups of flour. Beat mixture for 8 minutes.
Cook in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° until cake is done.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets on.
Peel and slice.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add onion.
Cut up bacon and brown.
Pour over potatoes.
Mix and let stand for about 1 hour.
Mix sugar and flour.
Add to vinegar and water.
Bring to a boil and add to potatoes.

title: fiesta meat loaf
directions: Saute onion, celery and green peppers in oil until vegetables are tender.
Stir in chili sauce.
Combine 1/2 cup vegetable sauce mixture with ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Shape into a loaf or shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Yields 6 servings.

title: spicy crackers
directions: Mix oil and seasonings.
Toss crackers and refrigerate. Freezes well.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, oleo and cocoa in boiler.
Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, pecans, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well and spoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: magic bars
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and butter well; press into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Mix together remaining ingredients and spoon into 13 x 9 pan. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Dissolve jello into water.
Add vinegar and mayonnaise; blend well.
Chill until it begins to jell.
Add spinach, cottage cheese, green onion and celery; blend well.
Pour into a 7 1/2 x 12-inch Pyrex dish.
Refrigerate.

title: winning meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix lightly but thoroughly.
Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Drain and let stand 5 minutes.

title: all gone soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook 45 minutes or several hours in a crock-pot.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: First Day:
Make a brine of 3 tablespoons salt and 1 gallon cold water.
Prepare rind by removing all green and red.
Let stand in brine 24 hours.

title: cornmeal pan-fried green tomatoes
directions: Spread the flour on wax paper.
Put egg wash in shallow dish. Spread the cornmeal on wax paper; dredge the tomato slices in the flour and shake off excess, then dip into egg wash.
Coat with cornmeal, shake off excess.
Heat oil in large heavy skillet over medium flame.
When hot, add tomatoes.
Cook until golden brown; then turn.
Repeat, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Serves 8 to 12.

title: pepperoni balls
directions: Prepare roll mix according to package, omitting egg and using 1 c. water.
Dough does not need to rise.
Place one cheese cube on one pepperoni.
Pinch off a piece of dough and shape carefully around cheese and pepperoni, forming a ball.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Fry in deep hot oil for 5 minutes, turning once.
Drain on paper towel.

title: ham spread
directions: Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Stir in the remaining ingredients. Yields 3/4 cup.
Serve on assorted crackers or breads.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.

Then add beans (drained), Rotel and cream of chicken soup; cook until hot.	In a 13 by 9 inch pan (or smaller pan to make thicker layers) put a layer of tortillas, then meat mixture and cover with cheese.
Then repeat layers. Bake at 350°
until cheese melts.
If you want spicy use Mexican Velveeta and hot Rotel.

title: strawberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in water.
Stir in strawberries and chill until slightly congealed.
Then add pineapple and pecans.
Put half of this mixture in an oiled pan (9 x 13-inch) and chill slightly.

title: eggplant souffle
directions: Peel, cook and mash eggplant.
Combine eggplant, soup, cheese, bread crumbs, onion, catsup, salt and egg yolks; mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into eggplant mixture. Pour in greased 2-quart dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: eggplant-zucchini fish stew(serves 8)
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
Remove any skin from fish fillets and cut fillets into 1-inch pieces; set aside.

title: hot chili cheese dip
directions: Combine well and heat over low until cheese melts.
Stir occasionally and serve with corn chips.

title: lentil and sausage soup
directions: Sort and rinse lentils; place in Dutch oven. Cover with water two inches above lentils; soak 2 hours. Drain. Melt butter in a Dutch oven over med. heat; add sausage and saute 3 to 5 minutes. Add carrots, onion and celery; saute 6 minutes or until tender. Stir in lentils, broth and next three ingredients. Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes or until lentils are tender, stirring often. Process 1 3/4 cups lentil mixture in a blender until smooth, stopping to scrap down sides. Return puree to soup. To garnish, add fresh parsley to top. May also serve over rice. Yield: 16 servings.

title: glazed pork and ham loaf
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Mix in milk and cracker crumbs. Add ham mixture and celery; mix.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over loaves.
Cover and bake 2 1/2 hours at 325°.
Baste every 1/2 hour with pan drippings.

title: earthquake cookies
directions: Fold whipped topping, beaten egg and vanilla together.
Add cake mix and stir well.
Put confectioners sugar in separate bowl. Drop cookie mixture in by the teaspoon.
Coat each lightly with sugar.
Put on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
When done, edges are lightly brown and the top has "earthquake" lines!
Yields 5 dozen cookies.

title: pasta soup
directions: Slice sausage in small pieces.
Simmer for 10 minutes, drain. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, chicken broth, seasonings and sausage together in soup pot.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Add pasta and continue to simmer for 20 minutes.

title: one cup salad
directions: Mix and chill before serving.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften the cream cheese.
Wash the shrimp and set aside.
Cut up the green onions.
Mix mayonnaise and cream cheese together. Then add the shrimp and onion tops, mix well.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: sliced cucumber pickles
directions: Cut pickles into sticks.
Pour boiling water over sticks and let stand 4 hours.
Drain and dry.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Bring to a hard boil and boil 5 minutes.
Pour over pickles and seal tightly.

title: flo's sugar cookies
directions: Add all items but flour; beat well with mixer.
Add flour and mix.
Spoon by teaspoons into sugar and roll.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: delicious frozen dessert
directions: Stir first 5 ingredients together, making a dough.
Spread on cookie sheet, making sure that edges are same thickness (1/2 inch) as center, otherwise edges might burn.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, cool and crumble.
Spread one half of crumbs in 9 x 13-inch pan. Spoon vanilla ice cream over this mixture. While ice cream is still soft, spread Kraft caramel topping over ice cream.
Spread rest of crumbs last.
Cover and freeze.
(Can serve as many or as few as you like.
You can slice off what you need and put the rest back in the freezer.)

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon and set aside, reserve drippings. Combine potatoes, bacon, and onion. Add salt, pepper, sugar, vinegar and egg to bacon drippings. Heat thoroughly and pour over the potato mixture. Place in 325° oven for 30 to 45 minutes to heat throughout.

title: carob eggnog
directions: Beat honey into egg yolks.
Add salt and carob.
Slowly stir in milk.
In a double boiler, cook mixture over hot, but not boiling water.
Stir constantly until mixture coats a spoon. Cool.

title: tuna cheese spread
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Drain tuna; mash with fork.
Combine cheese, tuna and mayonnaise.
Add lemon juice, curry and salt.
Mix to blend well.
Add onions and stir to blend.
Chill for 1 hour. Serve as dip or as sandwich spread.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream the butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed on mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture, alternating with milk, beginning and ending with the flour.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 40 minutes at 300°. Cool in pan 15 minutes, then cool on wire rack.

title: chicken and dumplins
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Mix in shortening and water.
Roll very thin.
Cut into strips and then pieces.
Drop into boiling broth a few at a time.
Make sure broth continues to boil while adding dumplins.
Add chicken.
Stir.
Reduce heat.
Cook until dumplins are tender.

title: yellow squash pie
directions: Cook squash in a small amount of boiling water until tender; drain well and mash.
Combine margarine, sugar, lemon extract, flour, eggs and salt.
Add squash, stirring well.
Spoon squash mixture into pie shell and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until firm.
This will surprise you.
It tastes exactly like a lemon pie.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla until well blended.
Add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, apples and nuts.
Batter is heavy and looks greasy.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350° in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: swedish potatis korb(potato sausage)
directions: Coarse grind potatoes and onion.
Mix all together the potatoes, onion, hamburger, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Using a hand sausage stuffing tube with casing attached, force in mixture into 2 feet of casing.
Flatten casing to half its thickness and leave ends 1-inch empty.
Place 2 to 3 lengths into 8 quarts of salted boiling water.
Cook 30 minutes.
Remove from water and serve hot with salad and French bread.
Serves 1 to 1 1/2 persons. Is good cold also.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and dry pudding mix; stir well.
Add other ingredients, mix well, pour into dish and refrigerate.

title: applesauce donuts
directions: Fill a large heavy saucepan or electric skillet 2/3 full with vegetable oil.
Heat to 360° on a deep fat frying thermometer. Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and salt onto a piece of wax paper.
Beat together the granulated sugar, brown sugar and eggs in large bowl with an electric mixer at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Beat in 2 tablespoons oil.
Stir in flour mixture alternately with the milk, beginning and ending with the dry ingredients.
Stir in the applesauce and vanilla.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Add shortening and water; beat 1 minute with electric mixer.
Add applesauce and egg; beat 3 minutes.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool; frost.

title: canadian cake mayonnaise
directions: Cream the mayonnaise.
Add other ingredients and the water. Bake in a lined-tin on 350° and reduce heat to 300°.
Bake for 3/4 to 1 hour until cake is dry when tested with a knife.
(This makes a large cake.
Half the quantity in a loaf pan, makes a fair-sized cake.)

title: reuben style skillet
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, combine soup, dressing and water.
Over high heat, bring to boiling.
Stir in slaw mix, reducing heat to low.
Cover; simmer for 5 minutes or until cabbage is tender-crisp, stirring twice.
Stir in beef and cover.
Cook 2 minutes or until heated, stirring once.
Combine croutons, cheese and parsley.
Sprinkle over mixture; heat 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spiced cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in slow cooking pot.
Cover and heat on low for 2 to 5 hours or more.

title: wiener mix-up
directions: Mix in crock-pot all ingredients. Cook until hot or longer.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in 3 quarts of rapidly boiling water for 7 minutes.
Drain.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, combine macaroni, tomato sauce, cheese, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all together. Serve chilled.

title: macaroni cheese pie
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Grate cheese.
Put 1 layer macaroni, 1/2 butter and 1/2 cheese in baking dish.
Repeat macaroni and butter. Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over layered macaroni and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rhubarb sauce or jam
directions: Cook rhubarb and sugar using the 2 to 3 tablespoons of water (no more than is necessary to start the mixture to cooking) until the rhubarb is tender.
Stir in jello.
Cool.
Must be kept refrigerated.
If using for jam place in containers and store in freezer until ready to use.

title: hot rolls
directions: Put yeast in warm water; add 1 teaspoon sugar. Let stand 5 minutes. Add scalded milk; let stand until cool. Add 4 tablespoons sugar, salt and shortening and mix.
Add egg, then add flour gradually. Knead and let rise until double. Make into rolls. Let rolls rise. Bake at 450° until light brown.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss lightly.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix
all dry ingredients together.
Add milk and melted margarine to dry mixture.
Stir well.
Blend in sliced apples. Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes in a 375° oven.
Cool for 10 minutes and slice into bars.

title: rolls
directions: Mix milk, sugar, yeast and water.
Beat real good.
Add oil. Mix real good.
Add flour a little at a time until dough is thick. Knead dough well.
Place in pan and let rise 1 hour.
Push dough back down.
Roll out and cut like biscuits.
Put in pan and spread butter on top of rolls.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 350° to 400` until done.

title: bread pudding
directions: In a large bowl mix all dry ingredients; add liquids, eggs and raisins.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour batter into a greased 2-pound baking pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: catfish stew
directions: Cook fish until well done; drain water off of fish.
Set aside to cool.
Peel and cut potatoes, onions and peppers.
Put tomatoes in blender and blend well.
Cook peppers, onions, potatoes and tomatoes until well done.
Take fish off bone.
Add to soup mixture.
Add black pepper, salt and shortening.
Heat until this comes to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; simmer until blended.
Serves 25 to 30.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix jello, hot water, lemon juice and cold water and refrigerate for soft gel.
Add pineapple, oranges and bananas; gel.

title: st. patrick's day punch
directions: In a gallon container, mix Kool-Aid, sugar, water and pineapple juice.
Chill to slush.
Before serving, add 1 to 2 cans 7-Up.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Cook beef and onion until beef is browned; drain.
Spread in pie plate. Sprinkle with salt and cheese.
Stir eggs, milk and Bisquick until well blended.
Pour on top of meat and cheese.
Bake 25 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: cascade potatoes
directions: Melt butter and saute onions. In a large bowl, beat soup and cream cheese until smooth. Stir in salt, pepper, onions and potatoes. Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole. Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Add to sugar mixture and beat well.
Stir in vanilla, grated carrots, pineapple and walnuts.
Bake in either 3 (8-inch) pans or 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan which have been well greased. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When cool, ice with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: party wieners
directions: Put chili sauce, jelly and mustard in saucepan.
Heat until jelly dissolves.
Add wieners and simmer.
Put in crock-pot or Fondue pot to keep warm.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Peel and slice all six potatoes.
Do the following in layers in casserole bowl: 3 potatoes, sliced; salt and pepper; 1/2 can of corn; 1/2 ring of sausage, sliced; 1 can of cream of chicken soup.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Blend
brown sugar and cinnamon.
Mix
cake
mix,
sour cream, oil
and
eggs.
Pour half mixture into
greased
x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle
with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Add remaining batter
and lightly swirl with knife.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. While cake is baking, mix together the confectioners sugar, milk and vanilla.
As soon as cake is done, put holes
all over
with
a
toothpick.
Immediately
pour sugar mixture over cake.
Will soon set up in a lovely glaze.

title: classic meat lasagna
directions: Saute onion and garlic in Crisco shortening or Crisco oil in large skillet on medium heat until soft.
Push to one side of skillet.
Add meat.
Crumble and cook.
Drain, if necessary.
Add tomatoes.
Break into smaller pieces.
Add tomato paste, basil, oregano, sugar and pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: easy oven pot roast
directions: Place roast in large piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil in a shallow roasting pan.
Sprinkle soup mix over roast.
Top with mushrooms, including liquid.
Fold foil down to meat and up on sides, sealing tightly.
Bake for 1 to 2 hours until fork easily pierces meat at 325° to 350°.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown 1 pound hamburger meat in a large Dutch oven; drain. Add canned vegetables. Heat until ready to eat.

title: chicken satinbocca
directions: Place chicken, bone side up, on cutting board and cover with plastic wrap.
Working from center out, pound with mallet into a 5 x 5-inch piece.
Remove wrap and place a ham slice on each breast, cutting it to fit.
Top with some tomato and a dash of sage.
Tuck in sides and roll up, jelly roll style, pressing to seal well.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix well.
Spoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Mix in gallon-size container.
Fill remainder of container with 7-Up.
May not use all 2 liters.
Place in freezer.
Thaw a little before ready to use.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: cherries 'n cake
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, flour, salt and baking powder in a large mixing bowl.
Add shortening, milk and vanilla or almond extract. Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover batter with drained cherries.

Sprinkle 1 cup of sugar over cherries, then pour 2 cups of hot liquid over cherries. Bake in a preheated 375° oven (350° when using glass baking dish) about 40 minutes, covering with foil the last 15 minutes, if necessary, to prevent overbrowning.
Serve warm with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: company potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in baking dish.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
It is done when no longer shakes in middle.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Line bottom of pie shell with largest berries, about 1/2 the quart.
Mash the remainder of berries and cook with sugar, water and cornstarch until thick.
Cool completely and then pour over berries in the shell.
Chill for about 2 hours before serving and add whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: a happy home recipe
directions: A variety
of
meals can be prepared as noted below and found to be very palatable.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Then add the eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition and very well after the fourth one.
Add remaining ingredients and fold in the cherries and walnuts.
Pour into a prepared tube cake pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: spice cake
directions: Beat shortening, sugar and eggs.
Combine dry ingredients. Add alternately with milk to first mixture. Beat well.
Add vanilla. Pour batter into two greased and floured 8-inch pans. Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven. Frost with favorite caramel frosting.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine and roll in nuts.
This
is soft so I refrigerate before I try to roll in ball.

title: puppy chow
directions: In a double boiler, melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over Chex and stir until covered. Place Chex mixture in clean grocery bag with powdered sugar and shake until coated.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Add other ingredients and spread between devil's food cake after cooking by directions on package.

title: the cake(from peg brachen)
directions: Beat all together for 5 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar if desired.

title: holiday punch(non-alcoholic)
directions: In large bowl, dissolve jello and 2 cups of sugar in 2 cups hot water, stirring until all sugar is dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and flour. Add hot water. Cook in a heavy saucepan until it boils and thickens. Serve with biscuits.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and lightly floured pan (8 x 8-inch).
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until done (do not overbake).
Cool; cut into squares.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Melt cheese and butter.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into cheese.
Cut bread into 1-inch cubes and dip into cheese mixture until covered.
Sprinkle with paprika and chill on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve 2/3 cup of dry cake mix.
Combine remaining cake mix, margarine and 1 egg. Mix together.
Press into prepared pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix 2/3 cup cake mix, brown sugar, syrup, vanilla, 3 eggs and chopped pecans.
Pour over partially baked crust.
Return to oven and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: grandma's strawberry shortcake
directions: Put the shortcakes in the bottom of a dessert bowl.
Pour the strawberries over the top (with the sugar mixed in the strawberries).
Then put the whipped cream over the top.
There you have Grandma's Strawberry Shortcake!

title: valerie's sausage and potato soup
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add sausage to onion and brown.
In large pot add browned onions and sausage, diced potatoes, tomatoes, beef consomme, V-8 juice and green chilies.
Cook on low heat for several hours.
About 1/2 hour before soup is done add frozen corn. This recipe works well cooked in a crock-pot.

title: mexican cornbread salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding mayonnaise last.
Stir together.

title: cherry stuff
directions: Mix well. Refrigerate until firm. Also may freeze.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Cube bread and place in large casserole dish. In large bowl, add milk and beaten eggs. Add salt and pepper. Pour over cubed bread. Top with sausage (crumbled) and cheese. (Best to prepare and set in the refrigerator overnight.) Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bread is cooked thoroughly.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend well.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 1 cup of sauce.

title: ozzarello sausage
directions: Cut sausage in 3-inch pieces.
Brown (without grease) in covered skillet.
Pour off any excess grease.
Add wine or dressing, water, rosemary leaves and mushrooms.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Add peppers and cook for 10 minutes more.
Buon appetito.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and dry jello.
Add other ingredients. Refrigerate for thicker consistency.

title: golden carrot bake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the 1/2 cup shredded process cheese.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle remaining shredded cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: breaded orange roughy
directions: Pour lemon juice in shallow bowl.
Combine breadcrumbs, cheese, garlic and onion powder in another shallow bowl.
Dip fish in lemon juice; roll in breadcrumbs.
Place fish in baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Sprinkle with remaining breadcrumb mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until fish flakes easily.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Place in crock-pot and cook 6 hours on high.

title: mexican joe
directions: Cook hamburger, pepper and onion in skillet.
Add olives and raisins when meat is about half done.
In another skillet, cook tomato sauce, paste and seasonings for about 20 minutes.
Combine meat and sauce; pour over Fritos in a casserole.
Lay cheese over all; bake at 350° just until cheese is melted.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix melted margarine, chopped pecans and flour. Pat out on 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool.

title: molasses cookies with date filling(mom's recipe)
directions: Mix all together.
Roll thin; cut out with round cookie cutter.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed. Spoon into small ovenproof dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Makes 2 cups. Serve with baked tortilla chips, crackers, baked pita wedges or breads of your choice.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients (do not stir); cook on High for 4 1/2 to 5 minutes according to your microwave temperature.
Remove from microwave.
Add paraffin; stir until melted.
Add nuts; return to microwave for 5 minutes.
Remove from microwave and add baking soda; stir well.
Pour into a pan sprayed with Pam and spread out immediately.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour in bowl.
Mix 1/2 cup milk and beaten egg yolks.
Scald 2 1/2 cups milk in double boiler.
Remove from boiler and gradually add to dry ingredients and egg yolk mixture. Return to double boiler, stirring until thick.
Remove from boiler, put in large pat butter and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Add 3/4 tablespoon cream of tartar and 6 tablespoons sugar.
Seal pie and bake at 350° until brown.

title: chicken breast scampi
directions: Fresh dill can be added if desired.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender. Mix melted margarine, flour, milk, salt and pepper and mustard together in saucepan on top of stove over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Put in 1 cup of the cheese to help thicken the mixture while stirring.
Pour water off cooked macaroni and put in long Pyrex dish.
Pour the cooked mixture over the macaroni and sprinkle the remainder of grated cheese on top. Cook at 375° until cheese is melted and bubbly on top.

title: brie pasta
directions: Chop garlic, tomatoes and basil.
Clean off the coating on Brie and shred.
Mix all of these ingredients with oil, wine and season. Let stand at room temperature.
Boil pasta, al dente.
Drain and mix with Brie mixture; serve.

title: bistro chicken
directions: Mix salad dressing and seasonings.
Brush chicken with 1/2 of the salad dressing mixture.
Barbecue chicken over medium hot coals for 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn and brush with remaining salad dressing mixture.
Continue cooking until chicken is done.
Makes a great sandwich on a roll with some extra dressing mixture on the roll.

title: corned beef stew
directions: In Dutch oven, cook onion, celery and green pepper in hot oil until tender but not brown.
Stir in water, potatoes, undrained tomatoes, zucchini, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and bouillon granules.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer covered 15 minutes.
Stir in corned beef.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes more until meat is heated through.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zabaglione
directions: Combine ingredients in top part of a double boiler.
Cook over simmering, not boiling water, beating constantly, with a wire whip or an eggbeater, for about 10 minutes, or until very thick.
Serve immediately in glasses or small coffee cups.
Makes 4 to 6 cold Zabaglione.
Proceed as above.
Set pan in basin filled with cracked ice.
Beat Zabaglione until thoroughly cold.
Pour into glasses or cups and keep refrigerated.
Unless Zabaglione is beaten thoroughly until cold, it will not remain frothy but will collapse and separate.

title: lazy betty fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Pour pie filling and drained pineapple into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Stir them together and smooth out in pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over the top of the fruit.
Drizzle melted butter over the top of the dry cake mix. Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: In a bowl, mix box of graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Put 2/3 crumb mixture in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan and set the rest aside.
Pour the cherry pie filling on top of the crumb mixture in pan and spread evenly.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, Dream Whip and milk, then spread over the cherry pie filling.
Take the rest of the crumb mixture and spread evenly over the top of the cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli. Drain and cool.
Beat eggs, then add to the cottage cheese.
Blend in flour.
Add broccoli last. Then sprinkle cheese on top.
Dot with the small chunks of butter.
Bake at 350° in a greased casserole about 45 minutes, until golden brown on top.
Test with a knife coming out clean.

title: peanut chicken
directions: Blend 3 teaspoons cornstarch and 1 tablespoon soy sauce.
Add chicken.
Chill for 1 hour.
Blend sugar, 1 teaspoon cornstarch, sherry and rest of soy sauce; set aside.
Melt oleo in wok or skillet.
Add chicken mixture.
Stir-fry until chicken is done, about 3 minutes.
Add onions and pepper.
Stir-fry until onions are clear.
Stir in sherry mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Stir in peanuts.
Serve over rice.

title: snack bar pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour and salt gradually and stir in vanilla extract and crushed pineapple with juice. Bake in large greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until tested done.

title: dee's too easy chicken teriyaki
directions: Start your rice.
Roll chicken in flour to coat.
In a large, nonstick frypan, melt butter.
Add chicken and cook over medium heat until lightly browned (5 to 7 minutes).
Turn chicken over and continue cooking until lightly browned.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Add remaining ingredients to pan and stir to mix. Simmer 1 to 2 minutes.
Return chicken to pan and simmer on both sides for 2 to 3 minutes each.
Serve over rice.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and slice eggplant in 1/4-inch slices. Dip each slice in egg, then bread crumbs. Saute in hot oil until brown. Place layer of eggplant in dish. Sprinkle with cheeses, oregano and margarine. Cover with sauce. Repeat until gone. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1/2 hour or until bubbly and melted.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown the sausage.
Cook and drain.
Spread the crescent rolls or pizza dough onto 16-inch ungreased pan.
(Make sure there is an edge to the dough.)
Spoon sausage over dough.
Sprinkle hash browns over sausage.
Sprinkle the Parmesan cheese over the hash browns.
Mix together the eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over pizza.
Top with the grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick and easy chili
directions: Cook ground beef in a Dutch oven until meat is browned, stirring until it crumbles; drain.
Add tomatoes and remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yield:
9 cups.

title: aunt marie's pineapple icing for angel food cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, then add 2 1/2 cups more of the powdered sugar.
Add crushed pineapple.

title: big orange cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan and set aside.
Beat together butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Drain and layer in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Mix the can of soup with the milk and pour this over the ground beef in the cake pan.
Sprinkle or spread the cheese evenly over the soup and milk mixture.
Dump the bag of Tater Tots on the top of the cheese.
Bake in the oven 30 to 40 minutes or until the potatoes are brown and done.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Separate broccoli into small flowerets.
Strip stem and chop up.
Toss broccoli, onion, raisins, cheese and bacon together. Blend mayonnaise, cider vinegar, lemon juice, sugar, salt and pepper together.
Combine with salad ingredients.

title: jalapeno pickles
directions: Drain juice from pickles.
Remove half the jar of pickles and save.
Pour sugar into jar with pickles.
Pour jar of peppers with juice on pickles and sugar.
Put remainder of pickles back into jar.
Seal extremely tight.
Invert jar - Place pan under jar just in case it isn't sealed good.
Turn jar upside down every day for 11 days.
Then chill.

title: apple cake
directions: *Plums or other fruit may be substituted.

title: fruit salad plate
directions: Prepare Curried Cottage Cheese and Lemonade Dressing.
Have all the ingredients, except banana, chilled.
Just before serving, slice banana and dip slices into fruit juice or syrup to prevent darkening.
Arrange fruit on lettuce leaves, with Curried Cottage Cheese in center of platter.
Serve Lemonade Dressing on side or drizzle over fruit.

title: mayonnaise cake
