directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and sugar.
Add mayo, water, vanilla and cocoa.
Mix on high with electric mixer.
No more than 2 min.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 35-40 min.

title: wild rice side dish
directions: Rinse rice thoroughly in a strainer.
Combine wild rice, water and chicken bouillon cubes in a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low boil; cover loosely and cook 45 to 60 minutes, or until rice has puffed and most of liquid has absorbed. Remove from heat.
Fluff rice with fork; cover tightly and let stand for 5 minutes.
Drain off excess water.
In separate pan, melt butter and saute onion, celery and mushrooms.
Combine cooked rice with saute mix.
Salt or spice to taste.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Preheat oven 425°.
Place crust in pie plate and add rhubarb and strawberries to pie crust.
Pour all other ingredients over top of fruit.
Place inverted second crust on top and seal with a fork, pressing gently around edges.
Bake 425° on lowest rack of oven for 10 minutes.
Make vent holes.
Place pie on center rack, reduce heat to 350°, bake 20 minutes and check.
Bake up to another 20 minutes if necessary.

title: chocolate malt ice cream
directions: Mix sugar and dry malted milk in 2 quart saucepan.
Gradually stir in milk and beaten eggs.
Heat just to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Pour into bowl.
Cover surface with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate until chilled, about 3 hours.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients well.
Wash and remove stems from mushrooms.
Microwave 2 minutes until tender.
Stuff mushrooms with crab mixture and top with grated Cheddar cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.

title: kaleidoscope salad
directions: Rinse the cans of beans in cold water and drain them well. Add the peppers and onions.
Mix the oil, vinegar, salt and sugar. Pour over the beans.
Chill in a covered bowl.

title: chicken ratatouille
directions: Heat oil; add chicken and saute 2 minutes.
Set aside.
Add zucchini, eggplant, onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Stir often during 15 minutes of cooking or until tender-crisp, then add tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer 5 minutes, until chicken is tender.
Serve with rice.

title: chew bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into well-greased and floured pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Bread will rise high to edge of pan and sink in middle.
Run a knife around edge of pan between pan and bread immediately after removing from oven to prevent sticking.

title: white texas sheet cake
directions: In a large saucepan, bring oleo and water to a boil.
Remove from
heat; stir in flour, sugar, eggs, sour cream, almond extract, salt and soda until smooth.
Pour into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 22 minutes, or until cake is golden brown and tests done.
Cool for 20 minutes.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Soak 24 hours in lime water.

title: special deviled eggs
directions: In a bowl mix together first 7 ingredients until creamy.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in shredded cheese.
Cover and refrigerate until serving.
Yield:
25 appetizers.

title: scarlett's hot dog chili
directions: Do not brown the hamburger!

title: california vegetable pie
directions: Brown
ground
beef, adding onion, salt, pepper, catsup and chili
and	set aside.
Saute zucchini and green pepper in margarine for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add dill weed and salt and set aside.
Separate
crescent rolls into triangles and press over bottom and sides of ungreased 9 x 10-inch pie plate.
Spoon in meat mixture.
Sprinkle
cup
cheese
on meat.
Spread on zucchini mixture and top with tomato slices.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle on remaining cheese and bake additional 15 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: pork and vegetable chili
directions: Toss 1/2 of pork with 1 tablespoon flour in plastic bag; shake to coat evenly.
Heat 1/2 tablespoon oil in Dutch oven over medium heat.
Add floured pork; cook until browned evenly on all sides. Remove to plate.
Repeat with remaining pork, flour and 1 tablespoon oil.
Remove pork.
Heat remaining 1/2 tablespoon oil in pot.
Add onion and garlic; cook 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, chili powder, cumin, oregano, sugar, cocoa powder, salt and reserved pork.
Simmer 40 minutes.
Stir cubed squash and green pepper into chili.
Bring to simmering; cook 15 minutes.
Stir in beans; cook until heated through and vegetables are just tender. Top with sour cream and/or shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: chicken 'n dumplings
directions: Cover chicken with water and boil until done.
De-bone chicken and set aside.
Mix together eggs and dry ingredients until no longer dry.
Put 1/2 of mixture on floured surface.
Knead
slightly and roll out flat and thin (like a pie crust).
Cut with table knife into 1 - 1 1/2 in squares.
Drop dumplings into boiling chicken broth. (IF BROTH IS NOT BOILING, DUMPLINGS WILL FALL APART)
Pat down with spoon.
DO NOT STIR.
Add chicken.

title: cracker pudding
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, sugar, salt and milk.
Stir in melted shortening and beaten egg yolks.
Add vanilla.
Pour mixture into greased baking dish and bake in moderate slow oven at 325°
for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and cover with meringue prepared by beating the whites of eggs until stiff, adding confectioners sugar gradually and lemon juice.
Bake in slow oven at 300°
until meringue is brown, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Bread chicken breasts by first covering breast with flour, then egg, then breadcrumbs.
Place breaded chicken breasts in frying pan with 2 tablespoons melted margarine.
Cook on medium heat, covered, until chicken is done.
Place cooked chicken in
9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover chicken with spaghetti sauce, then sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, when cheese is melted.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Whip all together well.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: never-fail divinity candy
directions: Boil the sugar, water and salt until it reaches the hard-ball stage.
Place marshmallow cream in large bowl.
Stir in hot syrup. Fold in nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: meltaways
directions: Combine butter, oil, sugars and vanilla extract in a large bowl; beat until creamed.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt together, add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Chill 2 hours (at least).

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all ingredients. Beat at slow speed.
Pour into greased loaf pan or pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: nova scotia cookies
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and cream.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Add water and nuts.
Roll out on floured board. Cut in squares and bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 15 minutes. Makes approximately 90 squares.

title: zucchini skillet casserole
directions: Cut all vegetables in nearly equal sized pieces.
Put zucchini and onions in non-stick skillet and saute with a small amount of water until nearly tender.
At this point, spoon or pour off as much liquid as possible.
Add mushrooms and lots of lemon-pepper. Saute until nearly tender.
Add tomatoes and stir until warmed. Spread mixture out in skillet and cover with cheese.
Put cover on skillet and remove from heat.
Let sit for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well and cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and uncooked oatmeal.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Bake cake according to instructions on box. Let cool. Drain juice from pineapple. Mix pineapple and Cool Whip together and spread on top.

title: peach pie
directions: Arrange cut peaches in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 15 mins. at 400°.
Mix together egg, sugar and cornstarch.
Add this mixture to the peaches.
Continue baking pie for 45 mins. at 350°.

title: creamy potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes well.
Do not peel.
Boil until tender.
Drain water.
Using an electric mixer, mix all ingredients except paprika until blended.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: five veggie soup
directions: Place all ingredients in a large deep cooking pan and bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer 2 to 3 hours or until beans and vegetables are tender.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Skillet brown beef and onion.
Drain fat.
Add soup and water; bring to a boil.
Add noodles and cook until noodles are tender. Add corn and bring to a boil.
Add cheese and sour cream.
Place in a greased casserole dish (1 1/2 to 2-quart).
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: aunt tammy's buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs until lemon-colored. Add buttermilk and oil.
Fold dry ingredients into wet mixture.

title: party apple cider
directions: Mix brown sugar and cider in slow cooker.
Put all spices in cheesecloth, hang over inside of slow cooker until spices are in liquid mixture.
Add orange slices.
Cook on low for 2 to 8 hours. Serve with dash of cinnamon or nutmeg.
Great to make ahead of Christmas for family gathering.
Makes the house smell great!
Can add port wine instead of cider.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Place onions and mushrooms in a 1 1/2-quart ovenware casserole dish with 2 tablespoons oil.
Cover.
Cook vegetables for 5 minutes or until onion is transparent.
Stirring once, add chicken.
Cover.
Continue cooking chicken and vegetables 7 to 9 minutes or until chicken is cooked, stirring once.
Drain.
Blend in sour cream and salt.
Stir well.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: almond chicken
directions: Chop chicken into
bite-size pieces.
Mix 2 tablespoons cornstarch and egg by hand into chicken.
Add vegetable oil to give chicken a glazed
look.
Put
enough
oil
in	skillet to cover chicken.
Make oil
hot.
Add chicken and stir-fry until done.
Add vegetables and
stir
for
2 minutes.
Drain excess oil.
Combine water, garlic salt, sugar, Accent and soy sauce. Add to	chicken
mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Mix 2 tablespoons cornstarch	with
a
little
water.
Add to sauce and thicken. Put in a dish and top with almonds.

title: easy foldovers
directions: Combine pie crust mix, cream cheese, sugar, milk and extract. Stir with a fork until mixture forms a ball.
Divide in half.
On a lightly floured board, roll to a 10-inch square.
With a pastry wheel or knife, cut into 16 (2 1/2-inch) squares.
Spoon 1/2 teaspoon preserves in center of each square.
(You can place a pecan half on each one, if desired.)
Moisten opposite corners with water.
Bring corners up over filling; pinch tightly to seal. Arrange on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Transfer to wire rack, lightly.
Makes about 32.

title: pork satay
directions: Mix peanut butter, coriander, cayenne pepper, black pepper, garlic, onion, salt, sugar, lemon juice and soy sauce in a bowl to make marinade.
Cut pork into cubes and toss with marinade.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate all day or overnight. Skewer meat and broil over charcoal fire 20 to 25 minutes or bake in a 375° oven about 40 minutes.
Baste often with olive oil.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Beat egg slightly.
Add remaining ingredients to egg.
Blend well with spoon.
Shape into loaf; put into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Tear cake in pieces; put in an 8 x 8-inch pan or bowl.
Mix pudding with milk as directed.
Stir in ice cream; pour mixture over cake pieces and chill for at least an hour.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Wash and drain chicken.
In a large bowl, mix vinegar, soy sauce and other ingredients and marinate for 3 to 5 minutes. Transfer to a cooking pot and cook over low heat until the chicken is tender.
Add cooking oil or sesame
oil. Serve with rice, potatoes or bread.

title: hawaiian style yams
directions: Combine yams, pineapple, reserved pineapple juice, butter, sugar, and cinnamon in a 3 quart casserole.
Beat until creamy and well blended with mixer or by hand.
Fold in pecans, sprinkle with brown sugar and drizzle with additional melted butter.
Cook in microwave 7 to 10 minutes, giving dish 1/4 turn once during time, or bake in 350° oven until bubbly around edges.
Casserole may be frozen.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: caramel pralines
directions: Put 2 cups sugar, cream, butter and salt in heavy saucepan. Bring to boil, stirring; continue cooking over low heat.

title: boston baked corn
directions: Mix all but bacon.
Put in a 1-quart casserole.
Top with bacon.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate kahlua cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate chips.
After ingredients are blended together, add chocolate chips.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or frost with chocolate fudge frosting or drizzle with a glaze of your choice.
Be creative.
The longer this cake is refrigerated, the better it gets.

title: chicken madrid
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken. Brown on both sides and remove to a plate.
Add onion, bell peppers and garlic to skillet. Cook, stirring constantly, until onion is transparent. Return chicken to skillet.
Pour in tomatoes. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot applesauce(diabetic)
directions: Start heating oven to 350°.
Heat applesauce and Sweet 'N Low over hot water; gradually add beaten egg, then grated rind and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 cups or four 1/2 cup servings.
A 1/2 cup serving equals 78 calories.

title: cucumber spread
directions: Place cucumbers and onion on paper towels; squeeze out all moisture.

title: corned beef ball
directions: Cream together the ingredients.
Cool; shape into ball or log. (I put in fridge overnight and shape next day.)

title: creamy potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes; drain off water.
(Reserve a small amount in case needed.)
Put margarine and milk in potatoes.
Chop up onions and eggs. Add eggs, relish and onions to potatoes.
Also, add mayonnaise to mixture.
Mix all together with potato masher. Serves 20 to 30.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk with wire whisk.
Add Eagle Brand milk. Add half of Cool Whip.
Layer dish with vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding.
Use remaining Cool Whip on top.
Crunch several vanilla wafers and sprinkle on top of pudding.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin into 1 c. hot water in a 10 x 6 dish.
Add raspberries with juice and applesauce.
Stir until thickened.
Do not add cold water!
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sweet tooth treats
directions: Combine peanut butter, corn syrup and coconut until blended. Stir in cereal.
Shape into 1-1/2-inch balls.
In a pan, over medium heat, melt chocolate chips and shortening.
Dip balls halfway into chocolate.
Place on waxed paper-lined baking sheets to harden.
Yield:
2-1/2 dozen.

title: grandma's chopped apple christmas cake
directions: Pour sugar over apples.
Let stand one hour.
Beat eggs into oil and add vanilla.
Mix this into apples (after they stand one hour).
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts and raisins. Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 60 minutes (glass pans 325°).
Makes 1 large cake or about 3 loaves.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Simmer chicken cutlets in broth or water.
Add bay leaf, celery, salt and peppercorns for about 25 minutes.
Drain. Reserve chicken for salad; save stock for another use.
Let chicken cool, then chop into bite size pieces.

title: icebox cake
directions: Lay graham crackers in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix 1 package pudding according to package directions.
Stir in 1/2 tub Cool Whip into pudding, mixing well.
Pour over graham crackers, then put another layer of graham crackers on top.
Fix second package of pudding as package directs, then add remaining Cool Whip, mixing well.
Pour over graham crackers.
For final layer, frost more graham crackers with chocolate frosting and cover pudding.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken in bottom of oblong baking dish; salt and pepper, if desired.
Mix soups and milk and pour over chicken.
Take stuffing mix and use broth to moisten stuffing.
Put stuffing mix on top and cover with aluminum foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fajitas
directions: Marinate meat strips in fajita sauce to cover as long as possible, preferably overnight or all day.
Slice vegetables into strips.
Wrap tortillas in foil and warm in 350° oven while preparing meal.

title: potato and cheese casserole
directions: To Microwave:
In medium bowl, stir soup until smooth.
Add cheese, milk, pepper and garlic; stir until well blended.
In 2-quart microwave-safe casserole layer 1/2 of the potatoes, 1/2 of the onions and 1/2 of the soup mixture.
Repeat layers.
Cover with lid; microwave on High 23 minutes or until potatoes are tender, rotating dish 3 times during cooking.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: never fail strawberry pie
directions: Add pudding and jello with 2 cups of water in saucepan.
Cook just to the boiling point.
Cool to room temperature and add strawberries.
Pour in baked pie crust and put in fridge at least an hour or until pie has firmly set.
Serve with whipped cream or whipped topping.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease generously and dust with flour three 9 inch round cake pans.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt together oleo and cocoa.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour, salt, baking powder, pecans and vanilla.
Mix well by hand.
(Do not use mixer for this recipe.)
Pour into well-greased, floured oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes (check at 20 minutes).
Spread with marshmallow cream while hot.
Cover with chocolate frosting, either cooked or prepared store type.

title: raspberry torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour three 8-inch cake pans.
Prepare cake mix, substituting 4 egg yolks for specified whole eggs.
Spread batter into pans.
Beat egg whites with salt until foamy.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Spread meringue mixture evenly over batter in cake pans.
Mix cinnamon with 7 teaspoons of sugar.
Sprinkle over meringue.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack, meringue side up.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine cheese, soup and milk in saucepan until cheese is melted.
Pour over broccoli, which has been placed in a casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers (about half of a stack) and combine with half stick of oleo (melted) and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 400° until bubbly.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Mix and bring to a boil the first 4 ingredients, stirring often.
Boil 1 minute only and remove from stove. Add last 4 ingredients. Stir together and drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper. Ready to eat when cool.

title: kossuth kiflie - half moon cakes
directions: In a
small
bowl,
beat egg whites.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and cream of tartar; set aside.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add
egg yolks (2 at a time); beat well until good and creamy.
Add
lemon juice, vanilla and lemon extract.
Mix baking powder
with
flour
and
add
to mixture at low speed. Fold in egg
white.
Pour into greased and floured pan, 9 x 12 x 2-inches. Mix
cup
chopped
nuts
and	1/4 cup sugar; sprinkle on top.

title: yellow cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar.
Add shortening, milk, vanilla and eggs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour in large bowl.
Mix oleo, cocoa and water in pan and bring to rapid boil.
Pour over dry ingredients and beat.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla and beat well.
This is a thin batter.
Bake in jelly roll pan 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: jiffy pumpkin torte
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cake mix and margarine. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1/2 stick margarine and Jiffy cake mix together.
Crumble together on top of pumpkin.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crab-stuffed chicken breasts(serves 8)
directions: Place chicken (one piece at a time) between plastic wrap and pound with a meat mallet, working from the center out until about 1/8-inch thick.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Cook rice (Riverbrand).
Cook broccoli and drain.
Saute onion, rice, broccoli and mushrooms in butter.
Add milk, soup and cheese.
In glass casserole, mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: new toll house cookies
directions: Cream shortening, adding sugars gradually until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition (for more than one recipe).
Add hot water, then sifted dry ingredients.
Add chocolate chips, oats and vanilla and blend thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: pocket bread (pita)(mraqud or  kmaj)
directions: Put flour in large bowl.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water and add the sugar.
Let set until it proofs, about 3 minutes.
Mix it together with the oil, salt and 2 cups warm water.
Pour it to the side of the bowl and start blending with flour.
Knead for 10 minutes, dipping hands in warm water occasionally to form smooth dough.
Shape dough into a ball and place in a lightly oiled warm bowl, turning to cover ball with oil.
Cover with cloth and let rise for 1 1/2 hours or until doubled in size.
Punch dough down and form 2 dozen balls.
Cover with cloth and plastic and let rest for 20 minutes.
On lightly floured board, roll dough with rolling pin to about 6-inches in diameter and 1/4-inch thick.
Place on cloth; cover and rest for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 500°.
Place on ungreased sheet.
Bake 7 minutes; broil 10 seconds.
Remove and brush with butter or oil.
The dough will puff up and have pocket inside.

title: zucchini spice bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts; set aside. Beat eggs lightly in a large mixing bowl.

Add sugar, oil and vanilla to eggs. Beat until creamy. Stir in zucchini and pineapple. Add dry ingredients, stirring only until dry ingredients are moistened. Spoon batter into well greased and floured pans (may use Pam spray). Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done. Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan. This makes 2 loaves (9 x 5 x 3-inch) or 5 small loaf pans. This is great to wrap in Saran and foil wrap, then freeze.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Turn out on floured board and work into a ball.
Roll out to about 1/2 inch and cut with cookie cutter.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and bake in 375° oven for about 10-12 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen, depending on size of cookie cutter.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes if frozen.
Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package, using pineapple juice and enough water to equal liquid; add pineapple to batter. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let set overnight in fridge.

title: party cheese balls
directions: Mix all together.
Then roll in crushed nuts.

title: chicken creole
directions: Brown chicken in cooking spray.
Remove from skillet.
Saute in oil, onion, garlic, celery and bell pepper until tender.
Add parsley, pepper, salt and tomatoes.
Simmer for 6 minutes.
Add chicken to mixture and simmer for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: pecan tossies
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Chill slightly.
Shape into balls and press into small muffin tins.
Beat the egg.
Add brown sugar, 1 tablespoon butter, vanilla and salt.
Beat until smooth and add 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Fill each tossie almost full and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: veal scallopini a la marsala
directions: Cut
veal
into
large	slices;
season both sides with salt and
pepper
and
roll
slices
in	flour.	Saute veal in butter until well browned, but not singed.
Then place veal on serving platter.
Saute
mushrooms	in
butter
seasoned with garlic and add Marsala wine.
Cook 1 minute over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Add
water to the bottom of the skillet drippings, stirring
and
scraping the bottom to loosen brown bits.
Cook until
bubbly
and add mushrooms and Marsala mix. Pour contents of	the
skillet over the cooked veal and serve with side dishes of Italian spaghetti.

title: grandma's never fail pie crust
directions: Combine flour, shortening and salt.
Whip together vinegar, egg and water.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Makes enough for 2 large 2-crust pies.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream sugar and butter in a bowl.
Beat egg, then add egg, milk and molasses.
Sift flour, soda and ginger into mixture and beat well.
Bake in shallow greased pan (9-inch pie pan works well) at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: neapolitan pork chops
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with Season-All and brown in hot oil. Combine remaining ingredients, except olives, and pour over chops. Simmer 30 minutes or until chops are tender.
Stir in olives and serve over spaghetti or noodles.

title: divinity candy
directions: Boil sugar, corn syrup and water until thick.
Test by dropping small portion into cold water and it forms a small ball. Gradually pour over 2 beaten egg whites.
Add 1 tsp. vanilla and continue beating with mixer until shiny appearance is gone.
Put out by teaspoon on slightly buttered wax paper.

title: pecan sand tart cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all six ingredients.
Roll into small balls. Place onto cookie sheet and flatten slightly.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes.

title: `best' chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate; cream butter and sugar. Add eggs one at a time. Sift flour and add alternately with buttermilk. Add 1/2 cup hot water to chocolate mixture.
Bring the other 1/2 cup of water to a boil. Add soda to boiling water. Pour into chocolate batter and add vanilla. Mix well. Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.

title: peach dessert
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together until smooth. Put in a 9 or 10 inch square pan. Drain juice from sliced peaches and reserve. Arrange peaches on top of Bisquick. Whip together cream cheese, sugar and 3 Tbsp. peach juice. Drop by tablespoons on top. Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: overnight vegetable salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients until sugar is dissolved. Pour over remaining ingredients.
Mix well.

title: microwave caramels
directions: Melt butter in 4 quart bowl, then add rest of ingredients. Cook on high 18 to 20 minutes. Stir every 2 minutes with wooden spoon. Out of microwave, add 1 tsp. vanilla. Pour into buttered pan. Cut and wrap.

title: country company rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Scald milk.
Combine shortening, sugar and salt to milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Blend in egg.
Add these to flour mixture.
Can be stored at this point up to 2 days in the refrigerator.
Shape and brush with melted butter.
Cover; let rise.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble, cook and drain sausage.
Remove crust from bread, then butter and cut into cubes.
Place cubes in buttered 3-quart flat casserole dish.
Sprinkle with sausage (using all) and top with cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard.
Beat well. Pour over mixture in dish.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
(Good company breakfast.)

title: peaches and cream
directions: Grease bottom and sides of a 9 x 10-inch deep pie pan. Combine first 8 ingredients in a large mixer bowl, beat for 2 minutes and pour into pan.
Place peaches over batter.

title: cheese grits
directions: Bring water to a boil in 2-quart casserole.
Add grits; cover with wax paper and microwave on High 3 minutes.
Add butter and stir in eggs slowly.
Add chopped up cheese and stir until melted. Microwave, covered, on Medium for 8 minutes, turning 2 or 3 times.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and then add mayonnaise, lemon juice to individual taste and the same with the garlic salt.
Beat in mixer a few minutes and add shrimp and beat 30 seconds more.

title: salmon hash
directions: Remove and discard skin and bones from salmon; flake salmon with a fork and set aside.

title: chocolate shortbread
directions: In bowl, beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Mix in flour and cocoa powder.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Divide dough into thirds on baking sheets.
Shape each third into a 5-inch round, score wedges with knife, score decoratively with fork.
Attach dragees.
Bake 15 minutes until sets.
While warm, cut wedges through.
Makes 18 cookies.

title: mushroom hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cut crust off bread and roll flat.
Saute onion in oleo.
Add mushrooms; stir in flour, seasoning and sour cream.
Do not boil. Spread on bread and roll up.
Place on cookie sheet.
Brush each roll with melted oleo and freeze.
After frozen, cut each roll into quarters.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 4 dozen.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water. Add rest of water and frozen berries. Stir until well mixed. Let stand in refrigerator until it starts to thicken. Dip chunks of cake in mixture and put in whatever container you want until mixture is all used. (I use a Bundt pan.) Refrigerate overnight. Top with Cool Whip.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Cut veal into 2-inch pieces.
Shake in flour.
Season with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in a large skillet and brown veal in it.
Add onions and parsley; stir until onions brown.
Add mushrooms with their liquid, plus a little water.
Cover tightly and cook over low heat for 1 hour.
Add wine a half hour before done to avoid evaporation.
Serves 6.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add well beaten egg yolks and lemon extract.
Add flour; mix well.
Soak raisins and drain well.
I mix raisins, pecans and candied fruit in 1 cup of flour and coat well, then add this to your butter and sugar mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Pour mixture into loaf pans.
Decorate top with cherries and pecans.
Bake at 200° for 1 1/2 hours, then increase heat to 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 8 small foil pans or about 5 (2 pound) foil pans.

title: pineapple coconut chess pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large bowl; add eggs and vanilla.
Stir until blended.
Stir in butter, coconut and pineapple.
Pour in crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set. Cover with aluminum foil after 40 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach.
Drain.
Add soup mix and sour cream.
Put into greased casserole.
Top with stuffing and drizzle with butter. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: olive macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook macaroni according to box, then drain.
Add to other ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate. Makes great salad for summer barbecues.

title: steamed cabbage, carrots and potatoes
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add salt and chicken seasoning.
Add cabbage and cook about 7 minutes.
Add carrots, onions and potatoes.
Cook until tender.

title: coney sauce
directions: Brown and add 3 cups water and 1 tabkespoon flour to thicken.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Fold in remaining ingredients.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Beat
eggs;
add
all ingredients.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add marshmallows and dissolve, stirring constantly.
Add cranberry sauce, nuts and pineapple.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Coat beef with flour. Brown beef and onions in hot oil.
Add green pepper, garlic, paprika, salt, seasonings, tomatoes and water.
Simmer, uncovered, for 2 hours until meat is tender. Combine 3 tablespoons flour with 1/2 cup water. Blend into meat mixture. Bring to a boil.
Serve over noodles or potatoes.

title: molded banana split salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup juice.
In a small bowl, stir together 1/2 cup jello and reserved juice.
Pour into bottom of 5 cup mold.
Chill until almost set.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Brown meat and onion together; drain.
Add seasoning, tomatoes and beans if desired.
Cook together for 30 minutes or longer.
In bottom of medium size casserole dish, spread cream cheese which has softened.
Cover with chili, about 1/2 of it.
Cover with chopped cheese.
Put in microwave for 2 minutes or until cheese has melted.
Serve with Tostitos chips.

title: cucumbers in vinegar
directions: Slice cucumbers and onion into a serving bowl.
Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper in small mixing bowl.
Adjust sugar and vinegar to taste and pour over cucumber mixture covering entirely. Allow to marinate for a few hours in refrigerator.

title: cure of hoarseness
directions: Whip white of one
egg very stiff.
Add honey and juice from one lemon;
stir.
Add
whiskey
and stir.
Drink as much as necessary to cure hoarseness or laryngitis.
Keep remainder of mixture in refrigerator.

title: shrimp elegante
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add thawed shrimp and mushrooms and saute until shrimp turns pink.
Add salt, pepper, chili sauce and water.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat.
Add rice and simmer 5 minutes.
Combine sour cream and flour; add to rice mixture.
Heat through.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in bowl; mix until smooth.
Fold in Marshmallow Creme.
Serve with bite-size fruit.

title: tangy baked chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry. Combine red and black peppers.
Rub over chicken breasts. Combine salad dressing, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Lightly brush both sides of chicken with dressing mixture.
Place chicken in a shallow baking dish or pan. Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for about 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
In a small saucepan, heat any remaining dressing mixture just to boiling. Serve with chicken. Makes 4 servings.
Only 145 calories and 4 grams fat per serving. Goes great with Lemon-Pepper Potatoes.

title: greek salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender, adding salt and coarse pepper to taste.
Make salad using lettuce, cucumbers, onions, Greek olives and crumbled Feta cheese.
Pour dressing over salad just before serving.

title: uncle ray's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms; drain.
Remove stems.
Chop stems finely in large skillet.
Heat 1/4 cup butter.
Add onions, celery and stems.
Simmer until celery is tender.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and Accent.
Brush caps with butter.
Fill with onion mixture.
Arrange caps with stuffed side up in same skillet.
Simmer 5 minutes or until light brown.
Cover first 2 to 3 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in oven-proof casserole.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix.
Heat until thick, then mix in crushed pineapple.
Add this to first two layers and chill.
Top with more Cool Whip and garnish with pretzels.

title: spanish noodle casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef. Stir in corn, tomato sauce, mushroom soup, pepper and onion. Boil. Layer in baking dish. Place grated cheese on top. Place in oven until cheese melts.

title: easy baked bean enchiladas
directions: In a large skillet brown onions and garlic in olive oil for 3-5 minutes. Add beans, chiles, salt, pepper, cumin and Tabasco. Take off heat and add 1/4 c. cheese. Set aside. Open tortilla package but don't remove tortillas. Place in microwave on high for 1-1 1/2 minutes or until soft. Take each tortilla and fill with 2-3 spoonfuls of filling. Roll and place in rows on a 13 x 9 inch baking dish (glass works well). When pan is full and all bean filling is used, cover rolls with 2 cans tomatoes and remaining cup of cheese. Bake at 350° for 35-45 minutes until cheese is lightly brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; remove from bone and cut into bite size pieces. Melt margarine; stir melted margarine into stuffing.
Put half of the stuffing in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Make a layer of chicken and soup mixture.
To make soup mixture, mix 1 can of soup and enough broth to make 2 cups.
(I usually do this in a blender.)
Make another layer of stuffing, chicken and 2 more cups of soup mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly, about 45 minutes.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix all together and serve.
This will keep several days.

title: six-layer dinner
directions: Place layers in greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Season layers with all.
Garnish with green pepper slices.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: butterscotch chewy cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder.
Add all at once to the cooked mixture.
Mix until blended.
Stir in pecans or walnuts and vanilla.
Turn into well-greased and lightly floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in medium oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until it springs back when touched lightly in the center with the fingertips.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream or sprinkle while warm with confectioners sugar.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in double boiler.
Remove from heat. Add chow mein noodles.
Stir until noodles are covered.
Dip out by tablespoonful and place on wax paper.
Cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix the sugar, flour and salt.
Mix in the corn syrup, then add the eggs, milk and vanilla.
Stir until smooth, then stir in the pecans.
Bake for 1 hour.
Periodically check the nuts after 40 minutes so they don't burn.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Drain all fruit except applesauce and place in large bowl.
